title: zucchini with turkey sausage
directions: Layer in skillet the ingredients.
Add a little water.
Cover and simmer on low to medium heat for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cook hot peppers separately and for those who like hot peppers, stir them in at the table.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Mix next 3 ingredients together to make dressing.
Pour over salad and let set for at least 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: chocolate pistachio cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding, orange juice, water, eggs and oil in large mixing bowl.
Blend to moisten, then beat 2 minutes with electric beater. Pour about 3/4 of batter into well-greased and floured Bundt pan or 10-inch tube pan.
Add chocolate syrup to remaining batter.
Mix well; pour over batter in pan.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour or until done (test with cake tester).
Cool in pan on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan, cool and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: garden pasta salami salad
directions: Cook frozen vegetables and pasta as directed on package until vegetables are crisp-tender.
In large bowl, combine vegetables and pasta, salami, bell pepper and zucchini.
Drizzle with olive oil and vinegar; toss gently.
Cover; refrigerate 1 to 2 hours or until chilled.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add eggs, then flavorings. Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture, mixing well. Drop onto greased cookie sheet and bake in 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes. Sprinkle with sugar before baking. Makes 8 dozen.

title: sugar cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add cream; mix well.
Add butter and vanilla.
Mix well and pour in crust.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake 10 minutes at 425°, then 45 minutes at 325°.

title: no peekie stew
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a 3-quart casserole, combine meat, both soups, and water.
Mix well.
Cover and bake for 3 hours.
I sometimes put this mixture in the slow cooker for 6 hours.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix the ingredients.
Pour in Pyrex baking dish.
Cover with miniature marshmallows.
Brown in 325° oven.

title: apple brownies from maine
directions: Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
Do not overcook!
Bon appetit.

title: chocolate peanut butter cup cookies
directions: In a large bowl, cream together the butter, peanut butter, white sugar and brown sugar until smooth. Beat in the eggs one at a time, then stir in the vanilla. Combine the flour, cocoa and baking soda; stir into the peanut butter mixture. Mix in the chocolate chips, peanut butter chips and peanut butter cups. Drop by tablespoonfuls onto ungreased (or sprayed with Pam) cookie sheets. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°. Let cool for 1 or 2 minutes on sheet before removing. Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Crush yeast and sugar together; add warm water.
Add 1/4 of the total amount of the flour to the yeast mixture.
Cover and leave in a warm place to set (about 1 hour).

title: german potato salad
directions: Fry diced bacon; pour off most of the fat.
Add diced onion, then flour.
Mix sugar, vinegar and water in bowl and add to bacon pan.
Bring to a boil.
Have this on sliced potatoes for at least 1 hour before serving.
Serves 10 to 15 people.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain partially the fruit cocktail.
Do not drain pineapple. Add all fruit.
Add box of instant pudding; mix well.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: sweet potatoes nice and easy
directions: Drain yams.
Combine yams, pineapple, molasses and brown sugar.
Blend thoroughly until yams and mixture are completely mashed.
Put in casserole dish and cook for 1 hour at 350° or until potatoes are completely heated.
Remove from oven and put marshmallows on top.
Return to oven and broil for 1 minute until marshmallows are golden brown.

title: rich sweet dough
directions: Scald milk; stir in sugar, salt and margarine.
Cool to lukewarm.
Measure warm water into large warm bowl.
Sprinkle in yeast.
Stir until dissolved.
Stir in lukewarm milk mixture, egg and 1/2 the flour.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in remaining flour to make a stiff batter.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Refrigerate dough at least 2 hours (may be kept 3 days).
To use, cut up off amount needed and shape as desired.
Basis for cinnamon/nut/brown sugar tea ring or peanut braid bread or orange rolls or cinnamon crumb coffee cake.

title: yum-yum pie
directions: Blend cream cheese, milk and lemon juice until smooth.
Divide mixture and pour into each pie shell.
Divide pie filling and pour over cheese mixture.
Cover with Cool Whip (light).
Refrigerate several hours or overnight preferably.

title: pineapple-pecan cake
directions: Cream together eggs, sugar and margarine.
Add baking powder and pineapple.
Mix in cracker crumbs and pecans.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/4 hours in tube pan.

title: banana pudding
directions: Put milk in large mixing bowl.
Add the pudding mix and topping into the mixture, until it is well blended.
Place a layer of vanilla wafers on the bottom of large deep dish.

title: sugar-free peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven at 375°. Place dry ingredients in bowl. Mix peanut butter, oil, egg, water and vanilla together, then add to dry ingredients. Mix well. Roll in balls and place on cookie sheet. Flatten with fork. Bake 10 to 12 minutes, until brown.

title: chili beef potato soup
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add onion and celery.
Cook to crisp-tender.
Stir in tomatoes, potatoes, beef broth, water, chili powder, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and cook until potatoes are tender.
Stir in green beans.
Heat and serve.

title: cheese toast
directions: Place cheese on bread.
Toast in oven until cheese melts, about 2 minutes.
Sprinkle with sugar.

title: cream cheese beef bake
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Stir together cream cheese, sour cream and onion. Spread on noodles.
Brown beef; add pepper, sugar and tomato sauce.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Spoon beef mixture on top of noodles and cream cheese layers.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° if the mixture is freshly assembled.
One hour if mixture has been refrigerated. Makes 9 to 12 servings.

title: welsh rarebit
directions: Grate cheese.
Heat milk and melt butter; then beat it into the grated cheese with other ingredients.
Turn cheese mixture into a bowl and cover with foil.
Store in refrigerator.

title: zucchini or eggplant casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut squash in 1/4-inch slices.
Cook in boiling water until tender.
Drain.
Saute carrots and onions in 1/2 of margarine.
Remove from heat and stir in 1 1/2 cups stuffing cubes, soup and sour cream.
Gently stir in squash and place in greased casserole.
Melt remaining margarine and coat remaining stuffing cubes.
Spread on top of casserole.
Bake uncovered 30 to 40 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: In mixing bowl cream softened butter, sugar and egg.
Stir in dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture.
(Batter will be very thick.)
Stir in apples, nuts and vanilla.
Spread into a greased 8-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Serve warm or cold with whipped cream or ice cream.
Yields 9 servings.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt butter or margarine in heavy
saucepan.
Combine cocoa, sugar and eggs and add the butter, stirring all.
Stir in flour and beat mixture.
Add nuts and coconut and stir.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. While still hot, spread Marshmallow Creme over cake.
Frost cooled cake with frosting.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions, omitting salt. Place on paper towels and squeeze until barely moist. Set aside. Combine cheese and flour.
Set aside.
Combine eggs, milk, salt, pepper and nutmeg.

Stir in spinach and cheese until well blended. Pour mixture into a 9-inch deep dish pie plate coated with cooking spray. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until set. Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 8.

title: cheese crisp
directions: Fry flour tortillas (or brush with butter and bake) until crisp.
Sprinkle with cheese while hot.
Add warmed refried beans with onion, chilies and garlic seasoning added.
Fry hamburger; drain and add mushroom soup and rest of green chilies.
Add second layer of cheese to tortilla.
Top with meat mixture.
Top with lettuce, tomatoes and sour cream.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Cook noodles and set aside.
Combine soup, milk, water and cheese in saucepan. Cook until cheese is melted. Stir in turkey, noodles and pimentos.
Put this in baking dish.
Sprinkle crumbs, Parmesan cheese and parsley on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: fried mozzarella sandwiches
directions: Make 8 sandwiches with bread and cheese; slice diagonally to form 16 triangles.
In shallow dish, beat eggs and salt with fork. Dip all sides in mixture to coat, letting excess drop off.
Heat oil and butter in large nonstick skillet over medium heat.
Cook sandwiches 2 minutes on each side until golden brown and cheese starts to melt.
Drain on paper towels.
Serves as side dish with chili.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes; cut into wedges.
Put into 3-quart pot with water.
Boil until potatoes are tender.
Mix together all ingredients in large bowl.

title: chocolate chip snack cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the first 5 ingredients; beat for 5 minutes. Stir in chips and half of the grated chocolate. Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2 baking pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Sprinkle with remaining grated chocolate while warm. Dust with confectioners sugar.

title: apricot dream cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients for 2 minutes.
(Do not add water to gelatin.)
Pour into greased and floured angel food cake pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Let cool in pan, right side up, for 25 minutes.
Glaze immediately after removing cake from pan.

title: hot dog stew
directions: Put first three ingredients and 1 cup water in 3-quart pot. Bring to a boil and add potato and carrots.
Cover and let simmer 15 minutes.
Add peas and hot dogs.
Cover and simmer about 6 minutes longer.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Remove bay leaves and serve.
Yields 6 servings.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients.
Add powdered sugar until pie dough consistency (between 3/4 and 1 box powdered sugar).
May refrigerate up to 6 weeks.
Dip in melted chocolate and put on waxed paper until set.

title: aromatic yellow rice
directions: Wash rice in several changes of water.
Pour on fresh water and let soak for 1/2 hour. Drain.
Place rice, salt, turmeric, cardamon, cinnamon and bay leaves in a heavy pot.
Cover with 1-inch of water.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Combine milk and sugar.
Put on stove. Cook until a soft ball forms when a little of mixture is dropped in water.
Take off stove.
Add peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Beat and drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hidden valley ranch party pinwheels
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Spread on tortillas.
Sprinkle on remaining ingredients.
Roll and wrap tightly.
Chill 2 hours. Cut off ends and cut rolls into 1-inch slices.

title: italian rice
directions: Brown ground beef with onion, celery and bell pepper; drain. Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 30 minutes covered.

title: salmon loaf
directions: If using fresh salmon, skin and halve salmon.
Cook in boiling water, about 12 to 15 minutes or until meat comes away from the bone.
Remove and cool.
Remove bones and flake.

title: peach pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place fruit in a buttered 8 x 8-inch dish.
Cut crust of bread and cut each piece into 5 fingers. Place bread fingers over fruit.
In a bowl, mix sugar, flour, egg and butter; pour over fruit and bread.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes until brown.

title: sour cream quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie crust.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Melt margarine and
mix
cup
pecans and 1 cup plain flour. Press down in oblong Pyrex baking dish and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Mix
one
package
cream
cheese, 1 cup Cool Whip and 1 cup powdered
sugar;
spread on cooled crust.
Mix both packages of pudding
mix and 2 1/2 cups cold milk; spread on layer 2.
Spread on
remaining Cool Whip and decorate with chocolate sprinkles. Refrigerate.

title: sour cream pound cake(awarding winning recipe)
directions: Blend
butter,	sugar
and
egg
in
this order: all of butter, 1/2
to
1	cup sugar and one egg.	Blend and continue process
until
all
is
blended,
beating well.
Sift flour 3 times; add	to egg mixture with sour cream (1 cup flour with a portion
of
sour cream);
repeat, mixing on medium speed with electric
mixer.
Add
soda; blend.
Add flavoring.
Pour into well-greased
pan.	Line bottom of pan with greased wax paper. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Baking time may vary. Cake is
done when a wooden toothpick is inserted and it comes out dry.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Heat sugar and lemon juice.
Add beaten eggs and cook until thickened.
Remove from heat and add butter, marshmallows and whipped cream.
Next mix in fruit.
Freeze.

title: beef paprika
directions: Melt shortening in a large skillet.
Add meat, onions and garlic; cook and stir until meat is brown and onions are tender. Stir in catsup, Worcestershire sauce, sugar, salt, paprika, mustard, cayenne pepper and 1 1/2 cups water.
Cover; simmer 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: aunt pam's snack crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients together, then pour over the oyster crackers.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Store in an airtight container once cooled.

title: good cake
directions: Pour in powdered sugar.
Add 1 egg at a time.
Add 1 stick of butter at a time.
Pour flour in a little at a time.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: mammy's skillet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into prepared 9-inch skillet.
Bake 350 degrees for 25-30 minutes or until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: microwave peanut clusters
directions: Combine chocolate and butterscotch pieces; cook on Medium for 5 to 6 minutes, stirring once.
Stir in peanuts when pieces are completely melted.
Drop by teaspoons on waxed paper.
Refrigerate until hard.
Quick and easy candy.

title: neiman-marcus cake(from grit)
directions: Combine dry cake mix, melted butter and 2 eggs.
Press into greased and floured pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown, about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: yellow rice and chicken
directions: Grease baking dish.
Place one serving of rice (per person); place piece of chicken (meat side up).
Sprinkle soup mix on top. Add can of soup.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: delicioso spaghetti salad
directions: Cook pasta as directed on package.
Drain and rinse in cold water.
Mix together remaining ingredients and pour over pasta and mix.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes excellent passing dish since it makes a lot.

title: watergate salad(full of fruits and nuts)
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: aunt kara's soft sugar cookies
directions: Beat butter, sugar, egg, milk and vanilla in electric mixer for 2 minutes or by hand until well blended.
Sift together the salt, baking powder and flour.
Add to butter mixture and blend well.
Form the dough (which will be sticky) into a ball and refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Mix all liquids together and add rice.
Put 1/2 mixture in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add chicken and rest of liquid. Sprinkle with nuts and cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 275° for 2 1/4 hours.

title: sweet potato snowball
directions: Mix ingredients into a ball and roll in marshmallows.
Then roll in coconut.
Place in oven to brown.
Turn so all sides will brown.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Tear lettuce and place in bottom of large salad bowl or casserole dish.
Crumble bacon on top of lettuce.
Slice onion and layer next.
Drain peas and layer.
Slice eggs and layer.

title: cabbage and conecuh sausage
directions: Cut sausage in small pieces; put in water and boil for 10 minutes.
Wash and cut up cabbage; pour in water with sausage and cook until tender.
Salt to taste.
Very good.

title: fat-free catalina dressing
directions: In small saucepan, put water and gelatin and heat slowly until gelatin dissolves.
Remove from heat and add other ingredients (liquids first).
Beat mixture well with a wire whip,
Pour into jar.
Cover and refrigerate.
If dressing thickens while in refrigerator, stir or shake before using.

title: potatoes and sausage
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Rinse and drain.
Cut up sausage and shred cheese.
Dice onion.
Pour milk in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan (enough to cover ingredients).
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 1 hour or until potatoes are tender. Serve as is or with a vegetable.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream margarine.
Add sugar and mix until light and fluffy. Add flavoring.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Fold in flour a cup at a time.
Stir in coconut and mix thoroughly. Spoon batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350° or until cake is done.
Let cool 5 minutes and turn onto cake plate.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Crumble ground beef into 2-quart casserole.
Add onion; microwave on High 4 to 6 minutes.
Break up meat and drain. Microwave vegetables in package on High 2 to 3 1/2 minutes, or until defrosted.
Stir soup, sauce, salt, basil and pepper into ground beef.
Spread evenly in casserole.
Sprinkle meat with mixed vegetables.
Mound potatoes over vegetables.
Microwave 5 to 7 minutes, until done.
Top with cheese.
Microwave 2 to 3 1/2 minutes.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into large bowl; add remaining ingredients.
Mix but do not beat.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Let stand in pan 20 minutes before removing.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken.
Skin and bone chicken.
In a large bowl, combine mushroom soup, chicken soup, Ro-Tel tomatoes, onion and pepper.
Stir until well blended.
Add chicken and mix well.
In a baking pan, layer Doritos, chicken mixture and cheese.
Repeat until all ingredients are used.
Pour 1/2 cup of chicken broth on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken; pull from bone.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° until crust is brown.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken breasts. Line large casserole with crushed chips. Add in this order: chicken, onions, salt, mushroom soup, tomatoes (drain 1/2 the liquid before adding tomatoes), peppers, chicken soup and grated cheese. Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 40 minutes. (Remove foil for last 20 minutes.)

title: casserole for a crowd
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain.
Drain corn.
Combine cream of chicken soup, cream of mushroom soup, corn, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Add hamburger.
Mix well.
Stir in noodles, cooked and drained.
Place in a 2 1/2-quart casserole. Combine bread crumbs and butter.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot.

title: slush punch
directions: Mix sugar and water in a large pot.
Boil until syrupy. Remove from heat and stir in jello until dissolved.
Add frozen juices, pineapple juice, almond extract and water.
Mix well. Pour into jugs or empty drink bottles and freeze.
Thaw 2 hours before serving.

title: beef-a-la-royal(fukuoka, japan)
directions: Saute onions and peas in butter until onions are still crunchy and peas still bright green.
Remove from pan and set aside for later.
Shake flour and beef together in paper bag.
Remove beef and brown lightly in 2 tablespoons oil.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until sauce is thickened.
Stir to keep from sticking. Just before serving, add onions and peas.
Serve over steamed rice.
No salt in recipe!

title: snack crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients, except crackers.
Stir in crackers, coating them well.
Bake on a cookie sheet at 225° for 1 hour. Stir occasionally.
Very tasty!

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix well in medium size bowl.
Add food coloring for appeal. Chill 2 hours before serving.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Dissolve strawberry Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water. Add frozen strawberries and cook until thawed. Set aside this mixture to cool; do not let it gel.

title: fudge pudding pops
directions: Beat pudding mix and milk until smooth.
Spoon pudding into paper cups.
Put a wooden stick into each pudding pop.
Put pops in the freezer until frozen.

title: glaze for bundt cakes
directions: In saucepan, mix and cook over medium heat.
Stir and boil for 10 minutes.
Pour over warm yellow Bundt cake.

title: steak fries tavern style
directions: Coat potatoes with nonstick cooking spray.
Use only salt and pepper or add hot chili pepper.
Sprinkle over potatoes.
(You may make mix using all spices.
Place in plastic bag and toss potatoes until coated.)
Place on baking pan and place in hot oven at 425° for 45 minutes or until crisp and golden.

title: lemon and garlic roast pork
directions: Trim fat from pork.
Combine next 5 ingredients in a small bowl; stir well and rub evenly over pork.

title: baked tenderloin
directions: Mix marinade ingredients together in a saucepan and heat until hot.
Place tenderloin in pan.
Pour marinade over tenderloin. Bake 40 to 50 minutes for medium rare in a 350° oven.

title: ground beef and wild rice casserole
directions: Pour boiling water over rice.
Let stand 15 minutes and drain. Brown onion in fat; add meat and brown.
Combine all ingredients. Let stand in casserole overnight.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Yield:
12 servings.

title: chicken in orange sauce
directions: Brown chicken in butter.
Salt lightly.
Remove chicken and mix in with butter, 2 tablespoons flour, cinnamon and ginger to form paste.
Add orange juice.
Return chicken to pan and add oranges, raisins and almonds.
Simmer about 1 hour.

title: old fashioned stack cake
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat well. Stir in molasses.
Sift flour with spices.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk into which baking soda has been stirred.
Use 2 cast-iron skillets for baking which have been greased and sprinkled lightly with flour.
Warm skillets.
Dip 2 heaping tablespoonfuls of dough which should be rather stiff, into center of each skillet.
Wet hand in ice cold water and pat dough toward sides of skillet.
Make a very thin layer.
Bake at 375°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together all the ingredients and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake in a 375° oven for 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: school teacher's hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add oil. Knead.
(Don't be lazy.
The more kneading you do, the better they are!)
Roll out.
Shape into rolls and let rise for 30 minutes. Bake at 425° for 12 minutes or until brown.
Yield: 1 dozen.

title: crescent cheese steak braid(uses flat stone)
directions: Cook steaks, remove from skillet.
Add onion and pepper; cook until crisp-tender.
Unroll 1 can of dough into 2 long rectangles onto stone.
Overlap one side to form 13 x 7-inch rectangle. Firmly press perforations to seal.
Place meat down center of dough.
Place cheese over meat.
Make 1 inch cuts on each side of rectangle just to edge of filling.
Fold ends of dough at an angle halfway across filling, alternating from side to side to give a braided look.
Fold ends under to seal.
Repeat with remaining ingredients to make a second braid.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 22 minutes.

title: make ahead fruit salad
directions: Fold together all ingredients in serving bowl.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
If desired, sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: garden tomato salad
directions: Use equal amounts of vinegar, sugar and dill weed.
Marinate the tomatoes in all.
Chill and serve.

title: coconut icing
directions: Beat egg yolks. Add milk, sugar and butter. Cook over medium heat for about 12 minutes, stirring constantly until mixture thickens. Remove from heat; add coconut, nuts and vanilla. Spread on cake.

title: cheese bread sticks
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
On lightly floured surface, roll out dough to 1/8-inch thickness (about 12 x 8-inch rectangle). Spread with margarine. Sprinkle with cheese.
Cut into 32 sticks (6 x 1/2-inch).
Place on prepared cookie sheet.
Bake 7 minutes or until lightly browned. Serve warm.
Makes 32 bread sticks.

title: oahu frappe
directions: Combine sugar and water in saucepan, stirring to dissolve sugar.
Bring to a boil; cook for 5 minutes.
Cool syrup to room temperature; add fruit juices.
Freeze until mushy.
Serve in chilled sherbet glasses.
Serves 6.

title: ham-potato chowder
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
In large saucepan, melt butter.
Add onions and pepper and cook until tender.
Add potatoes, water and seasonings.
Cover and cook until tender.
Make paste of flour and milk.
Add to potato mixture.
Add rest of milk and cook until thickened; stir in corn and ham.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 475 degrees.
Pour 1/4 cup of bacon grease into 12-inch iron skillet and let sit in oven while mixing ingredients together.
Mix above ingredients together and bake 25 to 30 minutes or until top is light golden brown.

title: easy broccoli casserole
directions: Cook the beef Rice-A-Roni to directions and cook the broccoli to directions, drained. Then in a casserole dish add the Rice-A-Roni, broccoli, Cheez Whiz, cream of mushroom soup and water chestnuts; stir together until well mixed.
Then cook in the oven at 350° for about 20 to 30 minutes until it looks golden brown on top.

title: glazed baby carrots
directions: Cook carrots in a small amount of boiling water 5 minutes or until crisp-tender; drain.
Melt butter in a small saucepan.
Add brown sugar, pineapple juice and ginger.
Pour mixture over carrots and toss gently.
Yields 4 servings.

title: punch bowl dessert
directions: Bake cake, cool and crumble.
Start layering in punch bowl with 1/2 cake first, then 1/2 pudding, 1/2 pineapple, 1/2 cup whipping cream, 1/2 nuts and 1/2 coconut.
Add all pie filling. Continue remaining ingredients in the same order, ending with whipped cream, nuts and coconut.
Serves 20.
You may substitute vanilla or any other flavor instant pudding if desired.

title: elbow macaroni and chopped meat
directions: Bring salted water to a boil. Add macaroni and cook 8 to 11 minutes; drain.
Heat margarine or oil in frying pan.

Add chopped meat and stir until lightly browned. Add onion and finish browning. Add red wine, beef stock, tomato, salt and pepper. Cook, covered, about 15 minutes over low heat, uncovering towards end of cooking time in order to cook down the liquid. Add chopped herbs.

title: ravioli
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients and knead lightly and place back in bowl, cover and let set while mixing other ingredients. Combine nest 5 ingredients in pan and brown in oil.
Set aside to cool.
When the meat mixture has cooled enough to put your hands in it add these ingredients to it and mix it together really well. Large jar of Ragu Sauce of your choice.
Parmesan cheese grated. Blue cheese if you like it.
Put a pot of water on to boil for ravioli.
Put some Ragu sauce of you choice on to heat up really hot.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cream butter and sugar.
Mix all ingredients.
Chill dough.
Roll thinly and cut with cookie cutters.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and lard.
Add the molasses; mix.
Add the 2 cups of flour, ginger, soda, cloves and salt alternately with the cold water.
Add up to 1 to 1 1/2 cups more flour (still enough to handle).
Roll in walnut size; dip in sugar.
Bake in moderate oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: apple crunch salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water or juice and cinnamon and chill until thickened.
Fold in apple, celery and nuts.
Spoon into mold or bowl.
Chill until firm, about 4 hours. Makes 5 cups or 10 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix well.
Shape into balls the size of walnuts.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and press with fork.
Bake at 325° until light brown.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Peel and quarter apples.
Divide each biscuit into two parts. Roll thin; wrap around 1/4 of apple.
Melt margarine in baking dish.
Place wrapped apples in dish.
I put them in, then turn them over to get both sides covered.
Bring sugar, water with juice, cinnamon and salt added to a boil.
Pour over apples.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: walnut cluster cookies
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Beat margarine, sugar, egg and vanilla until fluffy, about 3 minutes.
Fold in flour mixture.
Fold in walnuts.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on lightly greased sheets.
Beat egg white and teaspoon of water in a cup until just combined.
Brush over cookies.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until firm.
Cool on racks.

title: chicken breast diane
directions: Place chicken breasts between wax paper, pound slightly with mallet and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Heat 1 tablespoon each oil and margarine in large skillet.
Cook chicken on high 4 minutes on each side.
Transfer to serving platter.
Add chives, lemon juice, parsley and mustard to pan.
Cook 30 seconds whisking constantly.
Whisk in broth.
Stir until sauce is smooth.
Whisk in remaining margarine and oil.
Pour sauce over chicken and serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: cereal crunch
directions: Mix dry ingredients together in a large bowl.
Melt white chocolate over very low heat.
Pour over cereal mix and stir well. Pour out on cookie sheet to cool.
Break in pieces.

title: rice dressing
directions: Melt butter.
Saute sausage, celery, onion and rice.
Add mushroom soup and 3 cans of water. Put on low heat for one hour on top of stove.
Stir often to keep from sticking.
Serves approximately 12 people.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Combine the flour, cocoa, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Set aside.
Beat together butter and sugar until smooth. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Stir in vanilla, orange peel and zucchini.
Alternately stir in dry ingredients and milk to zucchini mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake for about 1 hour at 350°. Glaze with 2 cups powdered sugar, 3 tablespoons milk and 1 teaspoon vanilla.

title: indian relish
directions: Put apples, tomatoes, onions and green peppers through food chopper.
Combine with vinegar, brown sugar, salt and spices.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until most of liquid has evaporated.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal immediately.
Makes 10 pints.

title: fried shrimp
directions: Beat the eggs and add the milk.
Clean the shrimp and split down the back to "butterfly".
Dip in the seasoned flour, then the eggs and milk, then in the saltines.
Fry in deep fat until golden brown.
Serve with a good cocktail sauce or remoulade.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer together about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: french dressing with horseradish
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender and beat until well blended.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Cut cucumbers in slices.
Put cucumbers and lime in water. Soak for 24 hours; rinse 3 times in cold water.
Soak 3 hours in ice cold water; drain.
Mix the vinegar, sugar, salt and pickling spice.
Put cucumbers in to soak overnight.
Boil for 35 minutes. Put in jars.
Makes about 9 to 11 pints.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix and serve with Triscuits or Ritz or your choice.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Add cheese, eggs and salt and pepper to taste.
Pour butter and milk over macaroni.
Stir and bake at 375° for approximately 30 minutes or until bubbly and brown.

title: watermelon boat
directions: Cut top out of watermelon.
Use a melon ball scooper to take all the watermelon out.
Cut around the edges of the watermelon in a scalloped pattern, while making the watermelon look like a large canoe or boat.

title: lena's baked veggies
directions: Cut vegetables in 1/4-inch slices except cauliflower (break in small pieces). In large bowl, pour over 2 to 3 tablespoons of low-fat Italian dressing until all vegetables are coated well.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Saute
onion
in
melted butter until slightly browned. Stir in flour and seasoning.
Remove from heat; gradually stir in milk.
Return
to
heat;
boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly. Remove
from
heat	and
stir
in corn and egg; pour mixture
into a	greased
1-quart baking dish.
Combine 1 cup cracker
crumbs and
5 tablespoons melted margarine; sprinkle over casserole and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chuck wagon macaroni
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Saute onions and peppers; add to beef.
Add cream corn, tomato sauce and macaroni and cheese to beef mixture.
Pour into a well-greased 9 x 13 x 3-inch baking dish.
Cover with cheese and bake at 375° until cheese is well melted.

title: pineapple lime mold
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve syrup. Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups boiling water. Add sour cream and reserved syrup.
Chill until slightly thickened. Stir in pineapple, walnuts and celery.
Pour into 7-cup mold.
Chill until set. Serves 6.

title: chicken paprikas
directions: Brown chicken and onion with a little oil in a large saucepan. Then add tomato sauce, paprika, 2 cups water and cook over medium until chicken is done.
Add sour cream and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Serve over cooked macaroni.

title: squash casserole
directions: In a large, flat baking dish, 8 x 11-inch, pour half of dressing.
Melt margarine and pour over dressing.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour into baking dish, then sprinkle remaining herb dressing over squash mixture.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in 350° oven, until brown.

title: frozen citrus pie
directions: Place lemonade in a large bowl and beat about 30 seconds. Gradually spoon in ice cream and blend.
Fold in whipped topping and add food coloring (if desired), whipping until smooth. Freeze, if necessary.
Spoon into pie crust.
Freeze until firm, at least 4 hours.
Store leftovers in freezer.

title: gold rush pork chops
directions: Crab is abundant in Puget Sound.
A good day's outing was (still is!) to boat to a favorite crabbing spot.

title: mexican enchilada casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325° to 350°.
In skillet, brown meat.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add soups and sauce to meat and mix well and simmer for a few minutes.
Line baking dish with tortillas and meat mixture.
Top off with grated cheese and onions.
Bake at 325° to 350° about 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Can be made ahead and frozen.

title: cathy's punch
directions: Mix strawberry daiquiri with punch. Add ginger ale last.
Then scoop in sherbet last and garnish with orange and lemon slices and strawberry ice.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: cinnamon cheesecake
directions: Press one package of crescent rolls into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan; push out to sides of pan.
Pinch all the holes together.
Take 1 cup of sugar, cream cheese and vanilla; beat together until smooth and creamy.
Pour into pan and spread.
Take other package of crescent rolls, put on wax paper and push out to cover cheese mixture.
Pinch holes together.
Put over the cheese mixture.
Pour melted margarine over top evenly.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: english toffee
directions: Put 1 cup nuts on jelly roll pan.
In saucepan (use a heavy bottom pan to cook in).
Boil butter and sugar until the snap stage on candy thermometer, stirring constantly.
Pour over nuts.
Cool in refrigerator until hard.
Melt chocolate in double boiler. Spread over toffee.
Put rest of nuts on top of chocolate while still hot.
Cool.
Break apart.

title: pear bread
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Mix
the
flour, germ, sugar, baking powder, salt and coriander in 1 bowl.
In another bowl mix
the yogurt,
eggs, milk and oil.
Combine the 2 mixtures and gently fold in the pears by hand.	Pour the mixture into a greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: cream puffs
directions: Bring water, salt and butter to boil.
Add flour and stir until smooth and leaves the sides of pan.
Cool slightly, then stir in one egg at a time.
Drop by large rounded teaspoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until they are browned and look dry (about 30 minutes).

title: strawberry pie
directions: Blend together.
Cook until clear and take from stove.
Add 1 tablespoon of lemon juice.
Add red food coloring.
Cool and add 1-quart strawberries and pour into a baked pie shell.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Combine crumbs and butter; press into an 8-inch pan. Bake 8 minutes at 350°. Saute onions in oil until tender; put into shells. Mix remaining ingredients, except cheese. Pour over onions. Top with cheese and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: monster cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix in dishpan in order given.
Drop by large tablespoon.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 124 cookies.

title: flowlyn cymreig(welch chicken)
directions: Cut the bacon and carrots into small pieces and fry in butter until just brown.
Put the chicken on top of this in a heavy pan with leeks, herbs and seasoning.
Pour in stock, dot chicken with butter.
Cover and simmer for 2 to 3 hours for a boiling chicken, less for a roasting chicken.
Cook cabbage separately and make a bed of it on which to serve the chicken surrounded by the vegetables.
Boil stock, thicken with 1 ounce flour and 1 ounce butter and pour around chicken or serve separately.

title: chocolate pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix ingredients together. Cook until thick. Pour into baked pie shell and cover with egg whites, beaten real stiff with a little sugar. Brown in oven until golden brown.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix ingredients, adding cheese last. Pour into greased baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Mix buttermilk baking mix, water and minced scallion greens with a fork until blended.
Cut chicken in 1-inch pieces.
Put in large, nonstick skillet and stir in chicken gravy, frozen peas and carrots and sliced white part of scallions.
Bring to a boil, stirring a few times.
Reduce heat and drop 8 large spoonfuls dough on chicken mixture.
Simmer uncovered 10 minutes.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes more until chicken is no longer pink in center.

title: oatmeal coconut cookies
directions: Blend together butter, margarine and sugars.
Add 2 eggs.
Mix well.
Add all other ingredients, mixing well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: vegetable medley casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish.
(Size depends on how many eating.) Peel and slice potatoes, making first layer in dish.
Next, make a layer of sliced onions.
Next, layer of sliced carrots, then layer of celery.
Top with layer of ground beef.
Pour can of soup on, then salt and pepper. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: almond cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and Crisco shortening.
Add egg yolks, almond extract and yellow food coloring.
Add and mix salt, baking soda and flour.
After mixing everything, make a small ball for cookie (about the size of a golf ball).
Put a small hole in the bottom of cookie with finger (do not go all the way through). Place on slightly greased cookie sheet.
Dip raw almonds in egg whites and place almonds in center of cookie.
Put a pan of water on the last rack in the oven (to keep moisture in).
Place cookies on the rack above pan of water (middle rack).
Bake at 300° for 20 to 45 minutes, depending on size of the cookie.

title: crock-pot potatoes
directions: Put soups, potatoes and onion in crock-pot and cook on high all day; stir often.
Add ham and heat until warm.
Serve with a salad, roll and butter to complete meal.

title: classic pecan pie
directions: Stir together the first 5 ingredients until blended.
Add pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven 50 to 60 minutes.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix broken pretzels, melted butter and 1 tablespoon sugar together.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: broccoli, potato, cheese soup
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
DO NOT DRAIN.
Mash in the pan it was cooked in.
Add 12 ounces lite Velveeta cheese; heat, stirring constantly.
DO NOT BOIL.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Use crumbled cooked Tennessee Pride Country sausage moistened with beaten egg for filling party pinwheels.
For variety, blend spicy apple butter with sausage before spreading on dough and rolling.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: tex-mex layered dip
directions: Layer above ingredients in a quiche dish. (Use a very thin layer of picante sauce.) Add topping.
Chill several hours. Serve with taco chips.

title: french bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and knead for several minutes.
Place in large pan to rise. Brush top with small amount of shortening.
Let rise twice.
Form into long loaf.
Place on greased pan (cookie sheet is ideal) covered with corn meal.
Slash at 2-inch intervals.
Brush with cold water.
Leave uncovered until dough has risen to at least double its size.
Brush again with cold water and sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: escalloped oysters
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 2-quart baking dish.
Into dish, layer oysters, parsley and celery twice.
Top with salt, pepper and dots of the butter.
Top all with cracker crumbs.
Pour oyster liquid from can over all.
Punch holes in mixture and pour a little milk into each hole.
(Just pour enough milk to get the whole mixture moist.)
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: banana bread - guatemala(pan de banano)
directions: Soften butter at room temperature and cream it with the sugar in a mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Mashed the bananas and add to the butter and sugar mixture.
Add the salt, cinnamon, lemon juice and egg.
Sift the flour with the baking powder and fold it into the liquid mixture.
Pour the batter into a greased 9 x 5 inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350 for 1 hour or until a cake tester comes out clean.
You can serve with honey, pudding or ice cream.

title: mary jezek's broccoli dip
directions: Cook broccoli and drain well.
Saute onions in margarine.
Add soup, cheese and seasonings.
Cook on medium heat until cheese melts.
Add broccoli and cook 1 minute.
Stir to blend ingredients.
Add drained mushrooms and almonds.
Serve hot.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Prepare roast (or use leftovers), trimming all fat.
Save broth.
Cut meat fine and set aside.
Cut everything fine. Combine celery, carrots, onion and cabbage together with approximately 1 quart water; simmer until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.
Makes a large kettle.

title: polenta crusted brie(with brandied pear-cranberry salsa)
directions: Cut cheese into 8 wedges; set aside.
Stir together the flour and salt in a shallow dish.
Whisk together the egg and milk in a small mixing bowl.
Stir together cornmeal and cinnamon in another shallow dish.
Heat oil for deep frying to 365° in a heavy 3-quart saucepan or deep fryer.
Coat each piece of cheese with the flour mixture.
Dip into egg mixture, then into cornmeal mixture, being sure to coat entire wedge.
Gently lower cheese wedges, 2 at a time, into hot oil for 40-60 seconds, or until golden brown. Using a slotted spoon, transfer to paper towels to drain.
Serve with Brandied Pear-Cranberry Salsa.
Makes 8 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together and let sit in refrigerator several hours or overnight.
Before serving, add crumbled bacon bits.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Butter pan.
Add rice.
Sprinkle onion soup over rice.
Add consomme.
Place chicken in pan, skin up.
Bake at 325° for 2 1/2 hours.
When chicken is light brown, cover with foil.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken, then cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
While spaghetti is cooking, mix chicken with soups and Ro-Tel.
In a large pot on stove top, add spaghetti.
Mix and heat everything, then add cheese and cook until melted.

title: pecan spread
directions: Rinse beef as directed on jar.
Mix all and put in a Pyrex pie plate.
Top with 1/2 cup chopped pecans that have been heated in 1 tablespoon oleo and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: steam fry turtle
directions: Moisten prepared turtle in a bowl of water.
Hand roll turtle in flour and meal, 3 parts flour and 1 part meal.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Fry at low temperature approximately 1 hour under covered pan.
Electric skillet best.
Use vegetable oil or shortening.
Brown and serve.

title: cream of chicken soup
directions: In a large saucepan, melt butter or margarine.
Stir in flour. Stir in milk, cream and broth. Cook until mixture is slightly thickened and bubbly. Reduce heat.
Stir in chicken, dash of pepper or 1/4 teaspoon Mrs. Dash table blend, vegetables and rice. Cook and stir until rice is tender and heated through.
Yields 4 servings.

title: spaghetti deluxe
directions: Cook spaghetti, then rinse with cold water and drain.
Put spaghetti in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Pour over oleo.
Brown ground beef.
Mix tomato soup with beef.
Add water.
Add tomato bits, garlic, grated cheese, half and half, mushrooms, oregano, basil and rosemary and mix well.
Pour beef mixture over spaghetti and mix well.
Top with grated Mozzarella or Parmesan cheese. Bake 30 minutes at 350° (can be frozen unbaked).
Cover with aluminum foil.

title: johnny's dock butter rum batter
directions: Mix thoroughly and keep refrigerated.
Lasts forever.

title: meat loaf
directions: Add
bread slices to ground beef.
Add all other ingredients and
mix
well.
Form
into loaf and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine first three ingredients in a bowl. refrigerate for 30 minutes. Shape mixture into a ball and roll in chopped pecans, coating thoroughly. Serve with crackers.

title: deluxe rolls
directions: Soften yeast in water.
Add a sprinkle of sugar to help yeast act faster and stir.
Put shortening, sugar and milk in a pan and warm.
Watch that it doesn't scorch.
Cool.
Add yeast mixture and stir.
Add eggs and mix.
Add flour and salt.
Mix gradually and let rise double.
Work dough good.
Make into rolls and let rise. Bake at 375° until golden brown, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Heat sugar and milk; add caramels, after caramels have melted, boil 4 minutes. Remove from heat, add chocolate chips, stir. Add vanilla and peanuts. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper. WORK QUICKLY. Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook hamburger and drain.
Mix beans, ketchup, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, onion, sugar and meat.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: paska (slovak easter bread)
directions: Crumble yeast into small
bowl; add 1 tablespoon sugar, 1 cup lukewarm milk and 1
cup
flour.
Mix
and
set aside to rise. Cream butter and 1
cup
of
sugar;
add
eggs
and mix well.
To egg mixture,
add
remaining flour, alternating with yeast mixture and remaining milk.
Knead until dough is smooth and elastic. Place in greased
bowl;
cover
and set aside in warm
place until doubled
in
bulk.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix flour and sugar; add water and vinegar.
Cook over low heat until thickened; add salt and butter, then diced beets.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix well and chill at least 8 hours.
Put in foil cup cake liners; freeze until needed.

title: butternut squash pie
directions: In a large bowl, place squash, sugar, salt, ginger, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and molasses.
Mix together eggs and milk and add to mixture.
Put into unbaked pie shell and sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake 20 minutes at 425°, then 45 minutes at 375°.

title: dessert salad
directions: Combine jello, boiling water, and sugar and let jell to thick syrup. Then whip slightly. Add remaining ingredients.

Pour into 9 inch square pan. Top with maraschino cherry halves if desired. Refrigerate for several hours. This salad makes an excellent late evening dessert. Serve with crackers (Triscuits, Wheat Thins, etc.) or even with hot rolls. Coffee, of course!

title: jailhouse chili
directions: Cover beans with water and soak overnight. Add 1 teaspoon salt and simmer 1 hour or until beans are almost tender.
Drain and set aside.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice cookie dough like you are making cookies and lay out on pizza pan.
Press dough together.
Cook cookies and let cool.

title: chicken pasta
directions: Dust chicken with flour, salt and pepper.
Saute chicken in butter and garlic over medium heat 1 to 2 minutes.
Add peppers, mushrooms and artichokes.
Saute 5 to 10 minutes more.
Add sherry, whipping cream
and chicken stock mixed with cooked linguini.
Don't overcook.

title: snappy barbecue beef sandwiches
directions: Place beef in a Dutch oven.
Combine all ingredients; pour over beef.
Cover and bake at 350° for 5 hours, turning occasionally.
Shred beef with a fork.
Serve on rolls or buns. Makes 24 servings.

title: the best meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add water as needed.
Form into balls.
Roll in flour.
Brown in small amount of hot olive oil. Add to your favorite spaghetti sauce.

title: chocolate turtles
directions: Place pecan halves in 6 groups of 3 in a ring.
Top each one with a caramel.
Bake 2 to 3 minutes or until caramels are softened (not melted).
Melt chocolate morsels; stir occasionally. Spread 1/2 teaspoon of chocolate over each caramel.
Chill for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: scripture cookies
directions: Beat together first 4 items.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: as you like it macaroni
directions: Pour all together, except American cheese, in a 2-quart casserole and bake 30 minutes, having put the slices of American cheese on the top.

title: potato bake
directions: Wash and cut potatoes in large slices.
Place in baking dish with onion rounds. Spoon mushroom soup on top. Add 1/2 cup water and parsley flakes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with foil. Bake in oven until tender, 30 to 45 minutes at 400°.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell. Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350°
for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: baked celery
directions: Cook celery in saucepan for 10 minutes.
Drain liquid in measuring cup and add milk to make 1 cup.
Make a thin cream sauce by melting the butter, stirring in the flour, then blending in the celery liquid and milk.
Cook, stirring until thickened and smooth.
Add the salt.
Place half the cooked celery in a buttered 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with half the almonds and half the noodles.
Add remainder of the celery, almonds and noodles.
Pour the sauce over all.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix as for pastry:
2 cups flour, 4x sugar and butter or margarine.
Press into sheet pan.
Bake in 350° oven for about 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Beat together eggs, sugar and lemon juice.
Sift 1/4 cup flour and baking powder.
Stir into egg mixture.
Pour over baked crust.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Cut into bars.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush the Oreo cookies; set aside.
Cream together the cream cheese, butter and 10x sugar.
Mix the milk, pudding and Cool Whip separately.
Add cheese mixture to milk mixture; mix well.
Take the plastic top of Cool Whip container and place in bottom of 8-inch flowerpot (plastic).
Layer crushed cookies in the bottom, then layer cream cheese mix.
Continue alternating.
End up with cookies on top.
(Looks like dirt.)
Refrigerate a few hours or overnight (firm).
Decorate with gummy worms and frogs.
Place silk flower in pot.
Serve with a clean trowel.

title: broccoli and ham casserole
directions: Saute onions and mushrooms in butter until tender.
Add soup and stir well.
Gradually add milk.
Grease a 3-quart casserole dish and put 1/3 of cooked broccoli in bottom.
Season with salt, pepper and paprika.
Fill casserole dish in layers (1/3 of ham, 1/3 sauce and 1/3 stuffing mix).
Repeat until gone, ending with topping of bread mix.
Dot with butter and bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: garden vegetable soup(lo-cal)
directions: Combine all ingredients; bring to boil.
Reduce heat to medium-low; simmer, partially covered, until vegetables are tender, 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve hot.
Serves 4.
Low calorie, only 64 per serving.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: Pour all dry ingredients into sifter and sift into 9 x 9-inch ungreased cake pan.
Make 3 holes in dry ingredients.
Into 1st hole put vinegar, 2nd hole vanilla and 3rd hole vegetable oil. Pour cold water over all.
Stir with a fork until mixed.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Shred cheese and mix with the other ingredients until well blended.
Roll into small balls, about the size of a teaspoon. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes until brown.
If not brown enough, turn on broiler for approximately 2 minutes.

title: heavenly white cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together into a big bowl.
Add shortening and 2/3 cup orange juice, unbeaten egg whites and orange rind. Beat again for 2 minutes.
Pour the thin batter into 2 layer pans, lined with waxed paper.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix and drop balls on a cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Let cool.
Cream the cream cheese with gelatin.
Add oranges and pineapple to gelatin mix. Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Combine chocolate, butterscotch and peanut butter morsels in a 2-quart bowl.
Heat in microwave for 1 1/2 to 3 minutes, or until melted.
Stir in peanuts.
Drop onto wax paper with a teaspoon. Refrigerate in airtight container.

title: grandma's hassepfeffer
directions: Combine all ingredients except the rabbit and pour over rabbit.
Let stand in cool place for 2 days.
Remove rabbit and drain and dry.
Roll in flour; brown in hot fat.
Gradually add 1 cup of solution.
Cover and simmer until tender.
Thicken remaining liquid for gravy.

title: smoked sausage and bean soup
directions: In large pot, cook the onion and garlic in margarine until tender.
Add the water, potatoes, sausage, beans and bouillon. Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer, covered, for 15 minutes. Add cole slaw, catsup and vinegar.
Simmer 10 more minutes.
Quick and delicious.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Combine the egg, bread crumbs, meat and spices.
Split meat mixture in half.
Spread evenly in the bottom of a standard bread pan.
Layer mushrooms, onion, green peppers and cheese in the bread pan.
Add the remaining meat and tomato topping.
Bake in a 350° oven for one hour.
Voila!

title: sugared pecans
directions: Boil water and sugar until it becomes a syrup and can spin a thread.
Cook a few minutes longer or until mixture will form a soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat; add grated rind and stir until candy coats the nuts.
Pour onto a marble surface or onto wax paper.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Cut chicken, green peppers and onion into strips.
In 1 tablespoon oil, saute green peppers and onion until soft.
Remove from pan.
Saute chicken until cooked.
Cover with fajita mix that has been dissolved in 1/4 cup water.
Replace green peppers and onion and stir.
Add can of tomatoes.
Serve with warm tortillas and cheese.

title: ham strata(brunch do-ahead)
directions: Overlap bread in rows in the bottom of a 3-quart oblong baking dish.
Sprinkle with ham, cheese, peppers and scallions.
Beat eggs in a large bowl.
Beat in milk, mustard, pepper and paprika.
Pour egg mixture over ingredients in baking dish.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour or overnight.
Heat oven to 350°.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until knife in the center comes out clean.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: easy banana bread
directions: Mix all together and bake in an oiled loaf pan at 350° until done (about 35 minutes).

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Mix and warm.
Serve with Doritos for dipping.

title: hawaiian haystacks
directions: Combine broth and cornstarch.
Cook until thick and clear. Add chicken.
Place remaining ingredients in individual bowls. Have guests build their own stack in the following order:
rice, chicken in gravy, tomatoes, peas, celery, green pepper, onions, pineapple, almonds, coconut, raisins, water chestnuts, noodles and cheese.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix together and store in refrigerator.
Keeps for several days.

title: easy garden vegetable pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease pie plate (10-inch).
Cook broccoli or cauliflower until almost tender.
Drain thoroughly. Mix with onion, green pepper and cheese in pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean, 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: spice bread-in-a-jar
directions: You will need 7 pint wide mouth canning jars.

title: lemon cake pie
directions: Mix egg yolks with other ingredients.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in mixture.
Put into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until firm.

title: canton chicken
directions: Place chicken in 12 x 8 inch baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over chicken.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, turning occasionally.
Serve with fluffy rice and tossed greens.
Very simple.
Tastes great!

title: cheesy baked cod or orange roughy
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Rinse and dry fish well.
Salt and pepper.
Layer fish in baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread on fish.
Bake at 400° until slightly browned and fish is flaky.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Take dough out of refrigerator and roll out on a floured pastry cloth or board.
Roll dough to about 1/4-inch.
Spread one stick of butter on the rolled out dough, then sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up the dough, then slice and put in a greased pan.
Let the dough rise until doubled. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Let rolls cool slightly, then glaze with 1/2 cup orange juice and confectioners sugar to make glaze of the right consistency.
Glaze while warm, if desired.

title: grits casserole
directions: Take your sausage, green bell peppers and onions and brown them off.
Then you boil grits, and after you do your sausage, you drain the grease and add the grits to it.
Mix it together and then you add cream of chicken soup and shred a lot of cheese where it can cover the whole dish.
Then you bake it at 350° for 45 minutes. This dish is under $5.00.
It is used only in a casserole dish.
It is enough for your family.

title: meat loaf supreme
directions: Mix all together.
Add dry stuffing mix and form into loaf. Bake large loaf 1 hour and 15 minutes in 375° oven.
You can make 3 small loaves and bake them 1 hour.

title: french-style green beans
directions: Cook the almonds in the butter over low heat until golden brown. Remove form heat. Add salt and juice. Pour over beans. Serve hot.

title: rio grande meat loaf
directions: Drain and mash the kidney beans.
Combine all ingredients thoroughly.
Line a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan with foil and pack beef mixture into foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: stir-fried beef broccoli
directions: Cook beef in oil; add remaining ingredients and cook about 2 to 3 minutes over high heat, stirring constantly, just until broccoli is tender.

title: golden medley punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in large container.
Cover.
Store in refrigerator for 24 hours before serving.
Serves 40 (5 ounce) cups.

title: mom's carrot cake
directions: Beat oil, brown and white sugar, salt and eggs.
Add and mix in gradually the flour, baking powder, baking soda and 2 teaspoons of cinnamon.
Blend in carrots, pineapple and walnuts.
Mix and pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; drain blueberries and pineapple, reserving juice.
Measure juice, add enough water to make 1 cup, add to jello.
Stir in the blueberries and pineapple. Pour into 2-quart flat pan and refrigerate until set.
Combine sugar, sour cream, cream cheese and vanilla.
Spread over jello layer and sprinkle pecans over the top.

title: creamy baked cheesecake
directions: Combine margarine, crumbs and sugar.
Press firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: jello salad
directions: Make jello with crushed pineapple and let set until firm.

title: cheese cake bars
directions: Combine cake mix, egg and butter.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Beat cream cheese, powdered sugar and eggs until fairly smooth.
Pour evenly over crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: cherry salad
directions: Combine cherries, 1/2 cup water and sugar in saucepan; boil 5 minutes.
Mix jello with 2 cups boiling water; add Coke.
Cool until mixture begins to thicken slightly.
Add cherry mixture, nuts and pineapple.
Refrigerate.
Yields 12 servings.

title: sour cream candy
directions: Combine the sugar and sour cream and cook to 240° (soft ball stage).
Remove from heat.
Add a tiny pinch of salt and the butter.
Beat with electric mixer until mixture begins to grain. Stir in vanilla and walnuts and pour into a buttered pan and mark in squares.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer first 6 ingredients exactly as listed.
Frost with mixture of Hidden Valley dressing, sour cream and mayonnaise.
Make 24 hours ahead.
Toss before serving.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Cook peppers and onions until tender.
Mix all ingredients and cook at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: amazin raisin cake
directions: Mix first 11 ingredients for 2 minutes. Add apples, raisins and walnuts.
Bake for 45 minutes or until done.
Bake at 350°.

title: french raisin pie
directions: Cream
butter,	salt
and sugar.
Beat constantly.
Add eggs 1 at
a time, and beat just enough to mix or blend.	Add raisins and nuts.
Stir in spices.	(I mix the three together so they will be well blended.) Add vinegar.
Pour into unbaked pie shell (9-inch).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: japanese fruit pie(heritage recipe)
directions: Combine sugar, butter, salt, eggs, vinegar, coconut, pecans, and raisins until smooth.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake in preheated 325 degree oven for 40 - 45 minutes until set in center. Cook at least one hour before cutting.
Makes 1 pie.

title: buckeyes
directions: Cream margarine, peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Make into small round balls and set aside.

title: oven roasted vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a plastic bag, shake or toss all ingredients until vegetables are well coated.
Empty into 13 x 9-inch baking or roasting pan.
Bake, stirring once, for 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
(Choose from sliced zucchini, yellow squash, red or green peppers, carrots, celery and mushrooms.)
Serves 6.

title: marble souffle
directions: Melt shortening in top of double boiler.
Add sugar and flour; mix thoroughly.
Gradually add hot milk; cook over hot water, stirring constantly until thick.
Add a little hot mixture to egg yolks, mixing well, and put back into boiler.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla and salt.
Cool slightly, then add beaten egg whites. Divide mixture in half; add melted chocolate to one half.
Put vanilla half in casserole dish.
Drop the chocolate half by spoonfuls onto vanilla side.
Cut with knife to create marble effect.
Put dish into a pan of hot water.
Bake for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
(I usually double recipe.)

title: blueberry cream pies
directions: Prepare 2 baked pie shells. Slice 1 large banana in each. Prepare Dream Whip according to package directions.
Mix in 1 cup sugar and cream cheese.
Cool and pour over bananas.
Spread pie filling over cream.

title: beverly turner's famous taco casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Mix soups, milk and tomatoes in micro-safe dish and heat until hot.
Spray casserole dish with Pam and layer with half Doritos; layer half of meat, onions and cheese.
Pour 1/2 soup mixture over and repeat layers.
Pour rest of soup mixture over top.
Bake at 350° until hot and cheese is melted.

title: pagach
directions: This pagach dough recipe will make two pagach using a 15 x 10-inch cookie sheet.
Simply double the amounts of the ingredients for four pagach, etc.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix with hands the flour, powdered sugar and margarine; pat gently into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix together sugar, flour, lemon juice and eggs (beaten).
Pour over pastry and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Shake powdered sugar lightly over top and cut into squares while still warm.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix pie filling and cinnamon; set aside.
Beat flour, sugar, milk, 1/2 cup softened margarine, baking powder and eggs in large bowl on low speed, 30 seconds, scraping bowl.
Beat at medium speed 2 minutes.

title: three bean casserole
directions: This casserole requires only 15 minutes preparation time.
A great dish for those busy Moms and Dads.

title: heaven delight lemon pie
directions: Put in double boiler the egg yolks, 1/2 cup sugar and lemon juice.
Cook until thick; set aside and cool.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 1/4 cup sugar, beat well.
Add half egg white mixture to first mixture; mix well.
Pour into baked pie shell. Top with remainder of egg white mixture; put in oven and brown as desired.

title: spicy cocktail hot dogs
directions: Combine all ingredients except hot dogs and bring to simmer. Add cut hot dogs and bring to boil.
Turn on low and simmer for 45 minutes.
Can be put in crock-pot on low heat for serving.

title: beef pot roast in a skillet
directions: Salt, pepper and meat tenderize the roast.
Cut slices in roast and put garlic in the holes.
Roll in flour.
Brown in oil at high heat.
When brown, pour excess oil off.
Add enough water to cover.
Turn heat to low and simmer for 3 1/2 or 4 hours.
Add onions and potatoes.
Cook until done.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add Eagle Brand milk and vanilla; mix well.
Combine 1-quart finely chopped pecans, 1/2 pound candied cherries (chopped).
Set in refrigerator until firm. Make into balls.
Leave in refrigerator overnight.
Dip in 1 package melted chocolate chips and 3/4 block of paraffin.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix flour,
baking
powder
and salt.
In a large bowl, beat butter
and
granulated
sugar with a mixer until fluffy. Beat in eggs
until
mixture
is
pale
yellow,
then beat in vanilla
and melted
chocolate
until blended.
Gradually add flour mixture, mixing just to blend.
Refrigerate dough about 1 hour.
Heat
oven to
Lightly
grease cookie sheets. Shape heaping teaspoons of dough into 1 1/4-inch balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Place
inches
apart
on prepared cookie sheets. Bake
about
minutes until tops are puffed and cracked.
(Do not overbake.
Cookies are soft when hot but firm and chewy when cool.) Cool.
Store tightly covered for up to 3 weeks
with waxed paper between layers.
If you like, dip tops in powdered sugar before serving.
Makes 52.
Per cookie: 80 cal, 1 g
pro,
g car, 17 mg chol with butter and 49 mg sod.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Place sliced cucumbers and onions in a large bowl.
Heat vinegar, sugar and spices to boiling.
Lower heat and let simmer 5 minutes.
Pour liquid mixture over cucumbers and onions.
Let cool.

title: custard pie
directions: Scald milk and mix the slightly beaten eggs, sugar, nutmeg, vanilla and salt.
Stir the milk gradually into egg mixture.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake until knife blade comes out clean, about 25 minutes.
Use unbaked pie crust.

title: caramel dumplings
directions: Brown 1/2 cup sugar until melted in iron skillet.
Then add 1 cup sugar, 2 cups warm water, salt, butter and vanilla.

title: marinara sauce
directions: In a large saucepan, saute bell pepper, onion, zucchini, mushrooms, carrots, garlic and herbs in oil until onion is translucent.
Add the tomato products, breaking up the whole tomatoes.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Use in any recipe calling for spaghetti sauce.

title: carrot-pineapple loaves
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 4 small loaf pans or 2 large pans.
In a large bowl, stir together flour, baking soda, salt, ginger and baking powder.
In large mixer bowl at medium speed, beat eggs and oil until well blended.
Add sugar and continue beating until mixture is thick.
On low speed beat in carrots and pineapple.
Add flour mixture and stir until moistened.
Stir in nuts.
Bake 50 minutes until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: bean casserole
directions: Drain liquid from all beans.
Mix with bacon.
Bake at 325°F for 1 1/2 hours.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender and drain.
Mix ingredients together and cook in 350° oven for about 45 minutes.
When done, sprinkle crushed potato chips on top and return to oven until chips are slightly brown.

title: rolls
directions: In large bowl, combine Crisco, salt, sugar and 1 cup boiling water; mix by hand.
In small bowl, mix yeast with 1 cup warm water; stir until dissolved.
Mix both ingredients in large bowl. Mix flour with soda.
Mix all together.
Let stand for 2 hours in warm place.
When it rises, punch down.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Roll small amount and cut.
Put butter on each roll; let rise in warm place for 3 hours.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 25 minutes or until brown.

title: cocktail salmon log
directions: Blend all ingredients except nuts, parsley and bread or crackers.
Shape into log.
Mix nuts and parsley together; sprinkle onto board.
Roll log in mixture to cover.
Chill well. Serve with cocktail bread or crackers.

title: potato biscuits
directions: Mash potatoes; set aside.
In large bowl, stir together the flour, baking powder and salt.
With pastry cutter, cut in margarine.
Stir in potatoes, then milk, blending lightly with fork.
Spoon into 24 mounds on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: blueberry icebox pie
directions: Place milk in mixing bowl.
Add lemon juice.
Beat until fluffy.
Stir in well drained berries.
Pour into crust and cover with whipped topping of your choice.
Chill.

title: taco stew
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and chilies in a large Dutch oven on medium-high heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer on low heat for 30 minutes.
Makes 10 servings.

title: easy beef stew with rice
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Add meat and onion; cook and stir until meat is browned.
Sift flour, salt and pepper.
Stir in tomatoes, mushrooms, broth, carrots and garlic powder.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 10 minutes. Meanwhile, prepare rice as directed on package.
Serve stew over rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: potato dumplings
directions: Boil potatoes and mash in large bowl.
Add flour, salt, pepper, nutmeg, bread crumbs and eggs.
Cube white bread and saute in butter.
Put 2 to 3 cubes in center of each potato dumpling and round them (flour hands to form dumplings).
Drop dumplings into salted, boiling water.
Boil gently 5 minutes.
When they rise to top, they are finished.
If potatoes are too moist, add a little flour when forming balls.

title: salmon steaks(microwave)
directions: In a shallow bowl, combine egg, milk, lemon juice and salt; beat well. Dip each steak in mixture and then in cornflake crumbs. Put butter in a microwave-safe dish; cook on power 9 for 1 1/2 minutes, until butter is melted. Arrange steaks in the dish; cover with plastic wrap. Cook on power 9 for 5 to 7 minutes, until fish flakes easily with a fork. Let stand for a few minutes; internal heat will complete cooking. You don't want to overcook or the meat will be tough.

title: calico quiche
directions: Beat eggs with half and half.
Stir in corn, asparagus, 1 cup cheese, ham and onion.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour filling into pie shell.
Sprinkle remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together until smooth and shape into a ball. Roll ball in parsley, paprika and pecans. Refrigerate overnight to set.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Put wings in shallow baking pan.
Combine ingredients and heat until sugar and butter dissolve.
Cool and pour over wings. Marinate 2 hours.
Place in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Turn and bake another 45 minutes.

title: pear relish(very good)
directions: Remove seed from all fresh peppers.
Mix all ingredients and stir well.
Bring to a rolling boil over medium-high heat.
Cook 25 minutes.
Have hot sterilized jars ready.
Pack relish in hot jars and seal.
Process 5 minutes.
Makes 7 pints.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Slowly melt butter and chocolate. Remove from heat and pouring half the milk and half the sugar, mix well. Repeat with remaining milk and the sugar. mix well. return to heat and simmer until thick. Remove from heat. Cool slightly.
Add vanilla. Store in refrigerater.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Mix together and form into 24 balls.
Press into small muffin tins.
If dough is too soft, chill it.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Cut meat in 1-inch cubes.
Roll in flour and brown in butter. Stir in any remaining flour and cook 1 minute.
Add garlic, parsley, carrots, consomme and first cup of wine.
Cover and simmer 1 to 2 hours until meat is tender.

title: mr. mom's roast
directions: Make sure your roast is taken out of the freezer and thawed before you do anything else.
Season your roast with whatever you want.
Chop the onion and throw it in the crock pot.
Turn the crock pot on low.
If you use a beef roast use a little water at the bottom.
Pork does not need any water.
Cook your roast on low over night while you sleep or put it on first thing in the morning before you leave for work. I promise the house won't burn down, mine never did.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix together in pan Jell-O, sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in boiling water and bring to a boil.
Cook until thick.
Cool.
Add food coloring.
Fold berries into cooled sauce.
Pour into baked pastry shell.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.
Garnish with favorite cream.

title: basic pudding mix
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and store in covered container. Prepare as directed in individual recipe.

title: fudge puddles
directions: Cream butter, sugar and peanut butter together.
Add egg and vanilla.
Mix flour, soda and salt and add to mixture.
Mix all well and chill for one hour.
Shape into 48 balls, 1-inch each. Place in lightly greased mini muffin tins.
Bake at 325° for 14 to 16 minutes.
Remove from oven and immediately make "wells" in center of each with a melon baller.
Cool in pans 5 minutes. Remove to wire rack and fill.

title: steve's chili concoction
directions: In margarine, braise meat, onion, green pepper and garlic. "Heap everything into a large pot over an open fire in the middle of the piney wood; heat to a boil and then simmer until Wishbone rings the dinner chime."

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Grease souffle dish with 2 tablespoons of drippings.
Heat dish, while preparing batter, at 450°.
Beat eggs well.
Add milk, flour and salt.
Beat 30 seconds.
Add 1 tablespoon beef drippings.
Pour into dish.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 450°.
Do not open oven door while baking.
Serve with roast and gravy.

title: arkansas cheese dip
directions: Make sure Ro-Tel is diced.
For thicker consistency, drain about 1/3 of liquid.

title: peach schnapps cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool.
Sprinkle with 10x sugar.

title: rise-n-shine muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix eggs, oil and vanilla.
Add flour, baking soda and cinnamon, mix well.
Add the rest of ingredients, mixing well.
Bake in muffin cups for approximately 20 minutes.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook the mixed vegetables according to directions.
Drain and cool.
Mix vegetables with onion, celery, mayonnaise and 1/2 of the cheese.
Pour into a greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Top with cracker crumbs and remaining cheese; add melted margarine and return to oven for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix together sugar, vinegar, salt and celery seed.
Add cucumbers, onion and green pepper.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Pour pickles and juice into some type of freezer container and freeze.

title: oven caramel popcorn
directions: Bring sugar, margarine and Karo up to a boil; stir until it boils.
Cook 6 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in the salt, soda and cream of tartar.
Mix well.
Pour over the 6 quarts of hot popped corn and stir until all kernels are coated.
Grease 2 large cookie sheets; spread corn onto these and bake in a 200° oven for one hour.
When cool, place in airtight container.

title: bacon quiche biscuit cup
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 10 muffin cups.
In a small bowl, beat cream cheese, milk and eggs on low speed until smooth.
Stir in Swiss cheese and onions.
Set aside.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits.
Place in greased muffin cups.
Firmly press into bottom. Place half of the bacon into muffin cups.
Spoon about 2 tablespoons of egg mixture over bacon in cups.
Bake at 375° for 21 to 26 minutes.

title: pepperoni cups(yield:  24 cups)
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 375°.

title: ham and potatoes
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix together onion, soup, sour cream and pepper.
Layer mix with potatoes and ham.
Sprinkle shredded Cheddar on top.
Cover with foil; bake for 2 hours at 325°.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain, rinsing with cool water. Drain tuna. Layer noodles and drain. Top with mushroom soup, then top with buttered cracker crumbs. Bake until top turns brown.

title: vermont stuffed pork chops
directions: Place pork chops, trimmed not too closely and seasoned, in ovenware container.
Grind saltines and onion and cut and seed green pepper.
Add milk to ground mixture or until mixture just sticks together.
Spread on top of each pork chop and bake in a 350° oven about 1 hour or until chops are tender.
Time depends on thickness of chops.

title: holiday punch
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in punch bowl.
Slowly add 7-Up. Add ice (frozen rings of red with cherries frozen into it).

title: eva cranford's chuck wagon stew
directions: Combine flour and sugar and coat beef.
Brown beef in hot oil. Mix together salt, pepper, chili pepper, thyme, bay leaf, tomatoes and beef broth and cover meat.
Cover and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours until meat is almost tender.

title: orange fruit salad
