directions: Mix together in large bowl.
Amounts of cottage cheese, fruit cocktail and Cool Whip may be adjusted.
May use large or small containers of these.

title: sugar-free refrigeration cookies
directions: Cream together butter, egg and vanilla until mixed and fluffy. Beat in dry ingredients.
Mix well after each addition.
Mix in dates, coconut and 1/2 cup nuts.
Form dough into 2 (1 1/2-inch) logs.
Roll logs in remaining nuts (1/4 cup each).
Wrap in waxed paper and chill or freeze until firm enough to slice.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Slice cookies and bake 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown.

title: yeast breads
directions: Mix water, yeast and sugar together and let sit in mixing bowl.
Add top mixture and beat.
Stir in rest of flour.
Let rise in bowl until double.
Punch down; knead.
Make into loaves or rolls.
Let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 22 minutes.
It will be golden brown.
Remove from oven; brush with oleo.

title: cherry delite
directions: Mix flour, oleo and pecans well.
Press into a 9 x 13 baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.
Mix sugar and cream cheese; fold in Cool Whip.
Add to cooled crust.
Spread 1 can cherry pie filling on top.
Refrigerate.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Mash potatoes and combine with cream cheese, half and half, spices and butter, except 1 tablespoon. Put in greased casserole. Top with 1 tablespoon butter and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or if refrigerated for later, bake for 45 minutes. You can just warm up in microwave.

title: chicken parmesan with scallop tomatoes
directions: Cook pasta as package directs; drain. Dip chicken in milk; coat with crumbs. Cook chicken in hot oil in large skillet over medium heat 10 minutes or until no longer pink, turning once. Remove chicken; keep warm.

title: grapenut custard pudding
directions: Mix milk, tapioca, grapenuts, and salt together in a double boiler.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Add sugar, eggs, oleo and vanilla.

title: hot beef dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream together, then add remaining ingredients and salt and pepper to taste.
Heat in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Can be served hot or cold, but should be warmed first.

title: turtle candy
directions: Melt caramels and mix together.
Add nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Freeze 2 hours.
Dip in melted chocolate.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; then add cheese, undiluted soup, beef and eggs. Pour milk all over.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until crumbs are brown.

title: pig puken cake(pig eating)
directions: Mix all cake ingredients together and bake 20 minutes at 350°. Makes 3 layers.

title: potato dumplings
directions: Place potatoes in boiling salted water.
Boil until tender. Put potatoes through ricer.
Refrigerate.
Saute bread cubes in butter until golden.
Beat egg and flour with cold potatoes. Shape mixture in 8 to 10 balls, placing three cubes of bread in center of each ball.
Roll in cornstarch.
Carefully place 4 balls at a time in boiling water, simmering gently until light and fluffy.
Serve hot with sauerbraten.

title: calypso rum cake
directions: Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Cream the Crisco and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Add flavorings.
Add flour and buttermilk alternately.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: no fat traditional oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Blend oil, sugars and eggs.
Add vanilla.
Add sifted ingredients, then oatmeal, nuts and fruit of your choice.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto Pam sprayed cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 8 minutes.
Do not overbake, as they won't brown much when done.
(I add 2 tablespoons powdered milk to dry ingredients if I want them to brown a little.)
Cool on rack; store in tight container.

title: broccoli and bacon quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brush pie crust with some of the beaten eggs.
Prick with fork.
Bake 12 minutes.
Combine eggs and other ingredients.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is firm.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in small amount of water until tender. Add milk, beaten eggs, cheese, butter, salt and pimento.
Pour in greased baking dish and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes and ham
directions: Mix potatoes, ham, green beans, onions, salt, pepper and garlic in 9x13-inch pan.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown ground chuck and salt to taste while browning.
Mix ground chuck with all ingredients and bake 30 minutes, in 350° oven, in a large casserole dish.
Pour in large crock-pot and simmer until serving time.

title: mocha pound cake
directions: Sift together the cake flour, sugar, coffee, salt, cream of tartar and baking soda.
In a large bowl, combine the shortening with the flour mixture.
Add water and vanilla and mix until flour is dampened.
Beat vigorously for 2 minutes.
Add eggs and melted chocolate.
Beat 1 minute longer.
Pour into greased and lightly floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Can also be baked in a loaf pan for 65 to 70 minutes.
Cool in pan about 10 minutes.
Remove to wire rack and sift with confectioners sugar when completely cooled.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Combine Italian dressing mix and mayonnaise. Add chopped artichoke hearts. Chill and serve with crackers or chips.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil. Add eggs, one at a time.
Add carrots, then flour with soda and cinnamon. Bake in three 8 or 9-inch cake pans. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; chill and serve.

title: creole jambalaya
directions: Cook sausage in a large skillet about 5 minutes.
Drain off all but 2 tablespoons pan drippings.
Add green peppers, onions and garlic; cook until tender.
Blend in flour; brown slowly, stirring often.
Stir in tomatoes, water and parsley.
Bring to a boil.
Add remaining ingredients except shrimp.
Return to a boil, cover, reduce the heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook 10 minutes longer.
Fluff lightly with a fork.
Makes 8 servings.

title: brazilian black beans
directions: Wash beans and pick over.
Cover with water; soak overnight. Slice meats; add to beans with rest of ingredients.
Add more water if not completely covered.
Bring to boil.
Lower heat and simmer, covered, for 2 1/2 hours, or until beans are te nder.
Remove 1 cup of the beans and puree in blender or food processor.
Return to pot.
Add water if beans are too thick or dry.
Bring to simmer; cook for 5 minutes.
Serve with rice; garnish with orange slices.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar and beaten egg.
Combine yeast and warm water.
Add margarine and sugar mixture.
Add flour.
Mix well.
Place in airtight container.
No need to let rise.
Bake in muffin tin 20 minutes at 375°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, syrup, vanilla and butter.
Spread pecans in bottom of pie shell.
Pour in filling.
Bake at 400° until set.

title: southern corn sticks
directions: Combine first five ingredients in a medium bowl.
Stir well and set aside.
Combine next three ingredients and add to dry ingredients, stirring just until smooth.

title: blueberry sauce
directions: Drain blueberries, reserving juice.
Combine juice, water, cornstarch and sugar in a medium saucepan.
Cook about 5 minutes over low heat, stirring occasionally until thick and bubbly.
Add blueberries, cover and cook 5 minutes.
Stir in lemon juice.
Serve over pancakes, waffles or French toast.
Yields 2 1/2 cups.

title: beef stew
directions: Brown meat in small amount of oil in Dutch oven. Add onion, tomatoes, tomato sauce and water.
Simmer until meat is almost done, at least 1 hour.
Add carrots and simmer 30 minutes.
In a cup, mix together ketchup, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and a little stew broth and mix well.
Add this to stew; mix well.
Add potatoes.
Simmer until potatoes are done and to desired juiciness.

title: lime party salad
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk over very low flame or double boiler.
Pour hot mix over jello and softened cream cheese until dissolved.
Add undrained pineapple.
Let cool.
Blend in whipped cream and mayonnaise.
Refrigerate.

title: finish line chess pie
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, combine sugar, butter, cornmeal, white vinegar and vanilla.
Add eggs and mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool completely before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: barbecued green beans
directions: Brown bacon and onion. Drain excess grease and add catsup, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer for 2 minutes.
Add beans and continue to simmer until beans are heated thoroughly.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Blend in vanilla.
Stir together with flour and salt and stir into creamed mixture. Alternate with milk and stir in pecans.

title: jimmy carter pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and sugar; beat well.
Add peanut butter and milk; beat well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients, beat well and pour into a greased pan.
Bake in 450° oven until brown, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: souther pie
directions: Combine cereal and water; let stand until water is absorbed. Meanwhile, blend eggs with sugar; add syrup, butter, vanilla and salt.
Fold in softened cereal.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, or until filling is puffed completely across the top.
Cool.
Garnish with whipped topping.
Sprinkle with additional cereal, if desired.

title: rock cakes(great britain)
directions: Cream fat and sugar; beat in the eggs.
Sieve the flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix in coconut, raisins and fruit.
Mix with milk to dropping texture.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie tray.
Cook in a moderate oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix shrimp, crab meat, cream cheese and sour cream together. Add garlic powder and seasoning to taste.
Seasoning is hot, so be careful about how much you add.
Serve with crackers.

title: tapioca dessert
directions: Boil water.
Add tapioca and salt. Cook for 20 minutes.
Add sugar and jello.
Cool overnight.
Add pineapple, container of Cool Whip, bananas and strawberries.

title: fruit slush
directions: Let the fruit thaw partially.
Put in food processor or blender; blend until slush mixture.
Serve in a bowl or on an ice cream cone for a healthy kid's snack.
This can be refrozen. Partially thaw in microwave to serve.
Works great for popsicles.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, vanilla and oil.
Sift in all dry ingredients.
Will be thick.
Stir in zucchini.
(Drained pineapple and nuts can be added.)
Pour into 3 one-pound coffee cans or large fluted pan.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: no cook peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil powdered sugar and milk for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat. Immediately stir in, very briskly, the marshmallow and peanut butter.
Pour into buttered 9-inch square dish immediately.
Cut into serving pieces when cool.

title: quick cheese-garlic biscuits
directions: Mix the baking mix, milk and cheese until a soft dough forms; beat for 30 seconds.
Drop dough by spoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake about 10 minutes until lightly brown.
Mix butter, garlic powder and parsley.
Brush over warm biscuits before removing from cookie sheet.
Makes 12 biscuits.

title: taco dip
directions: Blend cream cheese, sour cream and 1/3 package taco mix; mix well.
Spread on a dinner plate and layer lettuce, taco mix, tomato, taco mix, Cheddar cheese and taco mix.
Serve with Doritos.

title: avocado and tomato salad
directions: Mix lemon juice (or vinegar), olive oil, salt and garlic and let sit out for about 2 hours.
Cube avocados, tomatoes and onions.
Add the dressing that you have prepared.

title: potatoes
directions: Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: dump cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan, spread pineapple evenly. Spread cherry pie filling evenly, then spread dry cake mix evenly. After this cut oleo into parts and lay on top of dry cake mix. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until brown.

title: gammy's italian cookies, biscotti
directions: Cream the Crisco or the lard (whichever one you are using), sugar and the butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, flour, baking powder, baking soda, vanilla and salt.
Dough will be sticky. Wrap in plastic and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: apple noodles(can be used as a vegetarian dish)
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salted water following package directions; drain.
Melt butter in large skillet.
Add half the noodles, then the apples.
Sprinkle with sugar, salt and cinnamon. Cover with remaining noodles.
Cover and cook for 10 minutes. Remove cover and cook until apples are tender and noodles browned.

title: mama's potatoes and chops
directions: To make sauce, melt butter, then stir in flour until blended. Add milk and salt; cook over low heat until smooth.
Grease baking dish.
Add layers of potatoes and sauce.
Arrange pork chops on top.
(If potatoes are not covered, a little milk may be added.)
Do not cover chops with sauce.
Bake about 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: brown butter glaze
directions: Heat butter in saucepan over medium heat until delicate brown. Remove from heat.
Mix in powdered sugar, stir in hot water 1 tablespoon at a time, until of desired consistency.

title: jan's kahlua(makes two 1-quart bottles)
directions: Simmer water and sugar 10 minutes to dissolve.
Add coffee and cool.
Add vodka.
Place 1/2 vanilla bean in each of 2 (1 quart) bottles.
Pour mix in bottles.
Store in a dry place, shaking once a week, until done, 4 to 5 weeks.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with skin on.
Drain and put in refrigerator to cool (better if they set overnight).
Peel potatoes and cut into 1-inch chunks.
Add the rest of ingredients and mix well.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: daddy's casserole
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Add onion and peppers.
Cook until tender.
Add beans to mix.
(My dad fixed this for us when we were growing up.)

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken removing skin and bones, then dice.
Mix chicken with soup and milk.
Put in casserole dish.
Use butter and broth to make Stove Top stuffing.
Put on top of chicken mixture.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° with foil covering.
Take off foil, then bake another 15 minutes.

title: sheet coconut cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on
box.
Bake
in
a
9 x 12-inch pan. When cake is
done	remove	from oven.
Punch holes over top of cake with a
fork.	Mix
condensed	milk
and
cream of coconut thoroughly and pour
over
cake
while still hot.
Let mixture soak into the cake.
When cake is cool, spread whipped topping over the top and sprinkle with coconut and nuts.

title: old fashioned tea cakes(cookies)
directions: Grease baking sheet lightly.
Preheat oven 10 minutes before baking; set to moderately hot (425°).
Measure sugar and shortening into mixing bowl and cream well.
Add egg and beat until smooth and fluffy.
Stir in nutmeg, vanilla and salt.
Stir soda in buttermilk and add flour and buttermilk alternately in 2 or 3 portions, beginning and ending with flour; stir gently until just smooth between additions.
Remove 1/3 of dough at a time to a floured pastry cloth and roll out about 1/8-inch thick.
Cut with 2 1/2-inch cutter and lift out with pancake turner onto baking sheet. Bake from 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 36 tea cakes.

title: tropical chicken
directions: Mix
all ingredients (except chicken and rice) in bowl. Put chicken
in roasting pan.
Pour mix over chicken.
Broil 7 to 10 minutes each side.	Serve over rice.

title: bing cherry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Add juice and sherry to gelatin mixture.
When gelatin has settled, add other ingredients and pour into mold that has been buttered.
Chill.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all together and roll into small balls. Bake at 350° until brown on edges.

title: passover brownies
directions: Grease 9 x 9-inch pan or mini cupcake tin (48 count).
Preheat oven to 350°.
In bowl, beat together butter and sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Sift together potato starch and meal in separate bowl.
Make a paste of cocoa and water.
Add to wet ingredients. Mix well.
Add sifted ingredients.
Mix gently.
Pour into pan. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or if cupcakes, 12 minutes.
Yields 16 squares or 48 mini cupcakes.

title: pear salad
directions: Measure 1 cup pear juice and bring to boil.
Dissolve jello in pear juice.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put all in blender and beat until smooth, pale green and creamy.
Chill.

title: parmesan noodles
directions: Combine soup, milk and cheese.
Heat in a large saucepan over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally. Toss hot noodles with butter and combine with soup mixture.
Sprinkle with additional cheese before serving.

title: mixon punch
directions: Just place the whole washed pumpkin in a pan with about 2 cups of water.
Bake in a 350° oven until tender.
This usually takes an hour to an hour and a half, depending on the size of the pumpkin. Once the pumpkin is tender, remove it from the oven and cut it in half.
Scoop out the seeds, then scoop out the pulp.

title: quick deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthways.
Remove yolks and mash.
Add sandwich spread, mustard and sugar; mix well.
Refill egg whites with mixture.
Garnish with paprika and serve.

title: quick coffee bars
directions: Cream the shortening and brown sugar together.
Add egg and coffee.
Stir.
Add flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Spread on greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cover with icing while still hot.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Combine all but Parmesan cheese in a baking pan.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: ham and potato scallop(microwave)
directions: Pour milk into 2 cup glass measure and cook on 70 for 2 minutes.
Set aside.
Place butter in 2 cup measure and cook on High for 1 minute.
Stir in flour and cook on High for 30 seconds. Stir hot milk, salt, pepper and soup into butter and set aside.

title: potato logs
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In large plastic bag, add all ingredients.
Close bag and shake until potatoes are evenly coated.
Place in shallow baking pan.
Bake for 40 minutes (or until tender and golden brown).
Stir occasionally.
Makes 8 servings.

title: baked leeks with bechamel sauce and chopped ham
directions: Discard any withered leaves from the leeks and chop off the green tops.
Cook in salted boiling water for about 10 minutes, until leeks are cooked al dente.
Prepare the bechamel (with nutmeg) and leave to cool.
Drain the leeks and saute for 5 minutes in a skillet with the butter, salt and pepper.
Transfer to an ovenproof dish.
Combine the egg yolk and 3/4 of the ham with the bechamel, mix well and pour over the leeks.
Sprinkle with the cheese and the remaining ham.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: corn relish
directions: Mix chopped vegetables together in a large saucepan. Add remaining ingredients. Bring to boiling, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes, uncovered.
Put into containers; seal.
Makes about 1 quart.

title: osgood pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour half into each of the pie shells.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix in large bowl the oil, baking powder, sugar, vanilla, eggs, flour, salt, baking soda, pecans, and apples.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°. To prepare icing, combine butter, milk, brown sugar and powdered sugar in a saucepan and cook for 1 minute. Pour over cake.

title: beef stew
directions: Place flour in a plastic bag.
Add meat cubes, shaking to coat.
In a large frying pan, brown meat in hot oil.
In a Dutch oven, put juice, onion, bouillon granules, garlic, basil and thyme.
Bring to a boil and add meat.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Add potatoes, carrots and celery.
Cover; simmer for another 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 8 main dish servings.

title: pimento and cheese casserole
directions: Boil spaghetti; drain.
In casserole dish add milk in bottom. Put a layer of spaghetti.
On top of spaghetti put cheese and pimentos (slice cheese and pimentos and put on evenly).
On top of that, put onions and tomato sauce.
Add more spaghetti and repeat. Put in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa.
Heat milk and eggs together, which have been well mixed.
When milk is almost ready to boil, add the dry ingredients and stir until thick as you want.
Remove from heat.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Let cool.
Put in baked pie crust.
Take egg whites and sugar; beat for top of pie.
Makes two pies.

title: baked salmon steaks(2 servings)
directions: Wash salmon steaks and pat dry.
Place in shallow baking dish just large enough to hold the steaks.
Sprinkle with salt, if desired.
Pour in half and half and enough milk to bring liquid halfway up salmon.
Sprinkle with fresh dill.

title: homemade rolls
directions: In a large mixing bowl, heat milk and margarine until warm (not hot); stir in sugar and add yeast (until dissolved), then add flour (the consistency of cake dough).
Set aside to rise for 1 to 2 hours in a warm place.
Then add 2 or more cups of flour as needed, until dough becomes tacky.
Add salt, soda and baking powder; mix.
Make into balls and dip into warm butter.
Put into muffin tins.
Let rise in a warm place for 2 hours and bake in a hot oven.

title: sweetened condensed milk(like eagle brand milk)
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and process until smooth. Makes same amount as a 14 oz. can of sweetened condensed milk. Refrigerate if not using right away.

title: dion's greek dressing(miscellaneous)
directions: Put everything except the olive oil into a blender.
Turn blender on medium speed.
Slowly add the oil until it is mixed completely.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in water.
Blend cheeses until creamy. Add mayo and stir until creamy.
Add beef bouillon and minced onions.
Stir until well blended.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Use with vegetables to taste.

title: pickled sweet and sour vegetables(will keep over a year, refrigerated.)
directions: Cut vegetables into bite size.
Bring water to a boil.
Add vegetables and immediately turn off heat.
Let vegetables stay in water for 2 minutes.
Drain and spread vegetables to dry.
When cool pack randomly in glass jar.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Layer: noodles, cheese, noodles and cheese in casserole dish.
Pour in milk and put butter on top. Crumble crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sauerkraut hot dish(slow crockery)
directions: Put sauerkraut and sausage in slow cooker for 3 hours.
Start on high.
Add after 3 hours the cream of mushroom soup.
Cook, drain and add to crock-pot the noodles.
Simmer one hour.

title: steak and onion roll-ups
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: dump cake
directions: Layer
pineapple and pie filling in cake pan.
Top with the cake
mix.
Nuts and coconut can also be put on top.
Pour the melted
butter
over top.
DON'T grease pan.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: bran flake cookies
directions: Stir together flour, soda and salt.
Set aside.
Beat margarine, shortening, granulated sugar and brown sugar until well blended.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Stir in Kellogg's Bran Flakes cereal and chocolate morsels.
Drop by level measuring-tablespoon onto greased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° about 11 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from baking sheets.
Yield:
about 5 dozen.

title: chili dog pie(kids' favorite)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Combine baking mix, mustard and water in small mixing bowl.
Stir until dough forms.
With fingertips dipped in baking mix, press dough into bottom and up sides of baking dish; set aside.

title: "my homemade kahlua"
directions: In large kettle combine and heat to a boil the water, sugar, coffee and vanilla bean.
Let cool.
Then add vodka.
Bottle it and store in a cool, dark place.
The longer it sets, the better it tastes!

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Put berries in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix 1 cup sugar, milk, oleo, 1 teaspoon salt, baking powder and flour.
Mix all real good.
Batter will be stiff.
Spread over berries.

title: tomato mac `n' cheese
directions: In large pot, melt butter over med-low heat, whisk in flour and cook 1 minute.
Reduce to low and cook, stirring 3 minutes or until pale gold.
Gradually whisk in milk, broth, mustard and Worcestershire sauce until smooth.
Increase heat to medium and bring to a simmer.
Stir in tomatoes, salt, and pepper and cook, stirring 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
In a large bowl, combine cheeses.
Stir 2 cups of the cheese mixture, green onion, and pasta into pot of sauce.
Pour into a 3 quart dish, sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Broil 8 - 10 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 10.

title: pheasant or chicken(this recipe is for the gravy lovers.)
directions: Pour over poultry.
Cover tightly with foil and bake in 300° oven for 4 hours.
Remove poultry to serving platter.
Sauce remaining makes great gravy for mashed potatoes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix Bisquick and water.
Add sausage and cheese.
Shape in small balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed by package and drain excess liquid. Combine all ingredients into large bowl and chill.
Makes 8 servings.

title: banana raisin cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and let stand to absorb moisture.
Drop by spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Loosen and let cool on sheet.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cheese stand
at
room temperature until soft.
Mix all ingredients
together
except
parsley
flakes and pecans. Roll in a ball, then roll in parsley flakes and pecans.
Chill before serving.

title: turkey club sandwich ring
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray fluted pan with Pam.
For bread: Remove dough from package; join ends together to form one large ring, pinching edges tightly to seal.
Place dough in prepared pan, seam side up, slightly pressing to fit pan.
Lightly spray top of dough with spray butter or margarine.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until deep golden brown.
Carefully invert pan onto cooling rack to remove bread.
Cool completely.
In small bowl, combine bacon, mayonnaise and chives; mix well.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix together and chill for 2 hours.

title: zucchini bars
directions: Cream margarine until fluffy.
Beat in sugars slowly.
Add eggs.
Beat in vanilla.
Stir in flour and baking powder.
Add zucchini, coconut and nuts.
Spread into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Place in baking dish.
Cook macaroni as directed on package; drain macaroni.
Add to sausage.
Add cheese from box.
Pour mushroom soup on top of sausage/macaroni mixture.
Mix butter and crushed cracker crumbs together.
Spread on top of mushroom soup.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake additional 15 minutes to brown.

title: corn-bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except crackers and butter, in a casserole dish.
Crumble crackers; put over mix.
Pour melted margarine over mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Cook broccoli according to direction, but cook 1/2 of required time.
Drain in colander, and drain further on paper towels and set aside.
Melt butter in heavy ovenproof skillet. Saute chopped onion and celery until golden brown.
Drain mushrooms and pat dry with towels and add to skillet and cook 3 or 4 minutes. Add soup.
Cut cheese into cubes, add to soup mix.
Add broccoli and mix lightly.
Cover skillet and place in 300° oven until cheese melts, about 25 minutes (don't overcook). Place in chafing dish. Serve with Fritos large corn chips.
Serves 50.

title: garden stir-fry salad
directions: Prepare linguine according to package directions; drain.
In large skillet, heat oil.
Add chicken; stir-fry until no longer pink.
Add vegetables; stir-fry just until tender-crisp.
Stir in parsley flakes, Italian seasoning, salt, garlic powder and pepper. Add to linguine; toss to mix.
Garnish as desired.
Serve immediately or cover and chill.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Melt butter; add sugar.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour over split crackers on cookie sheet with sides.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Immediately transfer crackers from cookie sheet to another sheet.
If you don't remove, they will become hard and stick to cookie sheet.
When cool, cover with melted chocolate.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil all ingredients to the soft boil stage; when dropped in cold water forms a soft ball.

Remove from heat and add 3 heaping tablespoonfuls of peanut butter and 2 teaspoons vanilla flavoring. Beat until flavoring and peanut butter are completely mixed in. Pour into a buttered pan and cut into squares.

title: spicy flowerets
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Combine nutmeg, sugar and cinnamon. Separate biscuits and cut into 5 petals. Dip in butter, then sugar mixture. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake for 12 to 14 minutes in 400° oven. Garnish with cherry halves.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients with a spoon.
Add a little milk if it's dry.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan (glass) and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: tripe italian style
directions: Boil tripe for 2 hours with 1 tablespoon of baking soda to soften.
Then rinse tripe with cold water.
Cut into 3 x 1/2-inch strips; set aside.

title: orange, date and pecan bread
directions: Wash and squeeze orange and add to the juice enough boiling water to yield 1 cup.
Remove pulp from orange and put peeling through food grinder.
Combine with dates, orange liquid, sugar, butter and egg.
Sift dry ingredients together 3 times and add; mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Turn into greased loaf pan and bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: tortilla rolls(appetizer)
directions: Mix sour cream and cream cheese together until smooth.
Stir in other ingredients.
Spread on flour tortillas.
Roll tortilla and refrigerate 2 hours.
Cut in slices and serve with picante sauce.

title: spinach stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and clean spinach.
Place in covered skillet and steam for 5 minutes.
Remove, thoroughly drain and chop.
Remove stems from mushroom caps and finely chop.
Saute chopped stems and spinach in 1 Tbsp. butter.
In a mixing bowl, combine the spinach mixture with the remaining ingredients.
Spoon the stuffing into the caps and refrigerate.
Before baking, place on cookie sheet and brush with remaining butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes or until heated through

title: pizza
directions: Spread over crust in order given and bake.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Blend all ingredients together and put in a casserole.
On top put 1 cup grated cheese.
Next add 1 roll Ritz crackers, crushed. Melt 1 stick oleo and pour on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes (until casserole bubbles).

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Cut hot potatoes in half.
Scoop out insides and reserve shells.
With electric mixer, beat potatoes and butter until creamy.
Gradually beat in milk; stir in onion, salt and pepper. Spoon mixture into reserved shells.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until heated thoroughly.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in pie shell for about 40 minutes.

title: sugar coated peanuts
directions: Dissolve sugar in water over medium heat. Add peanuts and continue to cook over medium heat, stirring frequently.

Cook until peanuts are completely sugared (coated and no syrup left). Pour onto ungreased cookie sheet, spreading so that peanuts are separated as much as possible. Bake at 300° for approximately 30 minutes, stirring at 5 minute intervals.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to
In medium mixing bowl, combine 3/4 cup sugar, flour, 3 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt. Blend in milk, margarine and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Pour batter into square pan, 8 x
8 x 2-inches or 9 x 9 x 2-inches.

title: chili con carne
directions: Prepare chili in microwave.
In a microwave-safe dish, cook meat, onions, peppers and garlic on High for 4 minutes.
Drain.

title: aunt flora lewis' angel biscuits
directions: Warm the milk and dissolve the yeast.
Mix other ingredients together.
Add milk.
Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter or glass.
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: stuffing casserole
directions: Saute onions, celery and mushrooms.
Break up bread.
Mix all ingredients together and place in casserole dish.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 45 minutes.
Remove cover and bake 15 minutes to brown.
Serve hot.
May also be chilled and cubed as an appetizer.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Prepare crust from the first 3 ingredients.
Blend and press into a pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and continue beating until fluffy.
Add flour, soda, salt, baking powder and vanilla. Mix until well blended.
Add rolled oats.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together, stirring well.
Store in airtight container until ready to use.
Mix 3 tablespoons of mixture with 1 cup of heated water.
Enjoy!

title: pea salad
directions: Heat green peas; don't boil.
Drain.
Layer first five ingredients as listed.
Beat dressings and spread on top of salad.

title: raw peanut cookies
directions: Combine sugars, margarine and eggs and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet; bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: beef stew
directions: Take stew meat; coat with flour.
Brown on stove until very dark, about 15 minutes.
Cover with water.
Simmer 45 minutes. Add potatoes.
Let cook for 20 more minutes.
Add frozen vegetables.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add bouillon.
Mix 2 tablespoons flour with 3/4 cup water.
Add until thick.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Crush wafers until fine and then add them to mixture.
Add milk, pecans and coconut.
Mix ingredients together well.
Bake in well-greased angel food pan at 350° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Let cool in pan.

title: lasagna
directions: Chop large onion and garlic; fry slightly in hot olive oil. Add tomatoes, tomato paste, bay leaves, salt, pepper and water; stir well.
Toss in ground beef in small pieces.
Cover and cook over low heat for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Finely chop small onion; cook in melted butter for about 2 minutes.
Mix in flour until smooth.
Add Parmesan cheese and salt.
Gradually stir in milk; continue cooking over low heat, stirring constantly, until sauce is consistency of heavy cream.
Beat egg yolks slightly.
Mix in a little hot cheese mixture slowly (to prevent egg from curdling), then mix all yolks into cheese mixture and cook over low heat for 10 minutes longer.
Remove from heat.

title: hot seafood mold
directions: Soften gelatin in water in bowl.
Bring picante salsa to a boil in saucepan.
Stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Beat in cream cheese.
Cool to room temperature.
Add onions, bell pepper, celery, crab, shrimp and Tabasco sauce.
Mix well.
Fold in mayonnaise.
Chill until partially set.
Spoon into greased mold. Chill overnight.
Unmold onto serving plate.
Serve with crackers.

title: orange julius
directions: Mix all together in food processor until ice is crushed.
This makes a good breakfast drink.

title: jogging in a jug
directions: *Use only apple cider vinegar.
No other kind works.

title: popcorn treat
directions: Boil
together the sugar and corn syrup just
until
it comes to a full boil.
Remove from heat; stir in	the
peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour this immediately over
the
popcorn and peanuts.
Pour at once into a greased pan or you can shape it into popcorn balls with well buttered hands.

title: chicken oriental with ramen noodles
directions: Brown chicken in 1 tablespoon oil and 1 tablespoon soy sauce. In saucepan, bring water to a boil.
Add Ramen noodles and seasoning packet.
Let stand 1 minute.
Combine vegetables and noodles with browned chicken.
Cook 5 minutes and serve immediately!

title: watergate salad
directions: Reserve liquid from fruit cocktail and pineapple.
In large plastic bowl, pour large and small pistachio pudding mixes.
Pour liquid from fruit, a little at a time, stirring until you have a soft paste.
Add drained fruits to paste and add Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Cover and let set overnight.
Serves about 10.

title: irresistible peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine peanut butter, Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat on medium speed on electric mixer until well blended.
Add egg; beat just until blended.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture at low speed.
Mix just until blended.
Drop by heaping teaspoons 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.

title: raspberry pretzel dessert
directions: Mix and spread pretzels, sugar and melted butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Cream together powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip and miniature marshmallows.
Place on cooled pretzel crust.
Let sit until firm.

title: polish sausages
directions: Place onion, bell pepper, hot pepper and margarine in pan and cook until tender.
Boil smoked sausage to get the salt out. Place smoked sausage in crock-pot.
Pour onion and pepper mixture over it.
Cover with tomato sauce and cook until done.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix
sweet
potatoes,
eggs, sugar, vanilla and butter. Place in
greased
pan,
then mix brown sugar, flour, nuts and butter. Pour this mixture over sweet potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread beans on bottom of pan after you have mixed with green chilies.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and taco seasoning mix and put on top of bean layer.
Next, spread on avocado dip.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese, black olives, chopped green onions and chopped tomato (respectively).

title: mother's pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream ingredients in order given.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes.
Yields 3 to 4 dozen.

title: carrot salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well. Refrigerate overnight. Serves 6.

title: apple-nut bread
directions: Gradually add sugar to eggs; beat until light and fluffy.
Add combined dry ingredients, alternately with oil and sour cream, beating well.
Stir in apples, pecans and vanilla.
Bake in 2 greased loaf pans 1 hour at 350°.

title: party fiesta(recipe for round platter)
directions: Layer ingredients on platter.
Serve with corn chips.

title: mock margaritas
directions: In blender, combine crushed ice, sparkling water, orange juice and limeade.
Process 2 minutes to mix well.
Coat rim of cocktail glasses with fresh cut lime and spin glass in salt.
To serve, pour mixture into prepared glasses.
Garnish with lime slices.

title: crispy onion biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Place biscuits in 8-inch round pan. Mix butter and dry soup.
Spread on each biscuit.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients (do not add water to soup), except potato chips.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Put in casserole dish; cover with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: hamburger biscuit bake
directions: Brown ground beef and chopped onion; salt lightly.
Remove from heat and add shredded cheese and parsley.
Stir in mayonnaise.
Add water to envelope of biscuit mix.
Knead lightly. Divide in half.
Roll out two 8-inch circles.
Place one in 8-inch casserole round dish and cover with beef and cheese mixture. Top with second circle of biscuit mix.
Bake at 375° for a half hour, or until browned and done.
Cut into wedges.
Serve with mushroom soup sauce.

title: spaghetti chili sauce
directions: Put the first 5 ingredients in a quart of water.
Cook slowly for 3 hours, then add the tomato sauce.
Pour over spaghetti.

title: cooked play dough
directions: Heat flour,
cream
of	tartar	and
salt in pan.
When warm, add oil and water.	Stir over low heat until ingredients form a ball.
Knead
with	hands.	Place in plastic container and add
a small
amount
of
food coloring.
Knead to spread color.
Great for when the small grandchildren visit.

title: peanut butter cream pie
directions: Place 3/4 cup confectioners sugar in a bowl. Cut in peanut butter until mixture resembles fine crumbs. Set aside 3 tablespoons for garnish. Sprinkle the remaining mixture into the pastry shell. Set aside.

title: yogurt cake
directions: Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan. Mix cake mix, eggs, oil, yogurt, lemon extract, grated lemon peel and cinnamon.
Blend until mixed; beat 2 minutes. Add nuts and mix until combined. Pour into pan. Bake at 350° for 60 minutes. Cool 10 minutes. Turn out on rack and continue to cool. Serves 16.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Cream together shortening, peanut butter, sugar and brown sugar in a large bowl.
Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Mix well. Sift together flour, soda and salt; add to mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape into balls and roll in sugar.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Heat together in saucepan on stove.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan and pour in hot (but not cooked) mixture.
Place skinless chicken breasts on top.
Put in blobs of butter.
Sprinkle with 1 package dry onion soup.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and bake 2 1/2 hours at 250°.

title: potato flake cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and salt in a saucepan.
Stir in hot water gradually and bring to a boil.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes on medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick and clear.
Beat egg yolks thoroughly and stir 5 to 6 tablespoons of cornstarch custard into the egg yolks; stir well and pour back into saucepan.
Cook at low temperature, about 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove from heat and add butter and lemon juice.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue.
Bake at 325° until golden brown.

title: chicken-vegetables stew
directions: In saucepan, boil fryer until about 1/3 tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook until all is tender. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: chicken delight
directions: Mix rice, milk and soups in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Lay pieces of chicken on mixture; sprinkle with onion soup mix. Prepare stuffing mix according to package directions (on top of stove).
Spread over top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, or until chicken is well done.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage; saute celery, green pepper and onion in grease.
Add soup, rice, milk and salt.
Bake in 1 1/2-quart casserole at 350° for 40 minutes (until rice is done).
Stir twice during baking.
Add topping of oleo and bread crumbs and continue baking until brown.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Put hash browns in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole dish.
Mix in bowl 1/2 cup butter, 1 cup sour cream, cream of chicken soup, onion and cheese.
Pour over potatoes.
Mix corn flakes and 1/2 cup butter together.
Place over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: orange ginger ale punch
directions: Place sherbet in large chunks in well chilled punch bowl.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well after each one.
Add vanilla, flour and cocoa; blend well.
Fold in nuts and coconut on low speed.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan (or larger).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Spread Marshmallow Creme over cake.
Return to oven if necessary to melt. Cool.
Spread on icing.

title: crazy cake
directions: Place flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and cocoa into an 8 x 8 baking pan.
Stir until completely mixed.
With a spoon, make 3 holes in dry mixture in your pan.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Turkey can be used instead of chicken.

title: killer brownies
directions: Mix brownie package as directed.
Add nuts.
Put in a greased (bottom only) 9 x 13-inch pan and bake as directed on package.

title: andrea's cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients (except nuts) and form a big ball.
Cover ball with nuts.

title: no bake butterscotch cookies
directions: Bring the sugar and syrup to a boil.
Add the butterscotch chips and peanut butter.
Stir until melted and add the corn flakes or Rice Krispies.
Drop on wax paper. Cool.

title: turkey and macaroni casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except paprika.
Mix well.
Spoon into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Chill, covered, overnight.
tags: cream of chicken and mushroom soup

title: hot chili cheese dip
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Melt other ingredients together.
Add to hamburger.
Serve hot with corn chips.

title: pastor goodwin's favorite chocolate pie
directions: Stir flour and cocoa in sugar.
Beat the egg yellows into the dry ingredients.
Add 1 1/2 cups milk and 1 teaspoon vanilla to the mixture.
Beat thoroughly.
Cook on stove, adding 1/2 stick margarine; continue to cook until thick.
Pour into cooked pie crust.

title: lomi salmon salad
directions: Soak salmon in cold water for 3 hours.
Remove skin and bones; shred finely.
Combine all ingredients but ice and chill.
Add ice just before serving in small bowls or hollowed tomatoes.

title: chicken rice dinner
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Shake flour in regular sized Reynolds cooking bag; place in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Add rice, margarine, peas, broth, water, onion, salt, pepper, poultry seasoning and garlic powder.
Squeeze bag gently to blend ingredients.
Arrange ingredients in an even layer.
Brush chicken pieces with oil.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt and paprika.
Place chicken in bag on top of rice; close bag with nylon tie.
Make 6 (1/2-inch) slits in top; cook 1 hour or until chicken is tender.

title: warsaw soup
directions: Cook meat in a large saucepan in 6 cups water about 2 hours. Add beets, celery and onion.
Cook another 30 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Blend sour cream, flour and egg.
Stir into soup.
Do not boil.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Dice onion.
Combine remaining ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Add diced onion and stir well. Ready to use for basting.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All, cream of chicken soup, onion and mayonnaise. Coat casserole dish with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown around edges.
Take out and add 1 package crushed Ritz crackers.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine and pour over crackers. Bake for 15 minutes.

title: brunch muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease or paper line 12 muffin cups. In a medium bowl, combine egg, milk and oil.
Stir in cereal.
Let stand 10 minutes.
In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and cinnamon. Add cereal mixture all at once to flour mixture, stirring just until moistened.
Divide evenly among muffin cups.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: double chip cookies
directions: Sift flour, measure and then add soda and salt.
Sift together 3 times.
Cream shortening and sugar together until fluffy.
Add vanilla and egg, beating well.
Gradually add flour mixture and mix thoroughly.
Add chips (chocolate and potato) and nuts, if using. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: everlasting cole slaw
directions: Cut cabbage, carrot, onion and celery up fine.
Set aside. Boil sugar, vinegar and spices.
Let cool.
Pour over cabbage, carrot, celery and onion.
Mix well.
Cover and store in icebox. Use as needed.
Will freeze well.

title: sauteed spinach(spinaci saltati)
directions: Wash
fresh
spinach
thoroughly.
Discard stems or any tough leaves.
Place
spinach
in saucepan with 1 teaspoon of salt
and a
few
tablespoons water; cook in covered pan over medium-low heat
for
10 minutes.
Drain well.
Heat oil in a large
skillet and
saute
garlic
until lightly golden.
Add spinach,
parsley, red pepper, salt and pepper.
Saute spinach over high heat for 4 to 5 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: kahlua
directions: Place vanilla bean in jar.
Boil water and then add sugar. Turn burner off and add other ingredients.
Cool for 1 hour and then cork.
Let settle for 30 days.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for about 8 minutes on ungreased baking sheet.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Mix
together
mushroom soup, onion, cheese, mayonnaise and well
beaten
egg.
Add broccoli and put mixture in casserole dish.

title: one dish chicken & rice bake
directions: Set oven to 375 degrees.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients, then add sugar, oil and eggs; mix well.
Blend in carrots, pineapple and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake approximately 50 minutes at 350°.
Let cool before frosting.

title: chicken breasts with tarragon
directions: Skin the chicken breasts.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Dredge with the flour.
Reserve remaining flour.

title: carrot salad or copper pennies
directions: Let cooked carrots cool.
Then mix all ingredients.
Store in refrigerator.
It will keep a long time.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs in a large bowl.
In a separate bowl add dry ingredients.
Mix together completely.
Add carrots and nuts. Mix.
Grease lightly a Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: taco bake
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef and onion over medium heat; drain.
Add water, taco seasoning and tomatoes.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
Stir in macaroni and 1 1/2 cups of cheese.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chicken and rice almondine
directions: Saute onion in butter until golden.
Add flour and blend. Add stock gradually, stirring until sauce thickens.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add cream and heat, but do not boil.
Add chicken, rice and remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a 2 quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until heated through.
Freezes well.
Serves 8.

title: french onion soup
directions: Slice onions as thin as possible.
Cook gently in melted butter until yellow.
Add water or stock and simmer 20 minutes. Season according to taste.
Place bread into individual soup crocks.
Sprinkle generously with cheese.
Pour soup over bread. Brown under broiler.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Mix and cook two minutes. Remove from heat and add 2 1/2 c. oats, 2 tsp. vanilla, 1/2 to 1 c. peanut butter; stir well. Drop onto wax paper by teaspoon.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini about 5 minutes.
Combine soup, sour cream, onions and carrots.
Fold in with drained zucchini.
Put in 1 large or 2 small casseroles.
Mix stuffing mix with margarine and spread over top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: "crock-pot baked chicken"
directions: Wash chicken thoroughly; rub down with olive oil, salt and pepper. If you like herbs, sprinkle some on here. Spritz the chicken with lemon juice (as much or as little as you like). Dump it in the crock-pot. Cook on low all day or on high 5 to 6 hours.

title: cherry blossom pudding
directions: Pour cherries and juice plus coloring in 9 x 9-inch baking pan. Mix remaining ingredients and press onto cherries.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in preheated oven.
Serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: crabmeat and rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients (except paprika and Parmesan cheese) together.
Put in a 2-quart casserole dish which has been sprayed with a nonstick coating spray.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry swirl coffee cake
directions: Blend sugar, oleo, shortening, extracts and eggs.
Beat on high for 3 minutes.
Stir in the flour, sifted with baking powder.
When well mixed, spread 2/3 batter in a greased 13 x 5-inch pan or a jelly roll pan.
Spread the cherry pie filling over this.
Drop the remaining dough by tablespoon onto the pie filling.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.
While cake is warm, make topping by mixing powdered sugar and milk.
Spread over top of cake.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O
in 1 cup hot water.
Add sugar (I only use 1/2
cup
sugar
if canned cranberries are used) and cranberries. Add nuts and pineapple.

title: western baked beans
directions: Brown beef, pepper and onions together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place in casserole and bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: baked chicken and broccoli
directions: Place chicken in a 9 x 9-inch pan and drizzle with butter. Bake 40 minutes at 375°.
Cook broccoli by package directions; drain.
Arrange around chicken.
Combine soup, milk and cheese and pour over chicken and broccoli.
Top with breadcrumbs and paprika. Bake an additional 20 minutes.
Serves 2.

title: vegie pizza
directions: Roll crescent rolls out flat on cookie sheet.
Bake until golden.
Mix together softened cream cheese, mayo, Ranch mix and finely chopped onion.
Spread this mixture onto the baked crescent on the cookie sheet.
Top with cheese, broccoli, cucumber, carrots and green peppers if desired.
Chill and slice into squares.

title: sky high strawberry pie
directions: In large bowl mash enough berries to make 3 cups.
In saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in mashed berries and water, mix well.
Bring to boil over medium heat.
Cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add coloring if desired. Pour into large bowl.
Chill for 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally until mixture is just slightly warm, then fold in remaining berries. Pile into pie shell.
Chill for 2 to 3 hours. In small bowl, whip cream until soft peaks.
Sprinkle pudding on cream and whip until stiff.
Put on pie.

title: spiced pickled peaches
directions: Tie spices in cheesecloth.
Add to boiling water and vinegar to the spice bag.
Add half of peaches.
Cook until tender 10 to 15 minutes.
Pack peaches in hot jars, leaving 1/4 inch head space.
Remove spice and heat syrup to boiling.
Pour over peaches in jars.
Seal.
Process 15 minutes in boiling water.

title: grilled vidalia onions
directions: Use charcoal grill or 350° oven. Trim and slice from the top of each onion and peel the onion without cutting off the root end. Using a potato peeler, cut a small cone shaped section from the center of the onion. Cut the onion into quarters from the top down, stopping within a 1/2-inch of the root end. Place a bouillon cube in the center of each onion. Put slivers of butter between the sections and sprinkle with pepper. Wrap each onion in heavy tinfoil and put onions directly on hot coals. Cook onions for 45 minutes, turning every so often. The onions will produce a broth which tastes like French onion soup.

title: by cracky bars
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Blend shortening and sugar; cream well.
Add eggs to creamed mixture.
Combine milk and vanilla and add alternately with dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Place 1/3 batter in 2nd bowl.
Add 1 ounce melted chocolate and 3/4 cup walnuts, chopped.
Spread in 2 greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch or one 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Arrange 9 double graham crackers over batter in pans.
Add chips to white dough.
Drop by spoonfuls over crackers to cover.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut when cool.

title: broccoli-cheese casserole
directions: Cut broccoli from stalk; cook until tender in a small amount of water.
Melt oleo; add crushed Ritz crackers.
Sprinkle half of cracker mixture over bottom of baking dish.
Layer cooked broccoli on top of crackers.
Completely cover broccoli with sliced Velveeta cheese.
Top this with remaining cracker crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 20 minutes, or until heated thoroughly.
Serve hot.

title: potato salad
directions: Leaving skins on, boil potatoes in large pan of water until soft.
Let potatoes cool, then peel.
In large mixing bowl, mix milk, mayonnaise, relish, mustard, onion, salt and pepper until smooth.
Add eggs to mayonnaise/milk mixture.
Take peeled potatoes and chop into 1 to 2-inch cubes; add to mayonnaise/milk/egg mixture.
Cool for 2 hours.
Keep refrigerated.

title: salmon cakes
directions: With a fork, flake the salmon into a mixing bowl and set aside. In a frying pan, heat 1 tbsp. butter, then add the onion, green pepper, and celery. Stir and cook until the onion is transparent and soft, let the mixture cool slightly. Then add it to the salmon in the bowl. Next, add bread crumbs, sage, parsley, eggs, salt and pepper. Shape the mixtures into 4 cakes, Place them on a plate, and cover with plastic wrap. Chill 30 minutes. Heat the remaining butter in a frying pan. Add the salmon cakes and cook
on both sides until golden brown and heated through. Serve with lemon wedges.

title: forgotten roast
directions: During the morning, preheat oven to 325°.
Rub mustard into the red exposed meat.
Place in oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Turn off oven; do not open door.
Half an hour before you are going to serve the roast, turn oven back on to 325°.
Your meat will be uniformly medium-rare from the fatty side right down to the bone. If you wish to have meat a little less rare, cook at 350° instead of 325°.

title: banana split supreme
directions: Combine butter and graham crumbs.
Pat in bottom of 13 x 9-inch dish.
Combine pineapple, sugar and flour.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Remove and cool completely.
Prepare pudding using directions on box.
Layer bananas on graham crust, then pudding, then pineapple mixture, coconut and pecans.
Cover top with softened Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut and pecans. Chill until ready to serve.
Contains 18 grams fat.

title: linguine with sweet pepper sauce
directions: Heat the oil in a large skillet.
Add the peppers, onions, shallots, garlic and basil or oregano.
Cook on medium-low until vegetables are soft and wilted, about 20 minutes.
Stir in the vinegar and honey.
Toss 1/4 of the pepper sauce with the linguine.
Divide the linguine between 4 plates.
Top each serving with the remaining sauce.
Serves 4.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix Philadelphia cream cheese and powdered sugar; place on bottom of cake pan.
Break into pieces the angel food cake.
Put over cream cheese and powdered sugar, then Cool Whip.
Next cherry pie filling.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix well the above ingredients and pour into a well greased pan and bake for 1 hour at 400° until done.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Boil 1 C. blueberries with 1 C. sugar, 1/2 cup water.
Blend together water, flour and salt to make a smooth paste. Add to the blueberries and stir until thick.
Remove from stove, cool, add 3 C. blueberries, put in baked pie shell.
Cover with Cool Whip. Chill and serve.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Add ingredients, except vanilla, in a glass bowl. Mix well. Cook on High in the microwave for 5 1/2 minutes, stirring occasionally. Cool and put on your favorite cake.

title: baked beef stew
directions: In a large bowl, combine tomatoes, water, tapioca, sugar, salt and pepper. Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Pour in greased 13 x 9 baking dish. Cover and bake at 375° for 1 3/4 to 2 hours or until tender.

title: baked potatoes
directions: Melt butter into baking dish.
Salt, pepper, and flour cut potato and place in pan.
Spread in melted butter and cover with lots of shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° uncovered until done.

title: free bean salad
directions: Mix together and chill before serving.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Spread half of the cookie crumbs on bottom of a 9x13 pan. Combine cream cheese, margarine, and sugar. Prepare instant pudding with milk and add cheese mixture. Stir in Cool Whip. Pour over crumbs in pan. Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top and refrigerate. * In our family, we often make this with lemon sandwich cookies and lemon pudding. The men like it better with lemon.

title: crab salad
directions: Cook, rinse and drain macaroni.
Combine all ingredients and serve.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar with mixer until smooth.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well.
Spread in pie crusts and chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: ham cheese ball
directions: Chop onions; shred meat and mix with other ingredients.
Roll into ball.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Melt Velveeta cheese over low heat.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.
Mix together with tomatoes and green chilies.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Grease and flour two 8 x 4-inch loaf pans.
Combine all dry ingredients; mix well.
Make a well in the center of mixture. Pour all liquid ingredients into it; mix by hand.
Pour mixture into pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until tester comes out clean.
Can be frozen.
Slice thinly before completely thawed. Spread with cream cheese to make sandwiches.
Refrigerate until served.

title: chocolate bread pudding
directions: Heat chocolate and milk until chocolate melts.
Add salt, beaten egg yolks and brown sugar.
Add chocolate mixture gradually, stirring well.
Add vanilla.
Pour over bread cubes.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Pour in baking dish.
Place in pan of hot water.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Beat egg whites.
Add sugar.
Beat until meringue stands in high peaks.
Place in spoonfuls around border of pudding.
Sprinkle with grated chocolate.
Bake at 375° until lightly browned.

title: delicious sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Add sour cream.
Mix in 1 cup flour mixture, which has been sifted with dry ingredients.
Fold in egg whites that have been stiffly beaten.
Add remaining flour and vanilla.
Bake for approximately 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: dressing supreme
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Use dressing for cold fish, salads, soups, etc.

title: nana's scotch shortbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Gradually add flour, then roll it into a log using wax paper.
Cut into small rounds and refrigerate about 1 hour.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until edges are brown.

title: long island cheesecake
directions: Mix together 1 egg and 1 package cream cheese.
Repeat with second egg and cream cheese, etc.
Mix thoroughly after each addition.
Add vanilla, lemon juice and sugar; beat well.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour into lightly greased 8-inch spring-form pan.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 30 minutes.
Turn off oven and leave cheesecake in oven until oven is cold (can be overnight if necessary).
Remove from pan onto a serving plate.

title: sock-it-to-me cake
directions: Mix cake mix and other ingredients, except the last two.
Pour half the batter into greased and floured pan (tube).
Sprinkle on brown sugar and cinnamon.
Pour in other half of batter.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: carolina chews
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, beating well.
Blend in flour, 1/2 cup at a time.
Stir in remaining ingredients except powdered sugar.

title: homemade biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 475°.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Cut in shortening until mixture looks like coarse meal. Stir in buttermilk with a fork until soft dough if formed.
Knead and roll out on lightly floured board. Cut to desired thickness. Bake about 10 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown onions in stick of oleo.
Remove onions and brown meat. Add to meat, flour and seasonings.
Dissolve bouillon cube in 3/4 cup hot water.
Add wine to this and then add to meat.
Cook on low heat for 2 hours or until tender.
Then put in onion and mushrooms for 1 hour.
Serve on rice or noodles.
Serves 8.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix until smooth the first 3 ingredients. Spread on a large plate or platter.
Layer on top the next 4 ingredients. Refrigerate until ready to serve, then add chopped tomatoes.
Pour on top 1/2 bottle of taco sauce.
Serve with corn or tortilla chips for dipping.

title: somertime chicken salad valencia
directions: Blend together orange juice, sugar, vinegar, mustard, salt and oil.
Set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add orange juice mixture and toss to coat.
Serve chilled.
Store, refrigerated. Serves 4.

title: melt in your mouth chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender (pressure cooker speeds time). Remove meat from bones.
Reserve broth; cut chicken into small pieces and place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In a saucepan, mix and bring to boil the broth and soup.
In another bowl, combine margarine, pepper, salt, flour and buttermilk.
Mix well to form batter.
Pour broth mixture over chicken.
Spoon batter over top. Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Position knife blade in food processor bowl; add half of the cookies.
Process until cookies are fine crumbs; remove from processor.
Repeat procedure with remaining cookies.
Set all cookie crumbs aside.

title: quick golden stew
directions: In a large saucepan or Dutch oven, combine carrots, potatoes, onions and just enough water to cover.
Cook, covered, until vegetables are tender, about 10 minutes.
Add peas and ham; continue to cook 5 more minutes.
Drain water.
Stir in soup and cheese.
Heat through.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: donuts
directions: Mix sugar and eggs together.
Add vanilla and milk.
Mix altogether.
Sift 3 cups flour, baking powder and nutmeg into egg mixture.
Stir until mixed.
You will need more flour.
Add 1/2 cup and mix.
If not enough, add a little more to form a teaspoon of dough for cooking.

title: banana bread or muffins
directions: Use 3 quarts of batter to a pan.
Use a #14 or #16 scoop for muffins.
Bake 25 minutes at 325° in convection oven or 1 hour for loaves of bread.
Yield: 3 1/2 sheet pans or 230 muffins.

title: almond and mushroom rice
directions: Saute onion and almonds in 3 tablespoons butter in a large, heavy saucepan until onion is soft.
Set aside.
Add remaining 3 tablespoons butter to saucepan and saute mushrooms until golden brown.
Add onion and almonds to mushrooms, along with rice.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Mix in chicken broth and salt.
Bring to boil.
Remove from heat and turn into a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Cover and bake in a 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: blueberry yum-yum
directions: Mix together cracker crumbs and margarine.
Line a 9 x 13 x 2-inch dish with half of this mixture.
Set aside the other half. Beat the Dream Whip and milk until stiff, then add vanilla.
Beat the cream cheese and sugar together until creamy and smooth and add Dream Whip mixture.
Blend thoroughly.
Spread half of this into graham cracker lined dish.
(Note:
If you will place this dish in the freezer and let each layer set, it will not run together.)
Pour in pie filling and spread.
Spread remaining creamed mixture over pie filling and top with remaining crumbs. Chill several hours or overnight.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together, adding eggs one at a time. Beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk. Stir in coconut and flavoring.
Place in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 5 minutes at 350°.

title: bro. dale's delicious vegetable soup
directions: Put a big pot on the stove; chop a roast into 1-inch squares. Trim fat from meat.
Put fat in another pot and cook down; drain juice and save.
Discard the fat.
Put meat squares into the large pot and brown; add small amount of water and simmer.
Microwave onion (do not cut) in a bowl of water for 5 minutes; puree onion and set aside.
Microwave broccoli in water; puree and set aside. Microwave celery in water; puree and set aside.
Microwave bell peppers in water; puree and set aside.
In large pot, drain into meat, juice only of corn, green beans, carrots and peas.
Add Heinz 57 steak sauce, A. 1. steak sauce, Tabasco sauce, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper to taste, tomato sauce and tomato paste into the water.
Chop garlic into soup mixture; let simmer.
Peel potatoes and chop into bite size pieces and add all vegetables (canned, pureed and potatoes) into mixture.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Serve with saltine crackers on a cold winter day.

title: green rice
directions: Mix all ingredients in casserole and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: microwave baked potatoes
directions: Wash and scrub potatoes.
Insert knife blade through center of each potato.
Microwave 4 potatoes at a time.
Microwave on High for 12 minutes.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Pound chicken breasts until about 1/4-inch thick.
Combine eggs, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken into egg mixture, then crumbs. Heat oil in frying pan.
Brown chicken on both sides; remove to shallow baking pan.
Pour excess oil from frying pan, then add tomato sauce, basil and garlic powder.
Heat to boiling; simmer 10 minutes or until thickened.
Stir in margarine.
Pour over chicken; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes; uncover.
Place Mozzarella over chicken.
Bake 10 minutes longer or until cheese melts.
Makes 6 servings.

title: snow mixture
directions: Melt bark and pour over mixture. Stir until blended.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Filling:

In nonstick skillet, heat the margarine until bubbling hot or vegetable oil until sizzling hot. Stir in the flour and cook over medium heat while stirring briskly until flour is just beginning to tan. Quickly combine broth and milk; add to the flour roux in a large stream while stirring.
Use a whisk if you have trouble with lumps in gravy. Turn heat down slightly and cook, stirring constantly, until the mixture thickens. Add the chicken, vegetables and seasonings.
Place the mixture in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Top with crust.

title: crocked ribs
directions: Brush short ribs with gravy seasoning and place in bottom of 5 1/2 quart crock-pot.
Add carrots, onions, garlic, bay leaves and potatoes.
Combine tapioca, pepper, thyme, salt and bouillon. Sprinkle mixture over short ribs.
Pour wine and water over all and cover.
Cook on high setting for 4 1/2 to 5 hours.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: harvey wallbanger's cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat for 4 minutes.
Pour batter into well-greased and lightly floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Dust with confectioners sugar.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms.
Remove stems and cut into small pieces. (Works best if microwave cut up stems for one minute High.)
Mix cut up stems and rest of ingredients in small bowl.
Stuff tops and put in shallow baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: greek meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape into one-inch balls.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Makes 45 to 50 meatballs.

title: toasted pecans
directions: Put pecans on cookie sheet.
Stir in melted butter.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes (set timer).
Take out as they begin to turn light brown.
Salt lightly.

title: beef-em-up-cups
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Add salt and barbecue sauce. Simmer gently about 15 minutes.
Grease 20 muffin cups and place 1 biscuit in each cup, shaping the biscuit with fingers to fit muffin cup.
Spoon meat mixture into biscuit cup and fill 3/4 full.
Sprinkle the top with grated cheese.
Bake for 15 minutes in 375° oven.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in baking dish; top with crushed potato chips or French fried onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Combine all ingredients to make punch.
You can use an ice ring or sherbet to add interest.
Very colorful at Christmas.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Work up with fork, roll out and use.

title: lamb marinade for butterflied leg of lamb
directions: Mix with whisk.
Marinate at least 24 hours.
Cook on low (gas grill) 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.
Baste occasionally.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Fill pie plate 2/3 full with sliced apples.
Sprinkle apples with sugar and cinnamon.
In a bowl, combine flour, sugar, egg, butter and nuts (optional).
Spread over apples.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: maegan ann's pumpkin walnut bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together. Set aside.
In a separate bowl, mix together pumpkin, water, oil and eggs.
Pour into dry mixture and mix well.
Fold in walnuts.
Pour into 2 greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in middle of loaf comes out clean. Cool before removing from pans.
Wrap in foil or waxed paper.

title: caribbean fruit sauce(club member: leslie jordan)
directions: In small mixer bowl, beat egg yolks with salt until very thick and lemon colored. Add sugar and continue beating until mixture is thick.

title: gingersnap crust(for gingersnap pumpkin pie)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly butter 10-inch pie plate. Combine cookie crumbs, sugar, nuts and orange peel.
Drizzle butter over crumb mixture.
Stir until all crumbs are moistened.
Press firmly in pie plate; bake for 10 minutes until lightly brown. Cool.

title: hamburg-potato casserole
directions: Cook beef and onions in skillet until meat is browned.
Drain grease off.
Add juice, salt, pepper, oregano and sugar.
Cook 2 minutes to blend flavors.
Put sliced potatoes and meat mixture in layers in 9 x 13-inch pan, starting with meat mixture and ending with meat mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° to 375° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are tender.
Remove cover and top with cheese.
Allow cheese time to melt before serving.

title: chocoroons
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine in a large bowl the coconut, flour and salt.
Stir in condensed milk and blend well.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Combine and bake in a 450° oven for 20 minutes.
Makes 4 small containers. Serve warm.

title: fried turkey seasoning marinade
directions: Mix well and store in airtight container.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pack firmly into ungreased loaf pan. Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken corn soup
directions: Boil chicken in 4 quarts of water until tender.
Cook chicken and cut in pieces.
Cut up carrots, celery and onion and cook until done in water from chicken.
Add bouillon cubes, cut up chicken, creamed corn and regular whole corn.
Boil noodles according to directions on package in another pot and drain.
Add to rest of soup.
Salt and pepper to your taste and cook for another few minutes.

title: swamp soup
directions: Simmer ham bone in water until you can cut up meat in bite size pieces.
Cut potatoes into bite size pieces.
Add potatoes and barley.
Cook with water until tender.
Add frozen packages of spinach and cook until all done.
This will thicken.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Chill milk and whip. Blend in mayonnaise with other ingredients. Crumble cheese and add seasonings.

title: chicken enchilada
directions: Cook chicken in a skillet or boil until tender. Set aside. Combine soup and sour cream in a bowl and set aside. In a medium sauce pan over medium heat, melt butter and saute onions and chili powder. Remove heat and add chicken, green chilies, and 3 Tbsp. of soup mixture. Bacon and a little cheese may be added. Spread half of the soup mixture in a shallow baking dish. Along one side of each tortilla, spread about 1/4 c. chicken mixture. Roll up each tortilla around filling and place seam side down in pan. Spread remaining soup mixture over enchiladas. Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350 for 25 minutes.

title: country fried swiss steak
directions: Cut meat into steaks (approximately 8 portions).
Coat meat with beaten egg; then flour.
In electric skillet, season meat while browning on both sides.
(Use high heat - do not scorch.) Pour meat and drippings into 8-quart stew pot.
Add tomatoes, carrots, onions, black pepper and 2 cups water (more as necessary). Salt, pepper and garlic to taste.
Cover and stew on medium heat for 2 1/2 hours; stir frequently.
Do not allow all water to cook out.
Serve over or with mashed potatoes.

title: baked apples
directions: Before baking, apples may be filled with raisins and nuts or mincemeat.
Honey may be substituted for part of the sugar.
Place apples, which have been peeled 2/3 way down, in long baking dish. Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Add water.
Place in preheated 425° oven and bake for 45 minutes.
Baste several times during baking and upon removing from oven.
Serve warm or cold.

title: squash puppies
directions: Trim ends off squash; slice and cook for about 20 minutes or until tender. Drain squash well. Mash and drain until all the water is gone. Combine squash and remaining ingredients. Drop scant tablespoon into hot oil (350°) in deep fryer until golden brown or about 5 minutes. Yields about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: cheese logs
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Shape into a roll about 5 inches long and 1-1/2 inch.
Roll in paprika, chili powder, or steak seasoning.
Chill and slice.

title: barbecue meat balls
directions: Mix and form balls. Place on flat baking sheet. Bake until brown, about 30 minutes; drain. Place in container to stay warm. Pour barbecue sauce over balls. Let simmer. Makes about 50 meat balls. Perfect for parties!

title: chicken breasts saltimbocca style
directions: This takes awhile to fix up.
Cut each chicken breast in half and pound until thin.
Place a slice of ham and a slice of cheese on each breast piece.
Roll up, stick ends in and secure with a toothpick.
Dip chicken rolls into mixture of flour, Parmesan cheese, salt, sage and pepper.
Save the leftover flour mixture. Chill chicken for at least one hour.
(I do all of this the day before.)
Put salad oil in the frying pan and brown the chicken rolls.
Place the browned chicken in the crock-pot.
Add soup mixed with wine.
Cover and cook for 6 to 7 hours.

title: sand tarts
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.
Roll out thin.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Brush with beaten egg whites and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: cha-cha chile for fine
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add tomato sauce and chili mix. Squash up whole tomatoes with hand.
Add kidney beans, squished tomatoes and beer.
Stir and allow to simmer for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Serve, topped with shredded Cheddar or mushrooms if desired.

title: danish apple bars
directions: Mix flour and salt and cut in shortening.
Blend egg yolk in measuring cup.
Add enough milk to make 2/3 cup of liquid.
Add to flour mixture. Roll half of dough to 17 x 12-inch rectangle.
Fit into jelly roll pan, bringing up the sides.
Place cornflakes on top of pastry.
Add apples.

Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon. Roll the other half of the dough to a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch rectangle and place over top. Crimp edges together. Whip egg white until frothy and spread over dough. Bake 1 hour at 400°.
Frost with powdered sugar glaze.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift together sugar and flour.
Place margarine, cocoa and water in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Add to flour mixture. Then add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla.
