Bake in 9 x 13-inch or 15 x 1-inch pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: meat and rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put dry onion soup mix in bottom of pan.
Pour raw rice in.
Cover with meat.
Spread creamed soup and meat; pour in water.
(Use 1/2 cup more water for moister rice.) Bake for 1 hour.

title: buttermilk fried chicken
directions: Place chicken in a flat dish.
Pour buttermilk over; cover and refrigerate one hour.
Combine flour, salt and pepper in a bag. Drain chicken.
Toss in flour mixture.
Shake off excess; place on waxed paper 15 minutes.
Heat 1/4 to 1/2 inch oil.
Fry until brown and juices run clear.

title: orange cream syrup
directions: In small mixer bowl, combine ingredients; beat until smooth and creamy
(about 5 minutes).
Store in refrigerator. Serve over pancakes, waffles or fruit.

title: ham spread
directions: Blend all ingredients and chill.
Makes about 2 cups for sandwiches later.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: oyster casserole
directions: Place oysters in bottom of 1 quart casserole dish.
Crush crackers, layer on top of oysters.
Pour lemon juice over mixture. In a bowl, beat eggs, milk, Worcestershire, red pepper and seafood seasoning together.
Pour over oysters and crackers.
Bake in 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes until dish is firm and brown.

title: microwave chili dip
directions: Soften and spread cream cheese in an 8 x 8-inch microwave cake or pie pan.
Mix the chopped green chilies with the can of Hormel chili and spread over the cream cheese.
Mix the Monterey Jack and Cheddar cheeses and sprinkle over top evenly.
Microwave about 8 minutes or until cheese is completely melted.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, molasses and boiling
water
in a large mixing bowl.
Sift together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and ginger
and add to boiling water mixture.
Add eggs.
Mix well and pour
into a greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: vegetarian chicken pot pie
directions: In no-stick pan, braise Fri-chix until slightly brown.
Add eggs and scramble until slightly brown, adding onion and flour. Saute mix.
Stir in skim milk.
Add cooked vegetables.
Bring mix to boil.
Pour into flat casserole and top with mayonnaise, milk and flour mix.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.
Add more liquid if needed, so it is not too dry.

title: pecan caramel triangles
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, combine flour and sugar; cut butter in until crumbly.
Press firmly on bottom of a 13 by 9 inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes or until lightly browned around edges.
Meanwhile in heavy saucepan, combine sweetened milk, cream, and vanilla.
Over medium-high heat, cook and stir until mixture comes to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium; cook and stir until mixture thickens, 8 to 10 minutes.
Stir in pecans.
Spread evenly over prepared crust.
Bake 20 minutes or until golden brown. Cool.
Garnish with chocolate drizzle.
Chill.
Cut into triangles. Store covered at room temperature.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Mix together; spoon into greased 9 x 13 pan.
Top with cinnamon (sprinkle generously and dot with butter).
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool 30 to 45 minutes.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: chicken curry southern style
directions: On waxed paper, coat chicken with flour.
In a 12-inch skillet on medium-high heat, in hot salad oil, cook chicken until it is browned on all sides.
Remove chicken from skillet.
In drippings over medium heat, cook garlic, onions, celery, green pepper, curry and salt until veggies are tender (10 minutes), stirring occasionally.
Stir in tomatoes and their liquid.
Add chicken pieces and heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer 40 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: peanut butter pie(club member: kristi mayfield)
directions: Mix peanut butter and powdered sugar until crumbly. Put 3/4 of crumbs in bottom of pie shell. Pour pudding on top of crumbs. Spread Cool Whip over the pudding. Sprinkle with the rest of the crumbs. Refrigerate.

title: orange pudding
directions: Cook first 6 ingredients in double boiler until very thick. Allow to cool.
Whip the cream.
Mix with cooked custard. Alternate layers of vanilla wafers and custard in ice tray and store in freezer until ready to slice and serve.

title: supreme chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Wash and dry chicken pieces; place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole pan.
Dot with butter or margarine. Bake 30 minutes or until chicken is browned lightly.
Lower oven to 300°.
Mix the cream of celery soup and cream of mushroom soup with 2 soup cans milk; pour over chicken pieces.
Bake for another 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cathedral window candy(microwave)
directions: Place butter and chocolate chips in medium size heat resistant mixing bowl.
Heat, uncovered, in microwave oven for 4 minutes or until melted.
Combine egg and sugar.
Add slowly to chocolate mixture.
Stir in marshmallows until well coated.
Pour onto waxed paper.
Form into an 18-inch long log.
Refrigerate.
Slice when ready to serve.

title: easy bread sticks
directions: Cut rolls in fourths, lengthwise, to make fingers.
Melt garlic spread and butter.
Brush on cut sides of rolls.
Sprinkle with cheese and seed.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake in a 450° oven until toasted.
Serve hot.

title: pizza dough
directions: Add enough flour to make stiff.
Knead 5 to 10 minutes. Let raise for 10 to
minutes.
Spread on pizza pan and top with sauce and whatever you like.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Cook chicken in olive oil until done.
Add garlic, onion and green pepper; cook 2 minutes.
Add tomato sauce, whole tomatoes, celery seed, bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Cook 1/2 hour, covered. Add wine and cook uncovered for 15 minutes.
Serve over noodles.

title: nut pie
directions: Beat egg whites stiffly.
Slowly add sugar, vanilla, baking powder, crushed graham crackers and walnuts.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie tin.
Bake for 1/2 hour (30 minutes) in 350° oven. Cool.
Top with whipped topping.
Chill at least 4 hours before serving.
Can be prepared the day before (including topping) as it is almost tastier.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into well-greased baking dish. Top with additional crushed saltines. Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lo-cal ambrosia
directions: Mix all ingredients. Store covered in refrigerator.

title: jam cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together first, then add all other ingredients and mix well.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours to 2 hours at 325°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put rice in bottom of casserole dish.
Chip up oleo over rice. Season the fryer.
Cut up fryer and lay over rice.
Mix soups and water; pour over rice and chicken.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: creamy cookie icing
directions: In a small mixer bowl, beat egg white, lemon juice and powdered sugar.
(The amount depends on the consistency you want.) Stir in food coloring, if desired.

title: refrigerator slaw
directions: Arrange in alternate layers in covered bowl the cabbage and onions.
Add 7/8 cup sugar on top and toss.

title: vegetable burger soup
directions: In frying pan brown meat; drain off fat.
Put in the pot with all other ingredients.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat to simmer and cover and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Custard:
In top of double boiler, scald milk.
Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Stir sugar and cornstarch into scalded milk.
Stir. Beat egg yolks.
Add to hot mixture, little at a time.
Cook until firm.
Cool.
Add flavor.

title: candied cranberry, orange and lettuce salad
directions: Spread cranberries in shallow baking dish; sprinkle with sugar.
Cover tightly with foil; bake for 1 hour at 350°, stirring occasionally.
They will shrivel and appear soft.
Cool to room temperature; refrigerate until well chilled (up to 2 days).
Tear lettuce into bite size pieces; wrap and refrigerate until ready to use.
Before serving, toss lettuce with oranges and as much dressing as needed.
Sprinkle with pepper and cranberries.
Toss again.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and spread the ingredients in layers.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes until brown on top. Serve warm or cold.
Top with whipped cream, Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: crab salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except greens, refrigerate a short time.
Serve on greens.
Makes four servings.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients to a soft ball stage.
Set off and let cool a little.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Stir this until it becomes real thick. Pour in a buttered dish.
Cool and cut.

title: fruit salad with sauce
directions: Strawberries, blueberries and diced apple may be added if desired.
Drain all canned fruit.

title: jew bread
directions: Mix brown sugar and eggs and cook in double boiler for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Stir in dry ingredients and vanilla.
Spread in two small well-greased pans.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: date logs
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients.
Stir in dates, walnuts and eggs.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan to bake in a slow 325° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool and cut into 48 logs.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Dainty and delicious with tea or coffee.

title: apple or banana fritters
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, sugar and salt together.
Combine egg and milk; add to dry ingredients, beating until smooth.
Add vegetable oil and mix well.
Dip apples or banana or pineapple in the batter and fry in deep hot oil (375°) for about 4 minutes or until light brown.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook together.
Add red food coloring.
Pour into cooled pie crust filled with berries.

title: cookies on a stick
directions: Mix and shape into round balls.
Insert popsicle sticks. Flatten onto cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: fresh blueberry syrup
directions: Combine all the ingredients. Bring to a boil and cook for 10 minutes. Serve either warm or chilled.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Pour dressing over and chill 4 hours.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Place ingredients in a bowl and mix until smooth. Frost cake while hot. Refrigerate 8 hours or more. (When I'm in a hurry, I just refrigerate it for 2 hours and it's still good.)

title: country ham and chicken casserole
directions: Place a 3 x 3 square of country ham on bottom of greased casserole dish.
Place 1 chicken breast on top of ham.
Place 1 slice of bacon on top of chicken.
Combine sour cream and cream of mushroom soup.
Spoon around edges of ham and chicken and in between also.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, uncovered.	Serves 6 to 8. This makes a very good casserole for company.

title: texas state fair grand prize pound cake
directions: Use 2 bowls to mix this cake.
In first bowl, mix together the flour and butter and work until it is creamy.
In second bowl, mix eggs and sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Then mix the mixtures of the 2 bowls together, beating well.
Add baking powder, salt, butter flavoring, lemon extract and vanilla; mix thoroughly. Pour into large tube pan.
Bake 1 hour in 300° oven.
Increase to 325° and bake 15 to 20 minutes longer.

title: tropical cranberry juice
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pitcher.
Chill and serve.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° to 350° for about 1 hour or until set.

title: sweet 'n' sour pork
directions: Cut tenderloin into 1/2-inch thick slices. In a wok or large nonstick skillet, heat oil. Add pork and cook and stir over medium-high heat for 6 to 8 minutes or until cooked through. Remove pork from wok. Reduce heat. Add white wine or broth, kumquats or orange and hoisin sauce to wok. Cook and stir 1 minute. Return pork to wok. Heat through. Stir in onion and sesame seed. Serve over rice. Makes 4 servings.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and shape into small balls. Brown balls in skillet. Combine chili sauce, jelly and lemon juice. Bring to a boil. Add meatballs and simmer to heat through.

title: frozen pineapple delight
directions: Press together the first 2 ingredients in a 9 x 12-inch pan and keep 1/2 out for top.
Cream your 1/2 cup soft butter; add 10x sugar.
Beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat until smooth. Add vanilla and spread on crumbs in pan.
Whip cream until stiff; add well drained pineapple and cherries.
Spread over mixture in pan.
Add rest of crumbs and put in freezer.
Remove 1 hour before serving.

title: monkey bread
directions: Quarter biscuits.
Put sugar and cinnamon in a large plastic bag. Add biscuit pieces and shake to coat.
Melt margarine in Bundt pan.
Place biscuit pieces in pan. Add extra sugar and cinnamon if needed.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute onion with butter.
Add remaining ingredients until potatoes are soft.
Put into blender and blend until smooth. Return to pan and add half and half.
Thoroughly heat.
Put in soup bowls.
Top with sour cream and chives.

title: moma's banana pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook in a double boiler, stir often. Cook until it becomes a custard, remove from heat. Line a large bowl or casserole dish with wafers. Cut up bananas and layer over wafers. Spread custard over the bananas. You can layer this if desired.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Pour in casserole dish. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: oven baked eggs
directions: Line a 9 x 13 greased pan with bread.
Put cheese over bread. Combine eggs, milk, onions, mushrooms and green peppers and pour over top.
Crumble bacon and spread on top.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, uncovered.

title: peanut butter crunch pie
directions: Combine peanut butter and confectioners sugar until crumbly, reserve 2 Tbsp for garnish.
Sprinkle rest over bottom of pie shell. For filling: combine sugar, cornstarch, flour, salt, egg yolks milk and butter in saucepan.
Bring to a boil stirring constantly for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.Add vanilla. Pour over peanut butter mixture in crust.
In small bowl, beat egg whites until foamy, add sugar, gradually beating until smooth and stiff. Spread over filling, sealing edges.
Sprinkle with reserved peanut butter mixture.
Bake in 350 oven for about 5 minutes or until meringue is lightly brown.
Serves 8.

title: eclair cake
directions: Line a 9 X 13 pan with graham crackers.
Mix together all other ingredients and pour on top of graham crackers.
Chill.

title: chicken cheese ball
directions: Mix together and set in refrigerator for 3 to 4 hours, then form in ball and roll in crushed pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: hot wassail
directions: Remember 4 cups of cooked egg noodles will serve about 4 people.
Use your own judgement as to the amount you want to prepare, depending on the people you will be serving.

title: spaghetti for a crowd
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add all other ingredients except spaghetti.
Let simmer.
Pour over cooked spaghetti.
Freeze or serve.

title: easy pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375° as well as baking sheet. In a large bowl with wire whisk, combine first 6 ingredients. Place pie crusts on baking sheet.
Pour filling into pie crusts.
Bake 70 minutes (45 minutes for regular crust) or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Cool on wire rack.
Garnish with whipped cream.
Makes 8 servings, 12 with regular crusts.

title: plum cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Then add eggs, Crisco oil and baby food.
Mix all together and bake in tube pan about 1 hour at 350°.
While still hot, glaze with 1 cup confectioners sugar, juice of 1 lemon and a little oleo.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Mix potatoes and eggs well; form balls around marshmallows. Roll in corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until balls pop open.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350°
for 30 minutes. Check for desired tenderness of ingredients.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cook potatoes, celery and onion in water to cover for 30 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; heat to boiling and decrease to simmer until heated through, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Season to taste.

title: baked catfish parmesan
directions: Combine cheese, flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
Set aside. Combine milk and egg.
Dip fillets in egg-milk mixture then dredge in flour mixture.
Arrange in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Drizzle with melted butter and sprinkle with almonds.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix all together, folding in Cool Whip last.
Pour into pie shells and chill.
Makes 2 pies.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream butter, Crisco and sugar; add eggs, one a time.
Beat well.
Add alternately milk and dry ingredients.
Beat on low speed.
Add vanilla.
Bake in tube pan about 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.

title: chicken stroganoff
directions: Brown chicken, onion and mushrooms in butter.
Add cream of mushroom soup, salt and pepper.
Simmer over low heat for 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and fold in sour cream.
Serve over rice.

title: orange-spiced pecans
directions: Heat oven to 275°.
Spread pecans on ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 275° for 10 minutes.
In large saucepan combine sugar, orange juice, cinnamon, salt and cloves.
Bring to a boil; boil 2 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat; stir in warm pecans.
Using slotted spoon, remove pecans to foil or waxed paper.
Separate with fork; let dry.
Store in airtight container in cool dry place.
Makes 6 cups.

title: mushroom spread
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter or margarine.
Add sherry and thyme. Cook 8 minutes or more or until almost dry.
In food processor or blender, combine mushroom mixture with cream cheese.
Process until smooth.
Place into crock and refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.
Serve with crackers.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: kathryn erickson's monster cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° about 12 minutes.
Makes many cookies...

title: zesty shrimp dip
directions: In a small bowl, combine ingredients; mix well. Chill.
Serve with assorted fresh vegetables or potato chips.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 2 cups dip.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Blend sugar and shortening. Add eggs and buttermilk with soda in.
Add remaining ingredients and drop on cookie sheet. Sprinkle with white sugar or colored sugars for holidays.
Bake at 325° to 350° until done in center.

title: chinese beef, bean sprouts and broccoli
directions: Cut beef across grain, 1/4 x 1-inch.
Mix beef with next 5 ingredients; set aside.
Cut broccoli tops into flowerets, 1 to 2 inches long and 1/2-inch thick.
Put 2 tablespoons oil in hot pan. Add broccoli; stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Remove and keep warm.
Add remaining oil and ginger root.
Stir in beef; stir-fry 2 minutes, or until almost done.
Add broccoli and bean sprouts; mix lightly. Serve with long grain rice at once with Chinese noodles.
Serves 4.

title: toffee bars
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Very rich.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat well.

title: homemade style done easy chicken noodle soup
directions: Cook chicken, onion, salt and pepper in a crock-pot.
When chicken is done, remove and pick chicken from bones.
Add to crock-pot the picked chicken, mushrooms, egg noodles and more salt. Cook until egg noodles are done, usually about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: scallop potatoes
directions: In a baking dish, place a layer of potatoes. Sprinkle with onions, bacon, salt, pepper and crushed saltine crackers. Keep layering until dish is nearly full. Pour milk 3/4 of the way up the potatoes. Cover. Bake at 350 for 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are tender.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix beans with soup and milk.
Pour in baking dish.
Top with dried onions.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Trim tough ends off mushroom stems; remove and mince remaining stems.
Reserve mushroom caps.
In medium bowl, combine minced stems, Ricotta cheese and remaining ingredients, except Parmesan cheese.
Spoon mixture into caps.

title: deluxe meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients (except beef) and let stand 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Then mix in with the beef.
Place in a greased loaf pan or casserole bowl.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, then drain off the fat. Then cover the top of the meat loaf with tomato sauce or ketchup. Return to the oven and continue to cook 15 minutes longer.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Mix sugar, oleo and Crisco together.
Mix in eggs, one at a time.
Add milk and flour alternately.
Mix baking powder, salt and vanilla.
Fold in coconut.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: deluxe double pecan pies
directions: *Note:
One-half cup black walnuts may be added with the pecans, which makes it a deluxe pie.

title: breakfast muffins
directions: On each muffin half, place 2 slices of Canadian bacon, 1 slice of tomato and top with sliced Cheddar cheese.
Broil 4 to 5 minutes, or until cheese is lightly browned and bubbly.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Beat eggs; add remaining ingredients.
Blend until flour is dampened and mixture is fairly smooth.
Cook on hot griddle. Makes about 12 pancakes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, sugar and wine vinegar.
Toss with remaining ingredients and refrigerate.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: tortilla chicken
directions: Grease the sides and bottom of crock pot. Mix chicken, soup, salsa, sour cream and onion together.
Layer on salsa then chicken mixture, followed by tortillas.
Save cheese until right before serving, 10 to 15 minutes, cook on low 4 to 5 hours.

title: "souffle froid au chocolat"
directions: Melt chocolate squares over hot water.
When melted, stir in confectioners sugar.
Heat milk and add to mixture; bring to boiling point, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add gelatin, softened in 3 tablespoons cold water, granulated sugar, vanilla and salt.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Beat until mixture is light.
Beat cream and add to chocolate mixture.
Pour into 2-quart dish.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Steam halved potatoes, covered, over boiling water until fully cooked, about 15 minutes.
Test potatoes for doneness using a skewer to avoid splitting them.
Toss potatoes with melted butter, herbs and salt until coated.
Serve hot.
Makes about 3 cups.
Total time: 20 minutes.

title: mushroom croustades
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Cut bread in rounds. Butter. Place in small muffin tin. Bake 8 minutes to toasty color. Let cool. (Can freeze.)

title: not-so-sweet pecan pie
directions: In a medium bowl, beat eggs slightly.
Beat in the next 4 ingredients.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes or until berries pop open, skimming foam from surface. Cool to room temperature.
Relish will set as it cools.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate syrup snacking brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 x 1-inch).
Beat margarine and sugar in large bowl.
Beat in syrup, eggs and flour thoroughly.
Stir in nuts.
Next a true chocoholic will wish to stir in chocolate chips; these are optional.
Pour in pan.
Bake until toothpick comes out clean, 30 to 35 minutes. Cool.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Make 48 squares.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Cream butter; blend in sugar and eggs.
Add nuts, cinnamon, nutmeg, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Add flour and applesauce.
Mix well.
Grease pans and fill 2/3 full of batter.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: mexican rice casserole
directions: In casserole dish, layer tamales, then rice, then chili.
Heat at 350° until hot, then sprinkle cheese on top.
Return to oven until cheese is melted.

title: "breakfast" sausage and gravy
directions: Fry
sausage
and
drain excess grease.
Add butter and allow to
melt.
Add flour and allow to brown slightly.
Stir in
milk until desired consistency.
Let simmer and serve over toast or biscuits.

title: taco-chicken bake
directions: Use 9 x 13 lightly greased pan or a nonstick pan. Mix only 1 cup of the corn chips with all the other ingredients, except the olives and cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, uncovered. Top with the olives, then cheese, then remaining 2 cups chips and bake 5 minutes more.

title: 7 minute frosting
directions: Boil sugar and water and then pour this into the egg whites. Beat while pouring and then add syrup.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter; add rest of ingredients and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: meatballs
directions: Soak bread in milk and combine with egg white.
Mix in ground beef, salt, thyme and onion.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch meatballs and bake for 30 minutes at 375°.
(You may cool and freeze meatballs for later use.)
Combine beef broth, water, ground pepper, yogurt and cornstarch in skillet.
Heat until thick.
Add meatballs and mushrooms, if desired.
Cook until meatballs are heated through. Serve over rice.
Serves 3.

title: spanish steak
directions: Flour steak and brown in pan.
Place in casserole dish.
In pan, place onion, pepper, tomatoes, catsup, water, salt and pepper.
Let simmer 5 minutes, then pour over steak in casserole. Cook at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes or until tender.

title: glaze for bread or cake
directions: Mix all and boil for 2 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Good over banana nut bread!

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Tip 1:
If you are caught without confectioners sugar, make your own in minutes!
Combine 1 cup regular granulated sugar and 1 tablespoon cornstarch in blender.
Blend until powdery.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: texas okra and tomatoes
directions: Cook bacon in a large skillet until crisp; remove bacon, reserving drippings in skillet.
Crumble bacon and set aside. Saute onion and jalapeno pepper in bacon drippings until tender. Add remaining ingredients and cook over medium heat 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add bacon and serve immediately.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: company casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Saute ground chuck in 1 tablespoon margarine until brown.
Drain.
Stir in tomato sauce.
Remove from heat.
Add cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream and chopped onion.
In 2-quart casserole, spread layer of noodles, layer of cheese mixture and repeat layers until all is used.
Pour melted margarine on top.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Chill.
About 1 hour before serving, heat oven to 375°.
Bake 45 minutes. Yield: 6 servings.

title: chuck wagon roundup
directions: Beat egg; add oil and milk.
Add dry ingredients.
Spread bottom and sides of greased 9-inch pie pan.
Reserve 2 wieners. Cut others in 1/2-inch slices.
Combine with rest of ingredients. Spoon into center of dough in pie pan.
Cut 2 wieners lengthwise, then crosswise.
Arrange, spoke fashion, skin side up, on bean mixture.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 375°.
Let stand for 10 minutes before cutting into wedges.

title: million dollar dessert
directions: Blend flour, margarine and pecans.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool. Mix cream cheese, sugar and 1/2 carton Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust.
Mix pudding mix and milk.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Garnish with nuts and shaved Hershey bar.
Truly a good dessert!!

title: cream cheese wreath
directions: Combine cream cheese and salad dressing well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Chill.
Place a small glass in center of plate and drop mixture around it to form a wreath.
Smooth with spatula and remove glass.
Garnish with chopped parsley and pimiento just before serving.
Serve with crackers and vegetables.

title: hungarian coffee cake
directions: Over low heat mix milk, 1/2 cup sugar, Crisco and salt; cool to lukewarm.
Add dissolved yeast, eggs and flour.
Mix well, dough will be sticky.
Knead on floured board; cover and let rise 1 hour or until doubled.
Punch down, let rest 10 minutes.
Pinch off dough and shape into ping pong size balls.
Roll in melted margarine and mixture of 3/4 cup sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Arrange balls in 2 rows in large greased tube pan.
Place a second layer of 2 rows on top; sprinkle with remaining nut mixture and melted margarine.
Cover and let rise until doubled.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cover top lightly with foil during last 20 minutes of baking.
Remove foil, let cool 15 minutes and invert on serving platter.

title: jello punch
directions: Mix boiling water, Jell-O and sugar in large pot.
Heat until sugar and Jell-O are dissolved.
Cool.
Add pineapple juice, orange juice, lemonade and 1 gallon of water.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale for fizz.
May be frozen for later use.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Grease bottom and sides of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Reserve 2/3 cup dry cake mix for filling.
Combine remaining dry cake mix, margarine and 1 egg.
Mix until crumbly.
Press into pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until light brown.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Wash potatoes and prick several times with a fork.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until done.
Let cool.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise, then scoop out pulp and set aside.
Discard skins.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Mix apples, celery and nuts with enough mayonnaise to moisten.

title: no cook fruit pudding
directions: Place sliced bananas in lemon juice to keep them from turning dark.
Put your chopped peaches and pineapple in a bowl.
Mix instant pudding with 1/2 cup pineapple juice and pour into bowl over chopped fruit.
If you wish, you may wait until time to serve to add your sliced bananas.
Make ahead of time so it will have time to season.

title: split pea soup
directions: Heat chicken broth until boiling; add peas and boil, uncovered, 2 minutes. Remove from heat and cover; let stand at least 1 hour. Warm peas and stir in remaining ingredients. Cook over medium-high heat until tender. Makes about 2 quarts.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add 1/2 cup of the mixture to 8 ounces boiling water. Stir.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press in 13 x 9-inch Pyrex pan. Bake 7 minutes at 400° or 375°; cool.
Blend next 3 ingredients and spread over cooled crust and chill.
Dissolve jello in water; add strawberries and pineapple.
Chill slightly and pour over cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate.
Top with Cool Whip if desired.

title: chewy butter cake
directions: Press in 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Great on crackers or toasted bread squares.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Sprinkle 5 ounces bacon, 1 1/2 ounces ham and 4 ounces cheese evenly in the bottom of each pie shell.
Mix together eggs, cream, milk and seasoning.
Pour over contents in bottom of crusts.

title: christmas punch
directions: In large bowl, dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup of boiling water.
Add 1 1/2 cups of sugar.
Stir until dissolved.
Add orange juice and lemonade, prepared according to directions on cans.
Add pineapple juice; stir in balance of sugar and mix well.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Makes 50 cups.

title: yummy peach cobbler
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart round cake dish or casserole.
Blend next 3 ingredients.
Beat in eggs and buttermilk.
Set aside 2 cups batter.
Spoon remainder over fruit.
Blend butter and marmalade into reserved batter. Pour into 12 greased 2 1/2-inch muffin pan cups.
Place cobbler on lower shelf, muffins on upper shelf of a preheated oven (375°). Bake muffins 20 minutes and cobbler for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve muffins warm, and serve cobbler warm with cream and nutmeg.

title: buffalo wings with blue cheese dip
directions: Cut wing tips off at joint and discard.
Cut each wing in half at joint.

title: cheesy scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix mayonnaise and flour; stir in milk.
Cook until thick and boils; add cheese.
Place sliced potatoes in a 10 x 16-inch glass baking dish and top with cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt, soda and cinnamon together.
Stir in oil and eggs one at a time, mixing well.
Add carrots and nuts. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: scalloped scallops
directions: Cut scallops.
Mix bread crumbs, crackers, salt, pepper and butter or margarine.
Grease baking dish.
Pour light cream over all with sherry.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: ham and cheese casserole
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender.
Add other ingredients and turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes or until an inserted knife comes out clean.
Serves 6.

title: red beans and rice(servings: 6)
directions: Boil pork for 5 minutes to get rid of salt.
Put pork in second water (hot) and add beans and water (should be 1/2-inch above beans).
Add immediately 1 bell pepper, 1 chopped onion, celery, garlic, Italian seasoning and whole hot pepper.
Cook slowly for 2 to 3 hours, until gravy is thick and beans tender.
Just before dishing out, add a pinch of Italian seasoning again.
Salt to taste and serve with rice.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.
Makes a cool, light dessert.

title: roll-out cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar, then add eggs, then flour, baking soda, vanilla and cream of tartar.
Chill dough, then roll out thin and cut out.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Bake on cookie sheet.

title: easy cherry pineapple cobbler
directions: Place in layers in a 9 x 13-inch pan the crushed pineapple, then the cherry pie filling and lastly, spread the cake mix over all.
Drizzle the melted butter over the cake mix.
Add just enough pineapple juice to moisten any dry spots.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream butter with sugar and add well beaten yolks.
Mix meal with milk and add to eggs.
Add flavoring; stir until smooth and add whites, well beaten.
Pour into pastry shell and bake in moderate oven at 350° until custard sets and crust is slightly browned.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening; add sugar. Gradually add eggs. Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder, salt and vanilla; add alternately with milk to creamed mixture. Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour. Add chocolate glaze if desired.

title: brown rice confetti salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a saucepan; cook according to package directions.
Remove from heat and cool.

title: raisin n' nut pull-apart coffee cake
directions: In 1-quart saucepan, scald milk; stir in 1/4 cup butter until melted.
Cool to warm (105° to 115°).
In large mixer bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add cooled milk mixture, 2 cups flour, 1/4 cup sugar, egg and salt.
Beat at medium speed, scraping bowl often, until smooth (1 to 2 minutes).
By hand, stir in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic (about 10 minutes).
Place in greased bowl; turn greased side up. Cover; let rise in warm place until double in size (about 1 1/2 hours).
Dough is ready if indentation remains when touched.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Mix all together.
Pour in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut into 1-inch squares and serve warm as hors d'oeuvres.
Cut into large pieces for side dish.

title: oatmeal drop candy
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and boil for 5 minutes.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until smooth.
Add oatmeal; drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Cool.

title: seafoam
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and water to thin syrup stage.
Pour 1/3 of syrup slowly into egg whites, constantly beating.
Boil remaining syrup to thread stage; add 1/2 to egg whites, constantly beating. Boil remaining syrup to hard ball stage and add to egg whites along with vanilla and nuts.
Drop on wax paper.

title: oysters casino
directions: Imbed the oysters in the pans of rock salt.
Cream together the butter, shallots, parsley, green pepper, celery and lemon juice.
Put a piece of the butter mixture on each oyster.
Top with pimento and a square of the bacon.
Bake at 450° until the bacon is browned, about 5 to 8 minutes.
Serves 2.

title: chicken in the garden
directions: For each serving:
Cut off a 40-inch length of foil and fold in half.

Place on foil chicken (1 breast or a leg and thigh), 1 pared potato (may be cut up in smaller pieces), 1 tomato (cut up), 1 onion (cut up), 4 to 5 mushrooms and 2 to 3 green pepper rings. Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons Minute rice, 1 teaspoon Worcestershire sauce and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Dot with butter.
Fold foil over and seal edges tightly.
Bake at 450° for approximately 1 1/4 hours, turning package over every 20 to 30 minutes.

title: amy's taco soup(this makes a big pot!)
directions: Brown and drain beef. In a large pot add all ingredients (NOT TOPPING).
Also, do not drain cans, you want juice and all. Simmer for 45 minutes.

title: deer jerky
directions: Mix first 10 ingredients to make a marinade.
Soak meat, refrigerated, in the marinade overnight up to 24 hours.
Drain well.
Coat with coarse ground black pepper.
Line the bottom of the oven with foil.
Spear meat with toothpicks and hang from the oven rack.
Set oven at 150°.
Keep oven door ajar to help the meat dry.
(This can also be done in my dehydrator.)

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugars, pumpkin and oil.
Beat until blended.
Add eggs.
Add flour and seasonings.
Beat well.
Stir in raisins, nuts and water.
Put in a well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: middle east pottage
directions: Place cracked wheat, lentils, onion soup and oil into the boiling water.
Simmer slowly for 40 minutes, stirring as needed. Add onion and grated carrot and mix well.
Cook gently for 5 minutes, until vegetables are soft.
Place in casserole dish and top with sliced tomato.
Bake for 30 minutes in moderate oven. Serve as a main entree with vegetables.
Delicious on toast with tossed salad for a light evening meal.

title: pudding candy
directions: Combine pudding mix, evaporated milk and sugar and bring to a boil for 5 minutes.
Stir in nuts and butter.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Stir until thick.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs to mixture.
Cream well.
Add flour and milk alternately (a little flour with a little milk).
Add vanilla, salt and baking powder.
Add can of chocolate syrup; mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.

title: pork creole and rice
directions: In large frypan, brown steaks in hot oil.
Drain off excess oil.
Add remaining ingredients; stir to combine.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer, covered, 30 minutes until rice is cooked and steaks are tender.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Make a cheese sauce:
Melt butter and flour together; then add milk and cook until it thickens.
Remove from heat and add cheese. Stir until cheese melts and is well blended.

title: corn bread from a mix(microwave)
directions: Prepare according to package.
Grease an 8-inch round baking dish.
Heat uncovered on roast for 7 to 8 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Let stand 3 to 4 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peanut butter milk balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well and form into small balls.
These are ready to eat.
Might wish to decorate the tops with M&M's candies.

title: deluxe turkey salad
directions: Mix turkey, celery and grapes.
Brown almonds in shallow saucepan.
Add to the mixture along with the salt.
Mix mayonnaise and Cool Whip together before folding into the salad mixture. Serve as sandwich with pita bread.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add Italian sauce; set aside.
In a bowl, mix cottage cheese, eggs, parsley and Parmesan cheese; set aside.
Cook noodles and drain.

title: baked empanadas (panama style)
directions: Filling Preparation:
Cook meat, onion, garlic, salt and pepper for 4 to 5 minutes, stirring, then add the rest of the ingredients.
Cook about 25 to 30 minutes, until potatoes are done; ladle off any excess oil.
Let cool.

title: peachy pork medallions
directions: Partially freeze pork; trim fat from meat.
Cut meat diagonally across grain into 1/4-inch slices.
Coat a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add half of pork; cook for 3 minutes on each side, or until pork is lightly browned.
Remove pork from skillet; drain and set aside and keep warm.
Repeat procedure with remaining pork slices.
Wipe drippings from skillet.

title: marinated broccoli
directions: Mix vinegar, oil, sugar, dill weed, salt, pepper and garlic powder together well.
Pour over broccoli and marinate for 24 hours.
Drain and serve.

title: chili sauce(a good old-fashioned recipe)
directions: Combine ingredients and boil until thick, about 2 hours.
Can in sterilized jars.

title: chess pie
directions: Heat sugar, brown sugar, milk, flour and butter to dissolve; cool.
Beat egg yolks and 1 whole egg.
Add vanilla and salt.
Mix well with the cooled mixture.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.
Pie will puff across top when done.

title: veal chops with lemon and pepper
directions: Arrange veal chops in shallow dish.
Sprinkle chops with lemon juice, black pepper and parsley.
Marinate 2 hours.
In nonstick skillet over high heat, cook veal chops 2 to 3 minutes on each side.
Remove to platter or plate.
Squeeze lemon wedge over each chop.

title: macaroni tuna supreme
directions: Prepare dinner as directed on package except using 1/2 cup milk.
Add soup, tuna and beans; mix lightly.
Spoon into 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with onions; continue baking 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: oven steak
directions: You will need aluminum foil.

title: broiled orange roughy(low cholesterol)
directions: One fillet of roughy, when halved, adequately serves 2 people. Arrange individual servings on a rack over a broiler pan.
Mix orange juice, margarine and wine and heat until margarine is melted and ingredients are well mixed.
Baste top side 3 to 4 times, waiting a few minutes between bastings to allow basting to soak in.
Sprinkle with paprika, then turn fillets over and repeat.
Place fillets under broiler; broil 3 to 3 1/2 minutes on each side.
Garnish with orange or lime slices and serve immediately.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: First soak raisins in hot water while getting other ingredients ready.
Mix first 8 ingredients with mixer, but must stir in the last 3 ingredients.
Roll in wax paper and refrigerate.
Slice and bake at 360° for about 7 to 10 minutes. Cookies will spread.
Watch baking and take out when they still appear raw.
(Dough will keep in refrigerator 30 to 45 days.)

title: cocktail meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into small meat balls. Combine small catsup and currant jelly.
Heat in pan until jelly is dissolved.
Pour over meat balls and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: golden garden dip
directions: Heat Velveeta and milk over low heat until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Chill.
Serve with assorted veggie dippers.

title: caramel sauce
directions: Melt all ingredients in pan.
Use sauce for Queen's Apples, ice cream sundaes or for Caramel Brownies (swirl into batter of brownies and bake as usual).

title: quick and easy apple cake
directions: Thaw bread.
Spread on greased cookie sheet.
Pour pie filling on top.
Combine flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle on top and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together the apples, water and sugar; let stand for 10 minutes.
Mix the dry ingredients together and add the apple mixture along with the pecans.
Blend well.
Pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mom's chicken deluxe
directions: Heat oil and butter in large skillet and brown chicken. Meanwhile, put remaining ingredients into jar.
Cover.
Press the liquefy button for 20 seconds. Pour slowly over browned chicken. Cover and simmer for 45 minutes, checking for seasoning as you cook.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all together and add 1 can drained shrimp and chopped onion.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Combine ingredients and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients; cool, then add remaining ingredients.
Stir while setting.

title: club punch
directions: Combine juice, whiskey and sugar to dissolve.
Chill.
Add tea and put mixture into a large punch bowl with a ring or block of ice.
Add soda and fruit.
Makes about 25 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Note:
Use as much squash, onion, green pepper and cracker crumbs as you like.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Combine sugar, dry mustard, salt, vinegar, onion and oil in blender.
Blend for 1 minute.
Add poppy seed and blend a few seconds more.
Refrigerate.

title: apple and cheese bake
directions: Grease a 9 x 12-inch casserole.
Drain 1 can of apples.
Place them and the 1 undrained can into casserole.
Melt in microwave the cheese, margarine and sugar.
Add the flour and mix.
Pour over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: gone all day stew
directions: Mix together soup, water and flour until smooth; combine with remaining ingredients in covered roasting pan.
Bake at 275° for 4 to 5 hours.
When ready to serve, adjust seasoning, if desired. Serve over noodles or with crunchy French bread.
Yields 8 servings.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Brown chicken in butter.
Add soup, water and seasonings; cover.
Simmer for 25 minutes.
Stir in rice; bring to a boil. Simmer for 5 minutes.

title: crispy cheese wafers
directions: Grate cheese and cream with oleo.
Sift dry ingredients and add cheese to mixture.
Fold in Rice Krispies.
Roll into balls and flatten into small wafers with fork.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 12 minutes at 350°.

title: soft chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine Crisco, sugars, vanilla and milk. Add egg.
Combine dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed ingredients.
Add chips and pecans.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.
Soft and chewy cookies.

title: chicken loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: creme de menthe cookies
directions: Make brownie mix and put in 9 x 13-inch glass pan and bake 12 to 15 minute at 350°.
Let cake cool.

title: texas sawdust pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together with hands (very thick).
Pour in pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm with Cool Whip.
Can reheat pie in microwave.

title: baked greek beef pattiesaunt elizabeth's recipe
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shape into 1/4 inch thick round patties (about 14 or 15 patties).Place in two 9 X 13 inch baking pans.
Do not use aluminum pans.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

Mix together ingredients for tomato sauce using 4 large cans of Hunt's tomato sauce, 2/3 cup of dry Burgundy wine, about 30 peppermint leaves finely chopped, 3 Tbsp. of olive oil and salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over patties in baking dish and bake for 35 minutes longer.
Serve patties and sauce over spaghetti or linguini, topped with grated Parmesan cheese. Serve with green salad, greek black olives and garlic bread.
"Bon Appetit"

title: strawberry cobbler
directions: Put 1 cup sugar in strawberries.
Pour melted butter in 2-quart dish.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk to make batter.
Pour over butter. Do not stir.
Put strawberries on top of batter.
Bake 1 hour or until brown.

title: brownie pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bring water to a boil.
Mix together brownie mix, water, oil and egg until well blended.
Pour into greased and floured 12-inch pizza pan.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Use any deep baking pan that holds in liquid. Grease the pan with some butter. Sprinkle the nuts into the pan and spread around. Mix the white sugar with cinnamon. Split the biscuits in half without cutting and lightly coat them with the mixture. Line the biscuits in rows on top of the nuts in the pan.

title: holiday fruit squares
directions: Gradually add sugar to margarine and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing on low speed.
Add flour and vanilla and mix well.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
With a knife, mark 20 squares and place one tablespoon of filling in each.
Bake at 350° until squares spring back when touched.
While warm, sift powdered sugar over and cool. Cut into squares.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: In mixer bowl, slightly beat eggs.
Add sugar, corn syrup, evaporated milk and vanilla.
Blend well.
Add pecans and pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake in a 400° oven for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for an additional 30 to 40 minutes or until filling is puffed in center and is well browned. Let pie cool before cutting.

title: hash brown casserole potatoes
directions: Put potatoes in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Sprinkle onions, salt and pepper.
Dollop 1/2 of butter on potatoes.
Heat on stove, soup, sour cream and Cheez Whiz; pour over potatoes.
Mix crushed flakes with other butter.
Sprinkle over potatoes.

title: chicken salad hawaiian
directions: Mix chicken and all ingredients except noodles.
Cover and chill.
Add noodles just before serving.

title: low-fat chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put dry ingredients in mixing bowl. Add liquid.
Mix until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Cream soft butter and 1/2 cup sugar.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together over creamed mixture.
Stir in milk and beat until smooth.
Pour into the bottom of a 2-inch deep, long or square baking dish.
Lay fruit over the batter.
Sprinkle 1/4 to 1/2 cup sugar over the fruit, then pour 1 cup juice over all.
Do not stir.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Batter will be thick and rise over fruit.

title: unbaked cookies
directions: Mix oatmeal, coconut, nuts, chocolate chips and raisins in mixing bowl.
Set aside.
In large saucepan, boil together sugar, margarine, milk and cocoa for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal mixture.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: broccoli crunch
directions: Cook broccoli until almost tender and place it in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Combine water chestnuts, cheese, soup and milk. Pour this over the broccoli.
Top with onion rings and bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Bake casserole before onion rings are put on top at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: borsch(beet soup)
directions: Put margarine into skillet.
Add onion and saute until golden in color.
Combine onion, potatoes, carrots and cabbage; add to beef stock.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add tomato sauce and beet juice.
Continue to simmer until vegetables are tender.
Add beets and lemon juice.
Season with salt and pepper.
Remove from heat before beets lose color.
Serve hot with 1 tablespoon of sour cream in each portion.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat and drain fat.
Add salt, tomato sauce, spaghetti sauce mix and tomatoes.
Simmer, uncovered.
Boil noodles 10 minutes and rinse in cold water.
Drain.
Alternate layers of meat mixture, noodles and cottage cheese.
Top with sauce and Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes until cheese is golden.

title: chicken supreme with toast cups
directions: Mix chicken, celery and onion pieces together and place in pressure cooker.
Add water to cover chicken halfway.
Pressure cook for approximately 30 minutes.
Reduce steam.
Take out chicken and debone.
Place chicken back in liquid.
Add soups and stir.
Thicken with cornstarch.
Let simmer about 30 minutes. Serve on toast cups.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: corn-shrimp soup
directions: Make a roux with oil and flour.
When roux is golden, add onions, bell peppers, garlic, celery and tomatoes.
Simmer about 10 minutes.
Add corn and mix all together well.
Add water, salt and pepper; simmer 1/2 hour.
If soup is too thick, add more water to desired consistency and bring to a boil.
Add green onions and turn off fire.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Stir together cocoa, salt, flour and baking powder.
Mix in separate bowl the vinegar and soda.
Cream shortening and sugar. Add eggs one at a time, food coloring and vanilla.
Add sifted ingredients and buttermilk; beat until smooth.
Add vinegar and soda.
Grease and flour 2 or 3 cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: creamy punch
directions: Pour thawed pink lemonade in large punch bowl. Add half bottle of ginger ale and stir. Add ice cream and more ginger ale. This will make the ice cream foam. "Pretty and Pink and ready to drink!"

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add frozen strawberries and mix gently until thawed.
Chill until slightly congealed.
Add pineapple, nuts and bananas.
Mix until well blended.
Pour half of the mixture in mold or dish.
Chill until firm. Spread sour cream or Cool Whip evenly, then remaining jello atop sour cream. Chill to congeal.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put in large casserole dish and add topping.
Cook at 350° until brown.

title: walnut broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions until just barely tender.
Drain well and place in oiled (vegetable) 2-quart casserole.
Melt 2 tablespoons of the margarine in a saucepan. Stir in the flour, cook briefly, and then add the milk.
Add the chicken broth and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Set aside.
Melt the remaining 4 tablespoons of margarine in the 2/3 cup of water.
Mix with the herb dressing and walnuts.
Pour the chicken broth sauce over the broccoli, sprinkle evenly with walnut mixture and bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until crusty on top.

title: lime delight salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Cool.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to gelatin.
Refrigerate until firm.
Serve with cold, sliced chicken or meat.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Season and brown pork chops.
Arrange potatoes in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix rest of ingredients except cheese; pour over potatoes.
Place pork chops over potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle with cheese the last 15 minutes of baking time.

title: santa's hermits
directions: Beat shortening and sugar together until creamy.
Beat in the eggs.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and spices.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients and drop by teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated moderate oven (350°) for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix all ingredients with hand mixer.
Shape into balls.
In double boiler, melt 1 cup chocolate morsels and 1/4 stick paraffin wax.
With toothpick, dip peanut butter balls into chocolate and cool on wax paper.

title: dill crackers
directions: Mix
all
ingredients well (except crackers).
Mix well and add
to
crackers.	Flavor	improves
after several hours. Put in oven
at 250° for 15 minutes; leave cool before you put into a closed container.

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown beef, bacon and onion.
Drain off excess fat.
Combine all ingredients.
Use juice from all beans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.
Stir in margarine.
Add Parmesan and eggs.
Form crust in 10-inch pie pan.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in with electric mixer; adding flour last. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until done.

title: tolerino
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain grease.
Cook noodles; set aside. Add remaining ingredients and noodles.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 20 minutes.
Uncover and add cheese.
Bake another 10 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: jiffy beans and franks
directions: Combine first five ingredients; spoon into a lightly greased, shallow, two-quart casserole.
Cover with heavy-duty plastic wrap. Fold back a small edge of wrap to allow steam to escape.

title: microwave carrot cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Add next 3 ingredients and mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.

title: no peek chicken bake
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle rice on bottom, then salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with dried onion.
In a bowl, mix mushroom and celery soups with water.
Pour over rice.
Place chicken on top of soup mixture.
Spoon onion soup on top of chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover.
Bake 2 1/2 hours at 350°.
No peeking.
When done, rice will be similar to dressing.

title: dump salad
directions: Mix together cottage cheese and dry jello; add drained pineapple.
Fold in the Cool Whip.
Store in refrigerator.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar together. Add beaten egg.
Sift the dry ingredients into the egg mixture. Stir the mixture.
Cover the mixing bowl with a plate and put in the refrigerator for 1 hour.
Preheat the oven to 400°.
Break off a bit of the cold dough and roll into a ball.
Roll each ball in the dish of cinnamon and sugar.
Bake for 10 to 20 minutes.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Mix flour, 1 cup sugar and milk together. Pour over butter.
Do not stir.
Mix fruit and 1 cup sugar, stir and pour into batter.
Bake about 30 minutes at 375°.

title: pumpkin dump cake dessert
directions: Combine eggs, pumpkin and milk in bowl; mix well. Add sugar, cinnamon, cloves, ginger and salt; mix well. Pour into a 9X13 baking dish. Sprinkle with cake mix; drizzle with margarine. Sprinkle walnuts over top. Bake at 325 degrees for 1 1/2 hours.

title: caviar dip
directions: Mix sour cream with chopped scallions and red caviar.
Blend and chill.
Garnish with chopped, fresh parsley.
Serve with water biscuits and chilled champagne.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Wash and drain lettuce; break into small pieces.
Layer in order as listed and put in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Will stay crisp 3-4 days.

title: frozen cookie crunch
directions: Combine first three ingredients.
Sprinkle one-third of cookie mixture in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spread half of ice cream on top.
Repeat procedure; sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Freeze 8 hours.
Yields 15 servings.
If desired, swirl chocolate sauce on top for a topping.

title: dirt dessert
directions: In large bowl mix butter and cream cheese.
Add powdered sugar, mix with cream cheese mixture.
Add milk, pudding and fold in Cool Whip.
Crush Oreo cookies (messy, use food processor or crush in plastic bag with rolling pin).
Layer Oreos and pudding in clean flowerpot, starting and ending with Oreos.
Garnish with silk flowers.

title: cranberry yogurt coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a large bowl, blend cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, yogurt and oil. Beat on high for 3 minutes.
Scrape bowl often.
Spread 2/3 of batter in pan.
Spoon cranberry sauce over batter.
Spoon remaining batter over sauce.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add salt and sugar.
Beat until stiff.
Fold in butterscotch or chocolate bits and nuts.
Drop on ungreased pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Turn off heat and put cookies in oven.
Leave in for 4 hours or overnight.

title: blend of the bayou
directions: Soften cream cheese and oleo. Mix some grated cheese with all other ingredients and pour in baking dish. Top with grated Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix well and put in bowl or pan.
Chill and serve.

title: roll out sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large bowl, cream margarine and sugar.
While mixing, put in eggs and vanilla.
Add baking powder and flour, a little at a time.
Dough will be stiff.
Do not chill dough.
Roll out to 1/8-inch thick and cut out.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet; bake at 400° for 6 to 7 minutes.
Decorate as desired.

title: infamous crab dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl combine all ingredients. Spoon into small ovenproof baking dish.
Bake 15 minutes or until heated through.
Serve warm with crackers or chips.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and salt to taste. Best to chill over night.

title: cabbage rolls(also known as "polish pigeons")
directions: Combine ground beef, rice, onion, egg, salt and pepper.
Boil cabbage leaves until limp.
Separate, trim and cool.
Combine all but tomato soup and vinegar.
Divide mixture among cabbage leaves. Roll together and secure each with toothpicks.
Mix tomato soup with (extra leaves cover the filled ones before tomato soup) 1 can water and 1 teaspoon vinegar.
Pour over cabbage rolls.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or cook in skillet over very low heat for 45 minutes.
Stir often spooning sauce over rolls.

title: layered cream cheese strawberry dessert
directions: Combine crackers and butter and press into bottom of 8-inch square pan. Bake at 375° for 8 minutes. Cool. Beat cream cheese with sugar and 2 tablespoons milk in bowl until smooth. Spread evenly in crumb-lined pan. Arrange strawberries on cream cheese mixture. Prepare whipped topping mix. Prepare pudding mix with 1 1/2 cups milk. Fold in 1/2 cup of whipped topping. Spoon over strawberries and chill until set, about 2 hours. Garnish with remaining whipped topping and additional strawberries. Cut into squares.

title: honey butter
directions: Put 2 sticks oleo or butter in mixing bowl. Add 1 cup honey. Mix with beater 1/2 minute. Put in jars.

title: chocolate surprise cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Butter and flour 12-cup Bundt pan.
In small bowl, beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat until blended; set aside.
Prepare cake mix according to label.
Fold in chocolate morsels.
Pour chocolate batter into prepared pan.
Evenly cover with cream cheese mix. Bake until wooden pick comes out clean (45 to 55 minutes).
Cool in pan on rack 25 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool completely. Dust with confectioners sugar.
Serve with whipped cream and raspberries, if desired.
Serves 12.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Soak candied fruit and raisins in brandy for 48 hours.
With a fork, beat eggs and sugar.
Blend in butter, soda, spices and vanilla.
Gently stir in flour, nuts and brandied fruit with remaining liquid.
Drop by rounded teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes or until lightly brown. Makes about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: famous pear pie(better than apple)
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt until mixture is about the size of peas.
Add milk and form into ball.
Divide dough and roll out for two crusts.

title: crustless quiche
directions: Cook spinach and sausage as usual, separately. Drain all grease from sausage. Drain all water from spinach. Combine eggs and milk; blend until well mixed. Place spinach and sausage in a 9 inch pyrex dish and top with grated cheddar cheese. Pour egg mixture over sausage and cheddar cheese. Shake on Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 35-40 minutes or until eggs do not run when cut.

title: pecan butter brittle
directions: Microwave sugar, syrup and butter for 3 minutes on High.
Stir in nuts; mix well.
Microwave on High 7 or 8 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes.
Add soda; quickly stir and pour onto greased surface.
Cool; break into pieces.
Store in airtight container. Delicious.

title: holiday squares
directions: Beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Gradually add flour; mix well.
Add vanilla.
Put batter on greased cookie sheet; score and put pie filling in center of each square.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes. Cut squares and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: gingerbread boys and girls
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add the egg; beat well.
Sift together all the dry ingredients.
Add alternately to the creamed mixture with the milk.
If necessary, add more flour to make a soft dough that can be rolled out.
Chill several hours.
Roll a portion at a time on floured board.
Cut with miniature gingerbread boy and girl cutters.
Place on lightly greased sheet and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Watch closely.
Decorate as desired.

title: veal scaloppine
directions: Slice clean veal tenders in 2 x 3-inch pieces.
Dip in flour, salt, pepper and garlic powder, coating each piece.
Brown in oil and remove from pan.
Brown together garlic slices, onions and green pepper.
Heat until tender.
Add mushrooms and heat.
Add browned veal and tomatoes.
Season to taste and cook, covered, on low heat, approximately 1 hour.
Serve with rice or pasta.

title: chicken-broccoli skillet
directions: Thaw the frozen broccoli.
Season chicken strips with salt and pepper.
Cook chicken and chopped onion quickly in the hot diet margarine until chicken is just done.
Stir in the thawed broccoli, lemon juice, 3/4 teaspoon salt, thyme and 1/8 teaspoon pepper. Cook, covered, 6 minutes.
Add tomato wedges.
Cook, covered, 3 to 4 minutes more.
Makes 4 servings.
One serving (1 1/4 cups) equals 2 1/2 lean meat exchanges, 2 vegetable exchanges and 1/2 fat exchange.

title: meatballs in dijon sauce
directions: Mix
and
shape
into
1/4-inch meatballs.
Place on nonsticking rack and bake, uncovered, at 400° until done light and brown, 20 to 25 minutes.
Prepare Dijon Sauce as follows:

title: chili bean soup
directions: Brown ground beef in large saucepan; saute onions with beef. Add all other ingredients; heat well.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and top with whipped cream.

title: alabama biscuits
directions: Mix yeast and 1/2 cup of warm water.
Mix dry milk and 1 1/2 cups of water.
Pour these 2 mixtures together and set aside.
Mix the dry ingredients and add oil, yeast and milk mixture together. Mix well.
Pour onto a lightly floured surface.
Knead 10 minutes. Roll out and cut into biscuits.
Place on greased cookie sheet and let rise 45 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 20 minutes.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Cook until boiling hot.
Add peaches and let cook slowly until peaches are done.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix together. Bake in oven at 325° until bubbly. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese on top and bake until brown. Remove from oven; cool and serve.

title: ruby red raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve raspberry jello in one cup boiling water.
Add raspberries and stir until berries are thawed and separated.
Pour into a 13X9X2-inch pan.
Chill until set.
Carefully spread with sour cream; chill.
Dissolve cherry jello in remaining cup of boiling water.
Add pineapple and cranberry sauce.
Mix well. Allow to thicken slightly.
Carefully spoon over sour cream mixture.
Chill, cut into squares and serve.
If wanted, use Sugar-free Jello, Fat-free sour cream. 12-16 servings.

title: dressing
directions: Cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix the first 5 ingredients in a large bowl, then sift in the flour and baking powder.
Stir lightly. Mixture will be lumpy.
Spoon into lightly greased muffin tins and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli bisque
directions: Place broccoli in a large saucepan.
Add broth, onion, butter or margarine, salt, curry powder and pepper.
Bring to boiling. Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 8 to 12 minutes, or until just tender.
Place half the broccoli and broth mixture at a time in blender container.
Cover and blend.
Repeat with remaining broccoli mixture.
Stir in lime juice.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Top with lemon slice, spoonful of sour cream and sprinkling of chives.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix 1/3 cup flour with blueberries; set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Add blueberries.
Spoon into muffin pans lined with paper muffin holders.
Bake 15 minutes at 450°.
Real butter is preferred.

title: sugar-free chinese chews
directions: Sift together dry ingredients and add dates and nuts.
Spread in well-greased 8-inch square pan and bake for 40 minutes at 350°. Score into 1-inch squares while warm.

title: festive fruit punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in a punch bowl.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Place filling in deep dish.
Roll out pie dough.
Spread on top and bake at 350°.

title: carrot souffl
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth and blended.
Pour into pyrex dish and bake at 350 degrees about 1 hour to 1 hour 15 minutes.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on top after cooking.

title: chipped beef cheese ball
directions: Mix and shape.
Serve with wheat crackers.

title: sugarless doughnuts
directions: Mix all ingredients except flour.
Mix well.
Add flour.
Fry in deep fat.

title: microwave hamburgers
directions: Mix hamburger and onion together; form into patties.
Throw in the microwave; cook until you are ready to eat.

title: ham, potato and onion casserole
directions: Melt butter. Blend in flour and add milk, stirring constantly. Cook mixture until thick, boiling about 3 minutes. Add seasonings and grated cheese and cook slowly until cheese melts. Add cooked ham, potatoes and onions.
Pour mixture into a greased casserole. Sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until the crumbs are lightly browned. Serves 8 to 10.

title: sausage and feta cheese casserole(serves 8)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown sausage, onion and garlic in skillet until sausage is brown and onion is transparent.
Add salt, pepper, rosemary and basil.
Drain sausage on paper towels.
Mix spinach and Feta cheese.
Add beaten eggs and sausage mixture. Stir.

Spray 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish with vegetable cooking spray. Place 6 sheets of fillo dough, spraying each sheet lightly with cooking spray on bottom of dish (sheets may be cut or simply bunched up to fit dish).
Spoon half of spinach/sausage mixture onto filo dough.
Place 6 more sheets of fillo dough on top of spinach/sausage mixture.
Again lightly spraying each sheet with cooking spray.
Spoon remainder of spinach/sausage mixture onto second layer of dough.
Top with 12 sheets of fillo dough, spraying each sheet lightly with cooking spray, except last 2 sheets, which should be brushed lightly with melted margarine.
Cook in center of oven at 350° for 35 minutes, until golden brown.
Let stand for 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: peanut butter crispy treats
directions: Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In large saucepan over low heat, stir together corn syrup, sugar and peanut butter, stirring constantly.
Bring to boil and boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add cereal; toss to coat well.
Press into prepared pan. Cool.
Cut into 1 x 3-inch bars.

title: rock candy
directions: Heat oven to 310°.
Remove from stove.
Add 1 teaspoon flavoring and food coloring.
Pour into greased cookie sheet.
Let harden.
Break into pieces.
Add powdered sugar, sprinkled on top.

title: fantasy cake
directions: Cook pineapple and sugar 2 to 3 minutes.
Poke holes in cake. Spread pineapple on cake while still warm.
Add cream cheese to prepared instant pudding.
Stir well.
Spread on cake.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Cream
sugar
and
butter;
add eggs, salt and vanilla. Beat until
fluffy.
Spoon
into two baked pie shells.
Spread evenly and
chill.
Whip cream until stiff and fold in pineapple and nuts.
Spoon
over top of first mixture.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: mad hatter meat balls
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add onion and green pepper.
Stir in chicken and rice soup, tomato soup and water.
Heat on low.

title: quick rolls
directions: Melt margarine; dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix all ingredients except flour.
Gradually fold in flour.
Bake in muffin pans at 350°.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat well and warm up (hot).
Pour in fresh pie crust straight side up.
Cook in oven at 325° to 350° for 30 minutes.
(Milk should not boil.)

title: baked fried pies
directions: Will keep for 3 weeks in refrigerator.

title: baked chicken reuben
directions: Mix all ingredients together, leaving the addition of the chicken to the last.
Each recipe should feed 4 to 6 persons.

title: auntie sue apples
directions: Peel, quarter and core apples.
Put in baking dish.
Mix sugar and spices.
Sprinkle sugar mixture over apples and the nuts.
Dot with margarine, pour water in bottom of pan.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, until tender.
Baste occasionally.

title: rice with mushrooms and artichokes
directions: In a medium saucepan combine broth and 1/3 cup water.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in the rice.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender, about 20 minutes.
While rice is cooking, in a medium skillet, heat the oil over medium-high heat.
Add mushrooms and red pepper; cook until tender, stirring occasionally, 5 to 6 minutes.
Stir in artichokes, parsley, thyme, cooked rice and salt and pepper to taste.
Heat through, about 3 minutes.
Spoon into a serving dish and serve hot.

title: boston cream pie
directions: Beat 3 eggs lightly with 1 cup sugar.
Add water, 1 1/2 cups flour, baking powder and vanilla and bake in quick oven until brown.
Split open to make 2 layers and fill with a mixture of 2 eggs, 1 cup sugar, 1/2 cup flour and milk.
Cook all together over slow heat, stirring constantly, in double boiler until thickened. Add butter.
Cool before spreading.
Bananas, coconut or crushed pineapple may be added to filling.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer vegetables in dish.
Mix together dressing, mayonnaise and bacon.
Pour over vegetables.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Toss just before serving.
Salad is better made 24 hours before serving.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to directions.
Add all ingredients in large bowl and mix.
More Italian seasoning or Italian dressing can be added to taste.
Can sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese, if desired.

title: jello pudding dirt cups
directions: You will also need 8 to 10 plastic cups.
Pour milk into large bowl.
Add Jell-O pudding mix; beat until well blended.
Let sit for 5 minutes.
Stir in Cool Whip and 1/2 cookies.
Place 1 tablespoon cookies into the cups.
Fill cups 3/4 full with pudding mixture.
Top with remaining cookies.
Refrigerate 1 hour. Decorate with gummy worms, frog, candy flowers or chopped nuts.

title: chicken & penne pasta
directions: Broiled or grill chicken strips with butter and Cavender's Greek spice and set aside; keep warm.
Cook the asparagus in a large pot of boiling, salted water until just tender (3-4 minutes). Remove and rinse under cold water.
Cut on the diagonal into 1 1/2 inch pieces and set aside.
Add the pasta to the boiling water and cook 10-12 minutes (or according to package directions).
While the pasta is cooking, heat half the olive oil in a large skillet or wok over medium heat.
Add the onions and cook until soft, stirring, about 3 minutes.
Add the mushrooms and cook until slightly browned, about 5 minutes.
Add garlic (optional) and cook for 1 minute.
Then add the reserved asparagus, the spinach, tomato and sun-dried tomato; season with Cavender's, salt and pepper (to taste).

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350° or can be made in a crock-pot.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: heavenly hash cake
directions: Melt cocoa and butter together.
Beat eggs and sugar.
Then add cocoa mixture.
Mix in vanilla and flour.
Fold in pecans. Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 20 minutes.
Take cake immediately from the oven and cover the top of the cake with the marshmallows. Then pour the icing over the marshmallows.

title: pecan or walnut tarts
directions: Mix together well.
Put pastry in small tins.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix together and pour into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Cover with bacon strips and bake at 375° until done.

title: layered dip for nacho chips
directions: Using an 8 x 10-inch serving dish, layer all ingredients in exact order given.
Make sure everyone knows to dig deep.

title: tang pie
directions: Mix first five ingredients well.
Pour into 2 graham cracker shells.
Sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs.

title: cream chicken over toast
directions: Boil chicken; debone.
In large skillet, melt butter on low heat.
Add flour, stirring constantly until brown.
Slowly, but continuously, add milk.
Stir constantly until gravy begins to thicken.
Combine chicken with gravy.
Place 2 to 3 large spoonfuls of mixture on toast.
Sprinkle with hard-boiled eggs. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix will be dry but do not add any liquids. Mix well all ingredients. Shape into bite size balls. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: coconut-pecan filling and frosting
directions: Combine milk, sugar, well beaten egg yolks, butter or margarine and vanilla in a double boiler.
Cook over medium heat in double boiler, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens, about 12 minutes.
May have to cook a little longer than 12 minutes in order for mixture to thicken.
Remove from heat; add coconut and pecans.
Beat until cool and of spreading consistency. Makes enough frosting to cover tops of 3 layers of German chocolate cake.

title: peanut crinkles
directions: Cream the oleo and peanut butter.
Gradually add brown and white sugars.
Gradually add flour.
Blend well. Drop by tablespoon on well-greased cookie sheet.
Press down each cookie with a fork.
Press a second time at right angle to first press. Bake at 350°.
Do not overbake.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream together the sugar and Crisco shortening.
Add the eggs, beating after each one, the flour, soda, salt, walnut flavoring, black walnut meats and milk. Bake in tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: chewy cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased pan for 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.
Cut into squares.

title: any flavor punch
directions: *If you use strawberry Kool-Aid add fresh or frozen strawberries for a more elegant punch.

title: rotel chili
directions: Place meat into a large saucepan and cook to a light gray color (grease may be drained).
Add chopped onion, chili powder, cumin, garlic, oregano and salt.
Stir thoroughly and heat for 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes and green chilies, whole tomatoes and water.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and cover.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Combine rice, soup, mustard, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, onion and pepper.
Add shrimp and grated cheese.
Put in large casserole dish and bake at 350°.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Melt butter and add to Stove Top stuffing.
Put 2/3 in bottom of greased casserole dish.
Set the other 1/3 aside.

title: tangy stuffed pepper salad
directions: In a bowl combine shredded cabbage, cooked meat, carrot, radish and cucumber.
Combine next 7 ingredients; mix well.
