Pour over vegetable mixture, tossing to coat.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour.
Remove tops from green peppers.
Cut peppers in half lengthwise and remove seeds.
Spoon vegetable mixture into pepper cups.
Makes 4 servings.

title: golden punch
directions: Mix well, adding enough water to make one gallon.

title: monkey bread
directions: Using a Bundt pan, spray generously with Pam. Sprinkle 1/3 of the pecans in bottom of pan. Pinch apart 1/3 of the biscuits, dropping them around the pan. Sprinkle cinnamon and sugar over top of biscuits. Repeat with pecans, biscuits, cinnamon and sugar. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done. Dump bread onto a serving tray and top with Glaze.

title: jello salad
directions: Cook crushed pineapple in saucepan.
Bring to boil and boil 5 minutes.
Stir in 1/2 cup sugar into boiling pineapple.
Keep stirring after boiling 5 minutes.
Add jello (any flavor).
Let pineapple with sugar and jello cool.
Take condensed milk and cream cheese and beat with electric mixer until real fluffy or until large bowl is full, then stir in pineapple.
Put into pan or large dish and chill in refrigerator for 2 hours or longer or leave overnight.

title: 1, 2, 3...fun!
directions: Mix water, Kool-Aid and sugar.
Pour onto crushed ice.
Spoon eat.

title: insalata di fagiolini(string bean salad)
directions: Cut off tips of beans.
Wash thoroughly.
Place in rapidly boiling salted water.
Cook about 20 minutes or until tender. Drain.
Cut in half.
Place in wooden salad bowl.
Add oil, vinegar, garlic, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix thoroughly.
May be served warm; otherwise, chill in refrigerator 15 minutes. Serves 6.

title: soybean loaf
directions: Soak soybeans all night.
Simmer until tender. Grind or mash. Form into loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: seafood newburg
directions: Saute meat in butter or margarine in large skillet.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup flour.
Slowly add cream, stirring constantly, on low heat.
When this comes to simmer, add egg yolks, mixing thoroughly. Never boil!
Heat through until warm.
Add wine and heat through. Sprinkle with cayenne pepper.
Serve over toast.

title: fabulous fudge
directions: Mix sugar, butter, marshmallows, salt and condensed milk in heavy 3-quart saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until mixture boils and is bubbly all over top.
Boil and stir over medium heat for 5 more minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and chocolate chips until melted.
Spread in buttered 8 or 9-inch square pan. Press nut halves on top if desired.

title: chicken bake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Place in a 2-quart greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheesy-pop bread
directions: Saute onion until done.
Add butter and mustard.
Place cheese between bread slices.
Spread with some of sauce.
Spread rest of sauce over bread.
Sprinkle poppy seed over top.
Bake at 275° about 45 minutes or until done.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Fold in Cool Whip and put in the 2 graham crusts.
Refrigerate.

title: tender baked ham
directions: Take oven grill pan and one very long sheet of wide aluminum foil.
You will make a total enclosure for ham with foil meeting on top.
Place ham in center of pan on foil, bend sides of foil up to hold liquid.
Slowly pour Coke over ham.
Seal up ham with foil.
Bake in oven at 325° for 3 hours for small ham, 4 hours for medium ham and 5 hours for large ham.
Slice and enjoy.

title: sweet potato pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In food processor or blender, puree sweet potatoes with 3 tablespoons melted butter until smooth.
Add cream, brown sugar, eggs, vanilla extract, pumpkin pie spice and brandy.
Process until mixture is well combined.
Spoon evenly into unbaked pie crust.
Bake 20 minutes until filling is almost set.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together.
Sprinkle on top of potato mixture; bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: lemon chess bars
directions: Combine cake mix, 1 egg and melted butter.
Pat into 13 x 9 x 2-inch lightly greased baking pan.
Blend cream cheese, 3 eggs and confectioners sugar.
Pour over unbaked cake layer.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool; cut into squares.
These cookies brown quickly, therefore, check frequently to avoid burning.

title: tropical carrots
directions: Combine carrots and water in a small saucepan; cover and cook until carrots are crisp and tender.
Combine pineapple, cornstarch and ginger in a small bowl, mix well.
Add pineapple mix to carrots; cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thickened. Yields 4 servings, about 59 calories per serving.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until done.
Drain thoroughly. Add remaining ingredients, except cheese. While squash is still hot, whip together.
Place in greased casserole dish. Cover with cheese. Cover to bake. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: best 5 minute fudge
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat and add chocolate chips.
Stir until melted.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Do not beat. Pour into greased pan.
Chill; cut into squares.
For thick squares, put in a 9 x 7-inch pan, thin squares in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with skin on.
Cool, peel and dice.
Mix everything together.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: sausage gravy
directions: Crumble sausage and fry (not too brown); set aside for later. In large skillet, mix flour with sausage drippings (judge amount for your personal use), stirring until lightly brown.
Pour in milk and boil; when gravy is almost done, add the crumbled sausage and continue to boil, stirring all the time the gravy is boiling.
Keep adding milk so it doesn't get too thick.

title: magic cookies
directions: Cream the Crisco and sugar, then add eggs, vanilla and the rest of the ingredients gradually.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
No flour in recipe.
You can store part of recipe in refrigerator for later.

title: overnight pineapple salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cherries; refrigerate overnight.
Just before serving, add the cherries and serve. Serves 12.

title: daiquiri
directions: Blend until smooth.
Garnish with orange slice.

title: pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grasse bottom only of loaf pan.
Beat all ingredients in a large mixer bowl on low speed, scraping bowl constantly for 30 seconds.
Beat on medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally for 4 minutes. Spread in pan.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, about 55 minutes.

title: rice krispies potato casserole
directions: Mix hash browns, sour cream, chicken soup, onion and cheese. Top with the Rice Krispies.
Melt the stick of butter and pour over the Rice Krispies.
Bake in preheated oven for 1 hour.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Place all ingredients into a large mixing bowl and beat on high speed until well blended.
Pour into well-greased tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes a large cake.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Bring last 5 ingredients to a boil and pour over vegetables. Let set overnight.
Keeps 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: strawberry-lime punch
directions: Place juices and sugar in pitcher and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add thawed strawberries.
Mix well until combined. Slowly add lemon-lime soda.
Refrigerate until ready to serve. Garnish glasses with fresh fruit slices;
Yields 16 servings.

title: fiesta chili dip
directions: Put meat and next eight ingredients in a large heavy iron or aluminum pot.
Stir until meat is no longer pink.
Add tomato sauce and hot water.
Cover the pot and simmer for approximately 3 hours.
Cool and place in the refrigerator overnight.
The next day, remove the grease from the top of the mixture and reheat. Add sliced hot tamales and cook until disintegrated.
Add cheese, reserving 2 cups, and stir until cheese has melted.
Put chili in two oblong flat baking dishes.
Sprinkle the remaining cheese on top and melt the cheese in the oven.
Remove from the oven and sprinkle with chopped green onions.
Serve with tostadas or chips. Serves 50.
Freezes well.

title: grilled ham slices
directions: Mix all ingredients and marinate ham slices for 2 hours at room
temperature.	Bake
in
12-inch
Dutch
oven	for 30 minutes.

title: american oriental chicken
directions: Mix dry ingredients; roll chicken strips in dry ingredients; put in oil. Cook until golden brown. Add rest of ingredients and cook for 30 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together in mixing bowl except Cheddar cheese.
Blend together until smooth.
Pour into a pie plate. Spread shredded cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Great with tortilla chips or crackers.

title: southern spicy gingerbread
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar, molasses and oil.
Sift in the dry ingredients last. Add boiling water. Pour into greased loaf pans or cupcake tins. Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes for loaf or about 20 to 25 minutes for cupcakes.

title: hamburger hash brown hot dish
directions: Butter 9x13 pan and cover bottom with hash browns.
Brown ground beef and onion, drain and put on top of hash browns.
Salt and pepper.
Sprinkle on vegetables.
Mix cream of mushroom soup with one cup milk and pour over vegetable.
Place cheese slices on top. and cover pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 50 minutes.
Uncover and top with fried onions and heat 10 more minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pork chops with golden apple dressing
directions: Saute celery, carrot and onion in butter in skillet until tender, but not brown.
Stir in sage, dash of salt, pepper and cinnamon.
In large bowl, combine bread cubes, apples, walnuts, raisins and vegetable mixture.
Add just enough chicken broth to moisten.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Saute onion and pepper in 1 stick of butter. Melt Velveeta cheese with Ro-Tel chopped tomatoes and hot chilies and mushroom soup. Mix this mixture with pepper and onions. Cook and drain spaghetti. Mix all together with cut up chicken. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: easy oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheet.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Drain
tuna.
Saute
onion in 2 teaspoons of margarine. Add bell
pepper
and
drained	tuna.
Mix cheese, evaporated milk, salt, pepper and remaining margarine.
Cook at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: coconut cake icing
directions: Mix and cook over very low heat until mixture begins to thicken. Remove from heat and add coconut.
Cool until thick enough to spread.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Drain tomatoes, reserving juice.
Measure 1/2 cup juice, adding water, if necessary.
Combine beef, salt, pepper, bread crumbs, onion, garlic and tomato juice.
Press into pie pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Drain off fat.
Cut up tomatoes and place in beef pie crust.
Sprinkle with parsley, oregano and cheese. Bake 15 minutes more.

title: cookie cutter sandwiches
directions: Wash hands.
Use cookie cutters to cut out bread for sandwiches.
Make sandwich with whatever you like.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Combine milk, biscuit mix, margarine, salt and eggs in a blender; mix well.
Turn into ungreased Pyrex dish.
Add meat, poking into batter.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until top is golden, about 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Drain liquid off beans.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over beans.
Let stand overnight.
Refrigerate.

title: apple crisp
directions: Generously butter spring-form pan.
Sprinkle with lots of sugar all around.
Cut crusts from loaf of French bread and slice. Butter each slice.
Use fresh raspberries with lots of sugar or sugared frozen berries.

title: sun-dried tomato spread
directions: To rehydrate tomatoes, place tomatoes in a steamer about 45 minutes.
Place steamed tomatoes in a 2-cup container with tight fitting lid.
Add all remaining ingredients except cream cheese and crackers.
Cover container.
Shake to blend ingredients. Refrigerate 2 days.

title: *rice pudding
directions: Wash rice, leaving a little water on it.
Place in saucepan. Add milk and bring to a boil.
Lower heat. Add sugar and continue on low heat, stirring occasionally. Add beaten eggs when rice is almost cooked. Take off heat. Add vanilla. Pour into casserole. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
(Rice takes 20 minutes to cook.)

title: holiday lemon-pecan cake
directions: Beat butter with sugar, adding 1 cup sugar at a time.
Add egg yolks 1 at a time, beating after each addition.
Add lemon extract.
Add flour, glazed fruits and pecans.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into lined and well-greased tube or loaf pans.
Bake at 275° for 2 hours in tube or 1 hour and 15 minutes in loaf pans.

title: lobster newburg
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on high; stir occasionally until soup is melted.
Cover and cook on low for 4 to 6 hours.
Serve over hot rice or in puff pastry shells.

title: cheddar hash brown bake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except hash browns, together.
Add hash browns last.
Butter 9 x 13-inch dish.
Put in hash browns and mix.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup corn flake crumbs on top. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in 2 tablespoons butter and remove from pan.
Cut meat into strips 2 1/2 inches long and 3/4 inch wide.
Melt additional 2 tablespoons butter in pan.
Toss strips in flour, coating thoroughly.
Brown meat in butter.
Add salt and bouillon.
Simmer, stirring occasionally until meat is tender, about 1 1/4 hours.
Add mushrooms and onion and sour cream.
Heat. Serve over noodles or rice.

title: microwave one bowl brownies
directions: Microwave chocolate and margarine or butter in a large microwavable bowl at High for 2 minutes or until the margarine is melted.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.

title: party punch
directions: Blend pineapple and cherries in blender.
Set aside.
Mix sugar and water; bring to a boil to make syrup.
Let cool.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cut carrots into chunks.
Cook until tender.
Cut onion and bell pepper in slices.
Place into bowl.
Pour cooked carrots into bowl with onions and peppers.
In saucepan, heat the other ingredients until very hot.
Do not bring to boil.
Pour over carrots, onions and peppers.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut green peppers in half, lengthwise.
Remove seeds; set aside.
Mix beef, tomato sauce, rice, egg, oregano, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Spoon into pepper halves.
Place on roasting rack.
Cover loosely with waxed paper.
Microwave at High (100%) until green peppers are tender, 12 to 16 minutes.
Top each with ketchup or spaghetti sauce during last 2 minutes.

title: quick chili
directions: Brown onion and meat; drain.
Add tomato sauce and spices and simmer 15 minutes.
Add kidney beans and cook additional 7 to 10 minutes.
Serve
over rice or noodles.

title: pepperoni bites
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Stir in cheeses and pepperoni.
Put into a 9 x 13 greased pan.
Bake at 400 degrees for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool and cut into 1 inch cubes.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix together and let stand an hour.
Meanwhile, take 2 cups sugar, 1 cup vinegar and 3 tablespoons celery seed and bring to boil.
Pour over first ingredients.
Put in jars and keep in refrigerator.
These are delicious.

title: new england blueberry muffins
directions: Combine sugar, butter, eggs and milk; beat well.
Blend flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to sugar mixture and mix until blended.
Fold in blueberries.
Spoon into 12 well-greased muffin cups.
Fill almost to the top of cup.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hawaiian sandwich
directions: Drain pineapple.
Combine 1 tablespoon pineapple juice with mayo, mustard, onion and pepper.
Spread on bread.
Layer ham, cheese, pineapple and lettuce on bread.
Cut sandwiches in half.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Combine butter and milk in pan; stir until warm.
Mix yeast, water and 2 teaspoons sugar in bowl.
Beat eggs and add to milk and butter.
Combine with yeast and add 1/2 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons salt.
Add flour, about 8 1/2 cups.
Let mixture set for 15 minutes.
Mix well.
Add more flour until smooth.
Let rise until double in size.
Work down and let rise again.
Divide into egg size portions and form around small link sausage.
Let rise again.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.

title: oatmeal caramel chewies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine oats, flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in margarine.
Mix well.
Reserve 1 cup.
Press remaining mixture onto bottom of pan. Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Top with nuts and chocolate chips.
Mix caramel topping and 1/4 cup flour until smooth.
Drizzle over chocolate pieces to within 1/2-inch of pan edge.
Sprinkle with reserved mixture.
Bake 18 to 22 minutes. Cool and chill until set.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cool Whip and Marshmallow Creme can be added to your own taste.
The Cool Whip makes the mixture less stiff.

title: no bake orange balls
directions: Position knife blade in food processor.
Add half of vanilla wafers.
Process until fine crumbs.
Remove crumbs; set aside. Repeat procedure with remaining wafers; remove crumbs and set aside.
Add pecans to food processor bowl; process until ground. Combine crumbs, ground pecans, sugar, orange juice and butter in a large bowl; stir until blended.
Divide mixture in half.
Cover 1 portion with plastic and set aside.

title: chocolate hershey pound cake
directions: Mix sugar, margarine
and
Crisco.
Add
eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Sift
flour, baking powder and salt.
Add milk a little at
a time.
Add syrup and vanilla.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325°.

title: jam dandy coffee cake
directions: Turn oven to 375°.
Pop all these things into a bowl at once. Beat 50 quick strokes with a fork.
Pour into a greased 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle top with 1/4 cup brown sugar (packed) and 1/4 cup chopped nuts.
Then dot with 2/3 cup jam (cherry is great).
Bake 25 to 30 minutes (test with a wooden pick).
Serve it warm to as many as 9.

title: reuben dip
directions: Heat all ingredients in a small saucepan over low heat.
Thin with milk if necessary.
Serve with rye snack sticks.
Yield:
1 1/2 cups.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Sift dry ingredients; add to shortening, sugar and eggs.
Mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Roll in wax paper; leave in refrigerator overnight.
Slice very thin.
Bake in a 350° oven until lightly browned.
Store in jar or tin.
Roll may be kept in refrigerator for several days and cookies baked at different times.

title: cream corn casserole
directions: Mix together in 2 quart baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set around edges.
Great for potluck!

title: vegetable medley
directions: Cut onions and green peppers into thin strips.
Saute with mushrooms in a small amount of margarine.
Combine broccoli and beans; cook until done.
Drain and toss with onions and peppers. Season to taste.

title: fruit salad
directions: Slice bananas.
Pour pineapple juice over bananas.
Slice pineapple into small tidbits.
Add fruit cocktail that has drained.
Add vanilla instant pudding and stir until dissolved. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix cheese and sour cream together.
Add lemon juice and seasonings.
Mix until creamy.
Then add shrimp and chill.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Mix all the ingredients and refrigerate overnight. When ready to cook, add salt to taste, Tabasco sauce to taste, oregano and 1/2 teaspoon mustard. Put in 9 x 11 glass dish and cook until firm (about 30 to 40 minutes) at 350°. Do not grease pan.

title: pickled beets
directions: Cook beets; cool and peel.
Mix syrup; let come to a boil. Drop sliced beets in, let simmer for 15 minutes.
Pack in jars and seal.
This syrup is good to put over fresh beets and serve right away.

title: do ahead party potatoes
directions: Saute onions in butter until transparent. Stir in flour to make a roux. Add hot chicken broth gradually and stir for 3 minutes. When slightly thickened, transfer to casserole dish. Mix soft bread crumbs with cheeses and sprinkle on top of onions. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until lightly browned and bubbly.

title: cousin linda's sloppy joes
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Cook hamburger and drain.
Add all ingredients.
Cover and simmer.

title: cucumber shrimp soup with dill cream
directions: Melt the butter in a large soup pot over high heat and then add the onions, garlic, dill, salt and pepper and saut, stirring, for about 2 minutes.
Add the shrimp and saut for 2 minutes.
Stir in the cucumbers and saut for 1 minute.

title: jumbles cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In bowl, beat sugars and butter until light and fluffy.
Add egg.
Combine flour and baking soda; blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in baking bits and nuts; mix.
Drop by tablespoonfuls, about 2 inches apart, onto a greased cookie sheet. Bake for 13 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 32 cookies.
May be made smaller, if you like.

title: beef macaroni skillet
directions: In skillet over medium high heat cook beef and onions until beef is browned and onions are tender, stirring to separate meat. Spoon off fat.
Stir in soup, water, Worcestershire sauce and cheese.
Add macaroni.
Reduce heat to low.
Heat through stirring occasionally.
Top with additional cheese if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: microwave-toasted cheese sandwiches
directions: Put 2 slices of bread into toaster.
Pull knob down.
When it pops up, put the bread on a plate.
Put 1 slice of cheese between the bread.
This makes the sandwich.
Then put it in the microwave for 15 seconds to melt the cheese.
It's delicious!

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Cut artichoke hearts into very small pieces. Mix with other ingredients.
Pour into shallow baking dish of choice.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Serve with French bread, sliced thin, or a variety of crackers.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix in order given. Drop by tablespoon onto cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes. Makes 12 dozen.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix eggs, then flour that has the other dry ingredients added. Fold in nuts and apples.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° about 60 minutes.

title: greek spinach pie
directions: In a large bowl, cover spinach with boiling water.
Let stand 5 minutes, stirring once.
Drain on paper towels.
Heat oven to 400°. Unroll 1 can of dough into 2 long rectangles; place in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press over bottom and up 1/2-inch to form crust. Bake at 400° for 5 minutes.
Combine drained spinach, onion, dill weed, Feta, cottage cheese and eggs.
Mix well.
Spread over partially baked crust.
Unroll other can of dough into 2 rectangles and place over filling.
Return to oven and bake 20 to 30 minutes or until deep golden brown.
Cut into diamond shaped pieces to serve.
Makes 8 servings.

title: fruit salad supreme
directions: Drain all canned fruit.
In large bowl or square casserole dish mix all fruit except kiwi; add marshmallows and mix.
Add sour cream and blend well together.
Cut tiny slivers of orange peel approximately 1 tablespoon and mix into fruit also fresh strawberries, if available.
Save some whole ones for the top decoration.
Smooth the mixture with back of spoon and sprinkle nuts over the top.
Slice kiwi fruit and make circle by overlapping each slice.
Place a whole strawberry in center of kiwi fruit circle and 1 strawberry on each corner.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Soak oatmeal in sour milk 1 hour.
Add egg and beat well. Add sugar and shortening.
Add flour with salt, baking powder and soda.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen muffins.

title: salmon log(hors d'oeuvres)
directions: Drain salmon.
Remove skin and bones.
Flake salmon with fork. Add softened cream cheese, lemon juice, onion, salt and liquid smoke.
Stir well.
Shape salmon into a 10-inch log.
Chill log in refrigerator overnight.
Combine chopped pecans and parsley.
Roll salmon log in pecan mixture.
Chill 2 or 3 hours.
Slice oblong. Serve with small hot bread or crackers.
Great for luncheons or appetizers.

title: bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Add to warm milk. Add sugar and salt. Add flour and mix well. Put in bowl to raise about double in size. Mix down. Put in 2 loaf pans and let raise well. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate crinkle cookies
directions: Mix oil, chocolate and sugar. Blend in eggs, one at a time. Add vanilla. Stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Drop by teaspoonfuls of dough into confectioners sugar.
Roll into balls in the sugar and place about 2-inches apart on a greased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes. Do not overbake.
Watch until they stop looking "shiny."

title: oven-easy chili-beef
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in large skillet.
Cook over medium heat until browned, stirring occasionally.
Add tomato sauce, chili beans and olives.
Mix well.
Cover bottom of 1 1/2-quart casserole with 1 cup corn chips.
Pour in meat mixture and top with remaining corn chips.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cake roll capri
directions: Combine eggs and salt; beat until thick and lemon colored. Add sugar, a little at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flavoring.
Add pancake mix.
Beat until smooth.
Grease jelly roll pan, 10 x 15 x 1-inch.
Line with waxed paper.
Grease again. Spread batter evenly in pan.

Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes. Sprinkle dry towel generously with confectioners (powdered) sugar. As soon as cake is done, loosen edges and turn out on towel. Peel waxed paper carefully from cake.
Roll up quickly in towel. Let stand 20 minutes.
Unroll.
Spread with filling.
Reroll and frost.

title: mrs. julia spence's strawberry preserves
directions: Cover
berries with boiling water; let stand 3 minutes; drain. Add
cups sugar; boil 5 minutes.
Set off and allow to
stop boiling
completely.
Add
4 more cups sugar; boil 5 minutes.
Put in hot jars and seal.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs with butter and sugar.
Mix will look wet and crumbly.
Spread diet margarine on bottom of glass dish; put graham cracker crumbs in pan and press.
Mix pudding and milk together.
When milk and pudding thickens, pour a thin layer on bottom and a thin layer of Cool Whip.
Add some plain graham cracker crumbs for extra yum!
Alternate layers until you reach the top.
End up with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle some crumbs on top for decoration.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut a thin slice from stem end of each pepper.
Remove all seeds.
Wash inside and out.
Heat 1 cup water and 1/2 teaspoon salt to boiling.
Add peppers; cook 5 minutes. Drain.
Mix remaining ingredients (brown beef).
Stuff each pepper with 1/3 of meat mixture.
Stand peppers upright in an ungreased baking dish.
Cover and bake 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix margarine, butter, sugar and eggs together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and drop on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes about 75 cookies.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook in a casserole dish at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle some stuffing over finished casserole.

title: morales taco shells
directions: Will also need a tortilla press machine and 1 (6 x 8-inch) plastic paper.

title: dump cake(makes 12 to 16 servings)
directions: Dump undrained pineapple into pan; spread evenly.
Dump in pie filling and spread into even layer.
Dump dry cake mix onto cherry layer; spread evenly.
Sprinkle pecans over cake mix.
Put butter over top.

title: sweet and crunchy popcorn and nuts
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Combine popcorn, peanuts and raisins in a 9 x 13-inch pan and set aside.
Combine brown sugar, corn syrup, allspice and salt until well blended.
Add butter and bring to a boil over low heat, stirring constantly, about 5 minutes. Increase heat to medium and cook 5 minutes longer without stirring.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla extract. Immediately pour over popcorn mixture; stir with spoon to coat. Bake 50 minutes, stirring several times.
Spread on greased waxed paper to cool.
Mixture will harden considerably as it cools. When cool, break into bite-sized chunks before packaging.
It makes about 10 cups candied popcorn.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O, using 2 cups boiling water and juice from canned pineapple and water or ice to make 2 cups.
As Jell-O is congealing, mix the cranberry sauce with chopped pineapple slices, orange peel, chopped oranges and chopped nuts.
When Jell-O is consistency of raw egg whites, mix together with fruit and pour into a large mold or casserole dish.
Refrigerate until firm. Great with turkey!

title: baked jack corn
directions: Combine eggs and sour cream in a large bowl. Stir in corn and next 5 ingredients. Pour into a greased 10-inch quiche dish or 2-quart baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and bake 5 more minutes. Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Yield: 6 servings.

title: unleavened bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place 1/2 pound butter in a small pan, then melt in the oven.
Sift the flours (at least once) and mix them thoroughly in a large bowl.
Place some extra white flour (several cups) in a medium bowl.
Measure the baking powder, salt, butter and honey.
Add to the 1 3/4 cups of warm water and stir well.
Grease baking pan with butter and dust with white flour.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Place crescent roll dough on cookie sheet, forming crust. Bake as directed on can until lightly brown.
Cool.

title: asian chicken noodle salad
directions: Boil water in a medium size saucepan.
Break noodles into pan. Cover and let stand for 10 minutes.
Mix dressing, soy sauce, oil and 1 seasoning packet from Ramen noodles.
Add chicken, broccoli, coleslaw and bell pepper.
Toss to mix and coat.
Stir in soaked noodles.
Serves 4.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let stand over night or at least 2 hours before baking.
Put in 9 x 13 baking dish.
Cover with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350 degrees for about 45 minutes.
To make buttered crumbs, melt margarine in skillet or pan and have crumbs dried before mixing them in the melted butter. Can add 3 hard boiled eggs diced up and mix in before putting crumbs on top.
This can be prepared and kept in refrigerator overnight.
Good for saving time on the day you serve a meal.

title: cheese straws(from cateress glenda linstrom)
directions: Sift flour and baking powder into bowl; cut in cheese and butter with a pastry cutter.
Add water and mix well.
Fill a cookie press half full.
Form straws on ungreased cookie sheet, using the star plate.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in 375° oven.

title: chicken crunch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased baking dish. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: minute fudge
directions: Mix confectioners sugar and cocoa, looks like chocolate milk mix, dry. Plop butter on top of dry mix, do no melt. Then pour milk on top, do not stir.

title: no-bake pecan balls
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Shape into balls. Roll in additional sugar.
Store in freezer until ready to serve; thaw.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Toss together the first 4 ingredients and let stand 2 or 3 hours.
Mix next 6 ingredients and put on stove.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Drain excess water off cucumber mix.
(Do not wash.) Add to boiling mixture.
Let come to second boil and fill sterilized jars; seal.

title: easy strawberry cake
directions: Bake the cake mix according to the direction on the box. While the cake is hot from the oven, punch holes in the cake, the more the better.
Pour the condensed milk over the cake and let it cool.
After the cake is cooled, top with strawberries and juice. It will be very moist and delicious.
Great with Cool Whip. Store covered in refrigerator.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cut potatoes into 1/4-inch squares.
Put in glass casserole. Set aside.
Cut bacon into 1/4-inch slices.
Fry bacon so it's crispy.
Add onion while frying bacon.
Fry until clear.
Add flour, water, vinegar, sugar, salt, celery seed and pepper.
Cook on low heat for about 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Mix in with potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cranberry-apple sweet potato bake
directions: Spray pan with cooking spray. Put sweet potatoes, apples and cranberries in pan. Sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon and dot with butter.
Seal with foil.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or 450° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Mix with remaining ingredients and pour into pie or quiche pan.
Top with pie crust.
Vent crust and bake at 350° until filling bubbles and crust browns, about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: aztec bean dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add 1/2 packet taco seasoning and can of beans.
Mix together.
Layer all ingredients in a casserole dish, starting with beans and ground beef mixture, then sour cream, salsa dip, lettuce, green onions, Cheddar cheese, tomatoes and black olives.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: fresh creamed corn
directions: Cut off corn and scrape cob.
Heat butter and oil in skillet; add
corn, salt and pepper.

Mix flour in water and add, then add enough water so corn can cook well before becoming too thick. Cook until corn is tender and thickened to desired consistency. One tablespoon sugar may be added, if desired.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix after each addition.
Stir in flavoring.
Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 to 15 minutes; remove to wire rack.
Cool.

title: hawaiian stuffed chicken breast
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix hot water and margarine in bowl.
Stir in stuffing mix, pepper and 1/2 the pineapple with syrup.
Spoon stuffing in chicken and roll up tightly.
Secure with toothpicks. Place in 9-inch square pan.
Mix remaining pineapple and syrup, vinegar and ginger; spoon over chicken.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: green beans(portuguese style)
directions: Put diced salt pork in bottom of casserole.
Cut beans into 1-inch pieces and add to casserole.
Scatter tomatoes over all. Add bouillon and seasonings.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until beans are tender.

title: ham and poppy seed delights
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients. Horizontally slice all 20 rolls at a time, leaving them attached. Spread both sliced sides of rolls with butter-poppy seed mixture. Put 1 layer of ham and 1 layer of cheese between rolls, cutting ham and cheese to fit as necessary. Another layer of ham may be added as desired, if sliced very thinly. Separate rolls by slicing with a bread knife or other sharp knife. Place on a cookie sheet and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 400°. Makes 60 small sandwiches or appetizers.

title: creamy broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli with salt.
Heat oven to 400°.
Put cooked broccoli in ungreased casserole.
Spread the Cheddar cheese on top.
Mix the Bisquick mix with margarine until crumbly and sprinkle on top of broccoli.
Beat the soup with milk and pour over the top of it all.
Bake for 20 minutes uncovered or until golden brown.

title: baked custard
directions: Beat eggs with fork until yolks and whites are blended.
Add sugar, salt, flavoring and nutmeg.
Mix thoroughly.
Add milk gradually, stirring constantly.
Pour into individual molds, which have been buttered.
Set in pan of warm water.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 to 40 minutes until an inserted knife comes out clean. Makes 4 servings.

title: coneys
directions: Brown hamburger; add salt.
Mix all other ingredients in a pan.
Bring to a boil.
Add hamburger and simmer.

title: claxton fruit cake cookies
directions: Dice the fruit cake into 1/4-inch pieces and set aside.

Mix cake mix, egg, oil and vanilla in large bowl until smooth. Add the fruit cake bits. Roll into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes until slightly brown at 375°. Cool; remove from cookie sheet and place in a bowl that can be sealed.

title: cheesy artichoke cups
directions: Preheat oven 350 degrees. Press wonton wrappers into lightly greased mini-muffin cups. Pat artichoke hearts dry; chop and place in medium bowl. Add mayonnaise, cheese and garlic; mix well. Stir in olives and bell pepper. Spoon into prepared muffin cups. Bake 12-14 minutes or until lightly browned. Remove from oven; cool in pan 2 minutes before carefully removing from pan. Serve warm.

title: roasted mustard potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Spray roasting pan with vegetable oil. Put mustard, paprika, cumin, chili powder and pepper in a large bowl; blend. Prick potatoes with fork and toss in mixture to coat. Place potatoes on pan with a little space in between. Bake for about 45 minutes to 1 hour, until potatoes are tender.

title: broccoli & cauliflower salad
directions: Mix cauliflower, broccoli, cheese and bacon in a bowl. Add dressing made from mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.

title: spicy apple syrup(for pancakes and waffles)
directions: In saucepan, heat apple juice, water, vanilla, spices and sugar.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Combine cornstarch with water to make a smooth paste.
Add to juice, stirring constantly, and continue to cook until thickened, about 5 to 10 minutes. Store in refrigerator.

title: christmas candy
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk, add all other ingredients and mix well. Grease hands.
Form 6 to 8 loaves, wrap in aluminum foil. Store in refrigerator.
Slice before serving.

title: bundt bread
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients.
Let cool.
Mix together the next three ingredients and set aside.
When the sugar, salt, shortening and water mixture cools, add 2 cups of the flour and the eggs.
Stir well and add the yeast mixture.
Gradually add the other 4 cups of flour and stir well.
Cover and allow to rise 45 minutes.
Punch down at this point.
The dough may be refrigerated (well) covered, 1 or 2 days.

title: ann's etouffee
directions: Peel shrimp; place shrimp shells into 2-quart pan.
Add 4 1/2 cups water.
Add chopped carrots, onion, bell pepper, celery, parsley, bay leaves and salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil and simmer about 25 minutes.
Strain and put broth aside and save the broth.

title: almond green beans
directions: Use as many cans of green beans as needed.
Cut ham in small chunks as desired.
Blanch the slivered almonds.
Cook beans and ham together, then add almonds.

title: down home chicken chowder
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; remove from pan and crumble.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons fat.
Brown mushrooms, then add onions and thyme and cook until tender.
Add bacon and remaining ingredients. Heat, stirring occasionally.
Serves 8.

title: venison steak
directions: Hack venison well.
Cut in serving size pieces.
Add milk to eggs.
Dip steak in this mixture.
Mix flour, salt and pepper to your taste.
Now, dip steak in the flour mixture.
Cook until batter on steak turns a golden brown.
Watch carefully and do not overcook.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef in oil; add tomato soup.
Make paste and stir in chili powder, flour and water.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer about 45 minutes.

title: mixed fruit salad
directions: Mix fruit pieces. Whisk together yogurt, orange juice and honey.
Pour over fruit.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: cousin john's cajun scampi
directions: Melt butter in a high-sided frying pan.
Saute chopped onions and garlic, being careful not to brown them.
When the garlic and onions are cooked, add the peeled, deveined shrimp.
Add as much Tabasco as desired, 5 or 6 dashes.
Cook shrimp for 4 to 5 minutes until pink.
To serve, place frying pan on table with Italian or French bread.
Dip bread in the butter sauce.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening; gradually add sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well.
Combine buttermilk and soda. Stir until soda dissolves.
Add flour to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk mixture, beginning and ending with flour.
Mix after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Add 1 cup black walnuts and coconut.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff. Fold into batter.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening, then add eggs and mashed bananas. Sift together the flour, soda and salt; add to mixture.
Fold in sour cream and chopped nuts.
Bake in greased bread pan for approximately 1 hour at 350°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream sugar, butter, flour and salt.
Add eggs, Karo, vanilla and pecans.
Add to first mixture.
Bake in 9-inch pie shell for 1 hour at 350°.
I also put pecans on top.

title: t.n.t. candy
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips together on low heat. Remove from heat when melted.
Add chow mein noodles and peanuts. Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet lined with wax paper.
Chill in refrigerator.
When set, remove from cookie sheet and store in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: fish worcestershire
directions: Roll fish fillets.
Place in well buttered casserole dish. Combine soup, Worcestershire sauce and thyme.
Pour over fish. Bake uncovered in a 425° oven for 20 minutes or until fish flakes when tested with a fork.
Sprinkle with fresh parsley and serve with lemon wedges.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: corn casserole
directions: Add egg to corn and rice.
Mix ingredients well.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: supreme cheesecake
directions: Mix together crumbs, butter and 1/4 cup sugar. Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
